Name: Aardvark
Summary: The aardvark (Orycteropus afer) is a nocturnal mammal native to sub-Saharan Africa. It uses its powerful claws to dig burrows, and primarily feeds on termites and other insects. Despite its appearance, it is most closely related to the elephant.

Name: Akagi (5 Ronin)
Summary: Ronin Akagi returns home from war to find his house burnt to ashes, and his wife and seven year old son dead at the hands of the Daimyo. Vowing revenge, he endlessly stalks the soldiers of Daimyo to slaughter them mercilessly, considering himself already dead.

Name: Alabai
Summary: The Central Asian Shepherd Dog, also known as alabai is a livestock guardian dog breed. Traditionally, the breed was used for guarding sheep and goat herds, as well as to protect and for guard duty. This breed presents a robust dog of greater than average size with great strength and power.

Name: AMT Baby AutoMag
Summary: The AMT Baby AutoMag is a very rare limited production American .22 Long Rifle pistol.

Name: Arapaima
Summary: Arapaimas are freshwater fish residing in the Amazon River and one of the largest species of freshwater fish.[1] Arapaima normally reach lengths of up to 2 meters, although in rare cases they can exceed 2.5 meters and over 100 kg.[2][1]

Name: Arkadimon (Cyber Sleuth)
Key: '''Arkadimon Baby''' | '''Arkadimon Rookie''' | '''Arkadimon Champion''' | '''Arkadimon Ultimate''' | '''Arkadimon Mega''' | '''Arkadimon Ultra'''
Summary: Arkadimon is one of the main antagonists of Digimon Story: Cyber Sleuth Hacker's Memory. It was imprisoned in Underzero but was freed when the worlds connected. Reacting to Ryuji's negative emotions, It becomes his partner Digimon and causes havoc in both Eden and the Real world.

Name: Bacteria (Kane Pixels)
Summary: Bacteria, are a species of entity that are recurring characters in the analog horror series The Backrooms. Bacteria resemble tall, thin, black humanoids that appear to be made of wires. Bacteria first was shown in The Backrooms: Found Footage, the first episode of the series, in which one chases and presumably kills Kane Pints. It exhibits similar behavior in the episodes Found Footage #2 and Pitfalls and is seen climbing on the ceiling in The Backrooms- Motion Detected. In Autopsy Report, more is learned about the nature of Bacteria, with it being implied to be a mutated strain of the hay bacillus disease. Despite all this, much about Bacteria is still left to be seen.

Name: Beretta ARX160
Summary: The Beretta ARX160 is an Italian modular rifle manufactured by Beretta. Developed for the Italian Armed Forces as part of the Soldato Futuro (English: "Future Soldier") program, the ARX160 was launched in 2008 as a commercial weapon system independent from the Soldato Futuro ensemble, complete with a companion single-shot 40×46mm NATO low-velocity grenade launcher, called the GLX160, which can be mounted underneath the rifle or used with an ad hoc stock system as a stand-alone weapon.

Name: Black Fox (Marvel Comics)
Summary: A master thief past his prime, Black Fox had taught best of the best in his heydays, but only looks now to save up for his retirement to the French Riviera.

Name: Blink (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Clarice Ferguson, first discovered her mutant abilities after a traumatic and bloody accident, which left her fearful of her own powers. Alongside other young mutants, she was captured by the techno-organic Phalanx, who sought to assimilate their abilities. In a selfless act of bravery, Clarice sacrificed herself to save her fellow captives—an act that deeply affected the survivors and inspired them to form the team known as Generation X.

Name: Bow (Real World)
Summary: Bows are among the earliest weapons known to man. A bow is a simplistic weapon in design; simply put, a lightweight arrow is shot with the pull of a string. While bows were made obsolete in favor of guns in war, bows are still used in hunting and sporting events (particularly the Olympic sport of archery). More recently, compound bows were developed, boasting stronger draw weights than modern recurve bows. Multiple arrows can be fired in a single shot, although generally multiple arrows being fired at once aren't as effective as firing a single shot.

Name: Brown Pelican
Summary: Brown Pelicans are one of the 8 members of the genus Pelecanus. The genus is known for its gluttony and willingness to eat nearly anything. Surprisingly, Brown Pelicans are more grounded in terms of their prey variety.

Name: Burmese Python
Summary: The Burmese python is a python that is once considered a subspecies of the Indian python before it was split into its own species in 2009. While Burmese pythons are Vulnerable species in its native range in India, Burmese pythons have taken an invasive stronghold in Florida, with its presence mostly extirpating many native species within their range.

Name: California Sea Lion
Summary: The California sea lion (Zalophus californianus) is a species of eared seal native to the coastlines of western North America. It is the fastest species of seal in the world, and can swim up to 25 miles per hour.

Name: Cassandra Nova (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Johnny Storm: And I’ll tell you who ‘her’ is. Cassandra Nova, a megalomaniacal psychotic asshole, a finger-lickin’ dead-inside pixie slab of third rate dime-store nut-milk, and I’ll tell you what she can do. Deadpool: I’m listening. Johnny Storm: She can lick my goddamn cinnamon ring clean and kick rocks all the way to bald hell. In fact, I don’t give a shit if she removes all my skin and pops me like some nightmarish blood balloon. If the last thing I do in this godforsaken cum gutter existence is light that fuck box on fire, I still won’t die happy.

Name: Cassowary
Summary: Cassowaries are known as the third tallest bird (behind the emu and ostrich) and the second heaviest bird (behind the ostrich). Cassowaries, however, are #1 in the aggression department, having been known to attack humans, occasionally fatally. If you see a cassowary, do not crouch or turn your back against it; instead, keep a good eye on the cassowary and move away. Female cassowaries average at a weight of 58.5 kg while males average in at 29-34 kg. Of all birds, the cassowary is among the most closely related to their dinosaur ancestors.

Name: Chameleon (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Born a Russian citizen named Dmitri Smerdyakov (Russian: Дмитрий Смердяков), he was the half-brother of Sergei Kravinoff.

Name: Charles Xavier
Summary: Charles Xavier (also known as Professor X) is a fictional superhero who appears in American comic books published by Marvel Comics as well as in a number of television and movie adaptations. The character was created in 1963 by writer Stan Lee and artist Jack Kirby, and has been a frequent if not regular character in most X-Men-related fiction since the beginning.

Name: Colt Single Action Army
Summary: The Colt Single Action Army, also known as the Single Action Army, SAA, Model P, Peacemaker and M1873, is a single-action revolver with a revolving cylinder holding six metallic cartridges. It was designed for the U.S. government service revolver trials of 1872 by Colt's Patent Firearms Manufacturing Company—today's Colt's Manufacturing Company—and was adopted as the standard military service revolver until 1892.

Name: Comet the Super-Horse (Pre-Crisis)
Summary: Comet the Super-Horse is the pet horse of Supergirl. Originally a centaur in ancient Greece named Biron, he was given a potion by the witch Circe after he saved her from water poisoning. The potion was intended to turn him into a full human but instead it turned him into a full horse. As compensation Circe granted Biron superpowers and immortality, but he was then sealed in an asteroid by a sorcerer who tried to poison Circe. Years later Supergirl traveled to this asteroid and her ship's passing broke the forcefield that was trapping him, and they became friends.

Name: Condiment King (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Mitchell Mayo, once an average guy went inexplicably crazy and donned the identity of the Condiment King to cause crime. He was shown tormenting multiple policemen with his special designed sauce, until he was swiftly defeated by Batgirl and Robin. He was then taken to Arkham Asylum, where he eventually was able to work in the kitchen and fuel his obsession, as well as improve upon his formula. This was further aided by Poison Ivy, who taught him vast knowledge on roots, herbs, and spices. Years later, he would get out of Arkham and be "jokerized". Jokerization is stated to amplify the infected's personality, which actually made Mitchell a credible threat. This would almost cause the Birds of Prey to lose to him, as they though he was a joke. It is later stated due to the nature of Condiment King's obsession/portrayal as a joke, juries and parole boards don't take him seriously, thus allowing him to be set free on Gotham again and again. During Final Crisis Aftermath, Mitchell was one of Immortus' followers, The Army of the Endangered, and was cybernetically enhanced by the brilliant Professor Achilles Milo. He was the one to introduce the "Human Flame" to the group, which would be a mistake. Human Flame would rebel, and along with Seductress, kill every member of The Army of the Endangered, including Mitchell.

Name: Cottonmouth (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Cornell Stokes, also known as Cottonmouth, is a crime boss stationed in Harlem, New York City. His negative influence on the people of Harlem led him to be opposed by Luke Cage.

Name: Crossbow
Summary: A crossbow is a type of elastic ranged weapon in similar principle to a bow, consisting of a bow-like assembly mounted horizontally on a main frame called a tiller, which is handheld in a similar fashion to the stock of a long gun. It shoots arrow-like projectiles called bolts or quarrels. The medieval European crossbow was called by many other names, most of which were derived from the word ballista, an ancient Greek torsion siege engine similar in appearance.

Name: Dagger (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Tandy Bowen’s life started in privilege, but it was a life without the love of her parents, that made her decide to run away from home. While living on the streets she met Tyrone Johnson, but they were both kidnapped by scientists that wanted test subjects for their new experimental drugs. Although most of the test subjects died, Tandy and Tyrone survived, and as a side effect awakened powers. Now under the alias of Dagger, she becomes a personification of light that promises to rid the streets of all drugs in an attempt to stop what happened to her from happening to anyone else.

Name: Dimetrodon
Summary: The Dimetrodon was among the earliest land animals, belonging to a proto-mammalian group known as synapsids. Dimetrodons were predatory creatures, with larger dimetrodons often being apex predators. Despite being confused with dinosaurs, Dimetrodons had a temporal range between 295 and 272 million years ago and were more closely related to mammals than modern reptiles, although they were not direct ancestors.

Name: Dinopithecus
Summary: Dinopithecus was a giant baboon that lived in Africa from the Pliocene to the Pleistocene. It is thought to have been bigger than a large man, one of the largest Primates to have ever existed. They lived alongside Homo Erectus; some argue that Homo Erectus drove them to extinction by killing all the young and sub-adults of their species as evidenced by ninety juvenile giant baboon bodies thought to have been killed by the human.

Name: Django Freeman
Summary: Tier: 10-A. 9-C with firearms. 8-C with preparation

Name: Ekko (Arcane)
Summary: nan

Name: English Mastiff
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:English_mastiff_barking_sound.mp3

Name: Eryops
Summary: Eryops is a large semi aquatic temnospondyl amphibian, the name of which comes from the Greek words ἐρύειν (eryein), which means 'drawn-out,' and ὤψ (ops), which means 'face.' The sole species Erypos megacephalus. It lived in the southwestern United States 299–278 million years ago, predominantly during the early Permian in what is now Texas,[1] while older specimens found in New Mexico from the late Carboniferous.[2] It inhabited lowlands around various bodies of freshwater, where it would hunt. Among the largest animals of it's time, they could reach 1.5 to 2 meters long on average,[2] and the largest could grow to 3 meters in length, with a mass of 102-222 kg.[3] Based on the structure of its vertebrae, limb girdle and ribs, this heavily built creature was well adapted for traversing land for prolonged periods of time.[4]

Name: Escapade (Marvel Comics)
Summary: When young Shela Sexton discovered both her mutant abilities and gender identity in quick succession, she was shunned by her parents and ran away with her best friend, Morgan Red. Determined to carve out her own path, she later emerged as the tech-clad thief known as Escapade, using her powers to target corrupt organizations and individuals—while Morgan provided crucial technical support.

Name: Firestorm (Ronnie Raymond) (Post-Crisis)
Key: '''Ronnie Raymond''' | '''Firestorm (Ronnie Raymond + Other Person)''' | '''Firestorm (Jason Rusch + Ronnie Raymond)'''
Summary: The original Firestorm was distinguished by his integrated dual identity. High school student Ronnie Raymond and Nobel Prize-winning physicist Martin Stein were caught in a nuclear accident that allowed them to fuse into the "nuclear man" Firestorm. Due to Stein's being unconscious during the accident, Raymond was prominently in command of the Firestorm form with Stein as a voice of reason inside his mind. The banter between the two was a hallmark of their adventures.

Name: Giant Anteater
Summary: The giant anteater is the largest of the four extant species of anteater. Unlike other anteaters and sloths, the giant anteater is a mostly terrestrial animal. The giant anteater is recognizable for its long snout, bushy tail, long foreclaws, and distinctive fur markings. The giant anteater's bold marking serves as warning coloration. The giant anteater has been featured in pre-Colombian myths and folklore and popular culture.

Name: Gorilla
Summary: The Gorilla is the largest genus of primate that currently roams the Earth, and is one of the closest living relatives to humans apart from chimps. Gorillas are found in Sub-Saharan Africa, and they can cover a wide range of elevations.

Name: Gray Wolf
Summary: The Gray wolf is an infamous carnivorous animal found all in the Americas and Eurasia. It is known to humans more than almost any other predatory animal, with more importance to human culture than most others. Although the fear of wolves is common in humans, wolf attacks are very rare.

Name: Guanlong
Summary: Guanlong is a genus of small proceratosaurid theropod family that lived during the late Jurassic in China. Its name comes from the Chinese words 冠, which means "crown", and 龍, which means "dragon." Its most distinctive feature is the crest on its head, which due to its fragile nature, was most likely for display.[1] It is the earliest discovered tyrannosauroid, and distantly related to the much larger and more famous Tyrannosaurus rex, which would emerge 92 million years later.

Name: Guido Mista
Summary: Guido Mista is a major character in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part V: Vento Aureo. He joins the Neopolitian gang Passione after his vigilantism almost gets him sent for twenty years in prison, but is saved by Bruno Bucciarati. He becomes involved in the week-long mission of protecting Trish Una and eventually to assassinate the Boss of Passione himself.

Name: Heatwave (DC Comics)
Summary: Mick Rory or better known as Heatwave is one of the Flash's Rogues and is utterly obsessed with fire to such as extent that in his youth he let his parents burn to death.

Name: Helmut Zemo (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Colonel Helmut Zemo was a member of a death squad in Sokovian Armed Forces who lost his family to Ultron during the Battle of Sokovia. Zemo blamed the Avengers and sought revenge on them. He knew the Avengers could not be beaten through force, and instead attempted to manipulate them into destroying each other and took advantage of the friction between the Avengers during the signing of the Sokovia Accords by committing acts of terrorism and framing James Barnes, causing further conflict between Steve Rogers and Tony Stark. Zemo would eventually be caught by the Black Panther and imprisoned.

Name: Herrerasaurus
Summary: Herrerasaurus is a dinosaur that lived during the Late Triassic period, approximately 231 to 228 million years ago.[1] It is considered one of the earliest known dinosaurs and belongs to the group called theropods, which includes famous dinosaurs like Tyrannosaurus rex and Velociraptor.[1] Herrerasaurus was first discovered in the Ischigualasto Formation of northwestern Argentina in the 1960s.[1] The name "Herrerasaurus" is derived from the name of the rancher Victorino Herrera, who owned the land where the fossils were found.[1]

Name: Homo Erectus
Summary: Homo Erectus was an early species of human. It lived around the early Pleistocene and it seemed to be a migrant species. This hominid was remarkable in the fact that their species survived until just 50,000 years ago. This early hominid showed the ability of using fire (As torches, harden clay and cooking).

Name: Hyneria
Summary: Hyneria is a genus of lobe finned fish, named after the village of Hyner in Pennsylvania where it was first discovered.[1] It lived in the Famennian part of the Devonion period, which was around 371.1 to 359.3 million years ago, and was an apex predator in freshwater environments it inhabited.

Name: Invisible Woman (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Dr. Susan "Sue" Richards (née 'Storm) was a college student before she was exposed to high levels of cosmic radiation when boyfriend and scientist, Dr. Reed Richards, took her with her younger brother, Johnny Storm and pilot Ben Grimm, into space in the stolen rocket Marvel-1. The radiation mutated her and her friends, turning her invisible and allowing her to create forcefields. Together they became the Fantastic Four, a team of adventurers who explored space, time and alternate dimensions and saved the world along the way from science-based threats, with Sue going by the name the Invisible Woman.

Name: Iron Man (Marvel Comics)
Key: '''Human''' | '''Extremis Enhanced and RepulsorTech Node''' | '''With Iron Man Armors''' | '''Cosmic Iron Man'''
Summary: Iron Man, or Tony Stark, is the main hero of a comic by the same name. Stark: an inventive genius, industrialist, and multi-billionaire, went to Vietnam to oversee a field test for one of his transistorized weapons, that his company Stark Industries made.

Name: J. Jonah Jameson
Summary: J. Jonah Jameson is the bossy and irascible editor-in-chief of the Daily Bugle. His dislike of superhumans, most particularly the Spider-Man (which stems from a combination of envy, distrust, and his son's accomplishments being overshadowed) leads him to tirelessly defame and vilify him at every opportunity with his newspaper, to the point where he has sometimes worked with supervillains to try and take him down.

Name: Jack Carver
Summary: Jack, a former United States Army Special Forces soldier, has left his past behind and offers his services as a freelance boat charter in the South Pacific. He is employed by a reporter named Valerie Constantine to take her to a mysterious island, once occupied by the Japanese during the war, claiming to study its little-known World War II ruins. When Valerie goes ashore alone on a jetski, Jack anchors down shortly before his boat is destroyed by a missile launched by an army of mercenaries occupying the island.

Name: Jayce (Arcane)
Summary: Jayce Talis is a scientist and innovator, and, after years of success leading the city's scientific and consequently its economic progress, is currently the Head of the Council of Piltover.

Name: Jean Grey (Marvel Comics)
Key: '''Jean Grey''' | '''Phoenix Force''' | '''White Phoenix of the Crown'''
Summary: Jean Grey-Summers (born Jean Elaine Grey) is a fictional superhero appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics. The character has been known under the aliases Marvel Girl, Phoenix, and Dark Phoenix. Created by writer Stan Lee and artist Jack Kirby, the character first appeared in The X-Men #1 (September 1963).

Name: Jean-Luc Picard
Key: '''TV Picard''' | '''Movie Picard''' | '''Piloting auxiliary crafts''' | '''Assimilated into the Borg'''
Summary: Jean-Luc Picard, known to the Borg Collective by his designation of Locutus, was a celebrated Starfleet officer, archaeologist and diplomat who served during the latter two thirds of the 24th century. The highlights of his career were centered around assignments as commanding officer of the Federation starships: USS Stargazer, USS Enterprise-D, and the USS Enterprise-E. In these roles, Picard not only witnessed the major turning points of recent galactic history, but also played a key role in them, from making first contact as captain of the Federation's flagship with 27 alien species, including the Ferengi and the Borg.

Name: Kangal Dog
Summary: The Kangal dog is a breed of guard dog originating from Kangal Province, Sivas, Turkey, used to defend both livestock herds and human families. Unlike many other domestic dogs, Kangals are rather antisocial and do not like being around too many people.

Name: Kumimanu Fordycei
Summary: Kumimanu Fordycei is the largest and heaviest penguin to have ever lived, living in New Zealand during the eocene over 55 million years ago.[1]

Name: Leopard
Summary: The leopard is a big cat that lives in Africa, Asia, and the Caucasus. Unlike the other big cats that it lives with, the lion, and the cheetah, who rely on either using their strength to overpower animals and using their speed to chase animals respectively. The leopard relies on ambushing their prey from trees.

Name: Leopard Seal
Summary: Leopard seals are the third largest species of pinniped, behind the walrus and the elephant seal. Leopard seals are named after their spotted coat and are known to have eaten a wide range in prey, ranging from penguins to other seals. Leopard seals are 2.4-3.5 meters long and weigh around 200 to 600 kg.

Name: Llama
Summary: Llamas are very social animals and live with other members of their species as a herd. The wool produced by a llama is very soft and lanolin-free. Llamas are intelligent and can learn simple tasks after a few repetitions. When using a pack, they can carry about 25 to 30% of their body weight for 8 to 13 km (5–8 miles).

Name: Madame Xanadu (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Madame Xanadu is an immortal sorceress with great skill in seeing the future. Thanks to this ability, she was the one to put together the team known as the Justice League Dark, to stop the Enchantress from destroying the world.

Name: Makarov Pistol
Summary: The Makarov pistol or PM (Russian: Пистолет Макарова, Pistolet Makarova, literally Makarov's Pistol) is a Russian semi-automatic pistol. Under the project leadership of Nikolay Fyodorovich Makarov, it became the Soviet Union's standard military and police side arm in 1951, and still sees widespread use in modern-day Russia.

Name: Man-Bat (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Studying methods to cure deafness by experimenting on bats, brilliant biologist Kirk Langstrom accidentally unveiled a formula that would go on to create one of Batman's most tragic foes, Man-Bat.

Name: Max (Sharkboy and Lavagirl)
Summary: Max is a fictional character who appears as the main protagonist of the movie The Adventures of Sharkboy and Lavagirl. He is a lonely boy who uses his dreams to escape reality. He records these dreams in his Dream Journal which was given to him by his grandfather. Max as the Daydreamer is the most powerful person on Planet Drool. Sharkboy and Lavagirl try to help Max remember this as he is the only one who can save Planet Drool.

Name: Megamouth Shark
Summary: The megamouth shark (Megachasma pelagios) is a species of mackerel shark endemic to deep waters worldwide. Like the whale shark and the basking shark, it is a filter feeder, and harmless to humans.

Name: Mission Sub-1
Summary: The Mission SUB-1 was designed to be the most accurate crossbow on the market. The name "SUB-1" means "under 1 inch".

Name: Mongoose
Summary: Mongooses are small mammals popularized by Rudyard Kipling's "Rikki-Tikki-Tavi." They are known as a natural predator of venomous snakes, most famously cobras. Despite this, the mongoose is a small creature, with the 29 species ranging in weight from 320 grams to 5 kg.

Name: Motormouth (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Young orphan Harley Davis was abandoned on the streets of London's East End, and rough-housed her way to the cusp of adulthood, at which point her foul-mouthed demeanor had earned her the nickname Motormouth.

Name: Neanderthal
Summary: The Neanderthals were an early species (or sub-species) of humans that lived during the Middle and Low Pleistocene in Europe and West-Asia until as recently as ~40,000 years ago.

Name: Nothosaurus
Summary: Nothosaurus is a genus of sauropterygian reptiles that lived around 240–210 million years ago, throughout the mid to late Triassic. Its name comes from the Greek words νόθος (nothos), which means "illegitimate," and σαῦρος (sauros), which means "lizard." It was widespread throughout the world, with 12 species having been found in North Africa, Europe, and China, inhabiting the ancient Tethys Ocean and its shores. These sea reptiles were likely related to plesiosaurs and pliosaurs that would later emerge, with Nothosaur-like reptiles thought to have given rise to them.

Name: Orangutan
Summary: The Orangutan is the only Great Ape besides humans native to Asia and the second largest. They are the third closest related animal to humans apart from Gorilla and Chimpanzee respectively.

Name: Overdrive (Marvel Comics)
Summary: James Beverley was once a boy who dreamed to become a superhero like his hero Spider-Man. However, after failing to obtain superpowers in any way and proving himself to be inept at martial arts, he resigned himself to become a motorist like his father. However, after an accident left him seriously injured, he was approached by Mr. Negative, who sought his talents as a driver and promised to enhance his abilities through a swarm of nanobacteria that would allow him to transform any vehicle he came into contact with, as well as heal his injuries.

Name: Pig (Real World)
Summary: Domestic pigs are pigs raised for meat, leather, or simply as pets. Pigs that either escape or get released into the wild are known as feral pigs and regain their fur. These feral pigs are considered an invasive species and are often targeted by hunters.

Name: Protoceratops
Summary: Protoceratops was a herbivorous ceratopsian during the late cretaceous period and a smaller predecessor to Triceratops, albeit moderately large compared to humans.[1] Protoceratops unlike other ceratopsians didn't have eye horns or a large nose.[1] While smaller for a ceratopsian, they still weighed 180 kg (400 lb) and had a length of 1.8 m.[1] Protoceratops is a well-known dinosaur since its fossils are common.[2]

Name: Puma Concolor
Summary: The cougar (Puma concolor), also commonly known as the puma, mountain lion, panther or catamount, is a large felid of the subfamily Felinae native to the Americas. Its range, from the Canadian Yukon to the southern Andes of South America, is the widest of any large wild terrestrial mammal in the Western Hemisphere. An adaptable, generalist species, the cougar is found in most American habitat types. It is the biggest cat in North America, and the second-heaviest cat in the New World after the jaguar. Secretive and largely solitary by nature, the cougar is properly considered both nocturnal and crepuscular, although daytime sightings do occur. The cougar is more closely related to smaller felines, including the domestic cat (subfamily Felinae), than to any species of subfamily Pantherinae, of which only the jaguar is native to the Americas.

Name: Red Kangaroo
Summary: The red kangaroo (Macropus rufus) is a species of marsupial native to Australia. It is the largest living marsupial, and the largest land-dwelling mammal in Australia. They are notable for their powerful jumps and kicks, which can deliver over 850 PSI of pressure.

Name: Regina Mills
Summary: Queen Regina, more commonly known as The Evil Queen and more recently, The Good Queen, is one of the main characters of Once Upon a Time, as well as the main fairytale antagonist. Filled with a deep hatred for Snow White ever since a tragic incident years ago, Regina makes it her life's mission to destroy the happy endings of the former and everyone else in the fairytale world. Her hatred for people led her to create the dark curse which sent all fairytale characters to a small town named Storybrooke. There she lives as Mayor Regina Mills, the stern adoptive mother of Henry Mills who sets out to stop his birth mother and Snow White's daughter, Emma Swan, from breaking her curse. Once the curse is broken, Regina finds herself in a vulnerable state and goes on a path of redemption to win back Henry's love. With this, she is eventually able to make the full transition from villain to hero.

Name: Rogue (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Anna Marie is a mutant who ran from home because of her aunt's controlling nature. As a runaway, already going by the name Rogue, she is found by Mystique who adopted her. She founds out in the worst way that she is a mutant by almost killing her first boyfriend, realizing that she couldn't have a normal life anymore she joins Brotherhood of Evil Mutants. On one of her missions she fights Ms. Marvel and by mistake permanently absorbs her powers almost killing her in the process. Didn't take long to realize that Carol Danvers memories were affecting her to the point of controlling her, so she asks Charles Xavier for help, after a long time of training and living her life as if she was cursed, she finally managed to control her powers and have a love life with Gambit.

Name: Ruger 10/22
Summary: The Ruger 10/22 is a semi-automatic rimfire rifle. It was created and distributed in 1964 and is mostly used by small game hunters, for pest eradication, as well as plinking and target practice.

Name: Slyde (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Jalome Beacher was a talented chemical engineer working in the design and development laboratory of Beemont Manufacturing who created a chemical coating that, when applied to any object, eliminated all friction between that object and surfaces. Beacher was about to unveil his discovery when Beemont was purchased by a larger organization and a man named Rockwall was placed in charge. The research and development lab was closed and Beacher was fired. He decided to build his own company founded on the non-stick chemical, but discovered that no bank would lend the money needed without a sizeable down payment.

Name: Snow Leopard
Summary: The snow leopard (Panthera uncia), also known as the ounce[1], is a felid in the genus Panthera native to the mountain ranges of Central and South Asia. Unlike common leopards, the snow leopard's fur is whitish to grey with black spots on head and neck, with larger rosettes on the back, flanks and bushy tail. The snow leopard is also widely used in heraldry and as an emblem in Central Asia.

Name: Spotted Hyena
Summary: The spotted hyena (Crocuta crocuta), also known as the laughing hyena, is a carnivorous animal found in all of Sub-Saharan Africa. The species is, however, experiencing declines outside of protected areas due to habitat loss and poaching. The species may have originated in Asia, and once ranged throughout Europe for at least one million years until the end of the Late Pleistocene.

Name: Stature (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Cassandra Eleanor "Cassie" Lang is the daughter of Scott Lang and Maggie Lang. Fascinated by the Quantum Realm, Lang invented the Quantum Satellite, which resulted in her, her father and the van Dyne family being shrunken deep into the Realm, being trapped in Axia. Wishing to aid the Freedom Fighters in spite of Ant-Man's denies, she donned the Stature suit to battle against Kang's Empire. However, Stature and Ant-Man were captured by M.O.D.O.K. and questioned by Kang the Conqueror, who used her life as leverage for Ant-Man to retrieve the Multiversal Engine Core. Once she escaped, Stature made a speech across Axia to motivate the oppressed citizens to revolve against Kang and his army before facing off M.O.D.O.K. and returning home with her family.

Name: Striped Hyena
Summary: The striped hyena (Hyaena hyaena) is a species of hyena native to North and East Africa, the Middle East, the Caucasus, Central Asia and the Indian subcontinent. It is the only extant species in the genus Hyaena.

Name: Sun Bear
Summary: The Sun Bear is the smallest bear species in the world. They are rare and elusive animals found in the forests of Asia. Due to this fact, much is not known about the Sun Bear, at least in comparison to other bear species. They are known for their small size, long tongues, and their dog-like faces.

Name: Tenchi Masaki
Key: '''Base Form''' | '''With the Juraian armor and the Tenchi-ken''' | '''Awakened Power''' | '''New Timeline''' | '''Ascended self'''
Summary: Tenchi Masaki (柾木 天地, Masaki Tenchi) is the main protagonist of the Tenchi Muyo! series. Tenchi was a normal boy until he unsealed Ryoko Hakubi, and became the center of events surrounding the highest authority of the galaxy, Jurai. In the Ryo-Ohki continuity, he's actually the grandson of Yosho, the crown prince of Jurai as well as one of the only beings who's able to create Light Hawk Wings as a result of Tokimi's disruption of space-time in the hope of creating a being stronger than her and her sisters.

Name: Thorvin Twinbeard
Summary: A gifted engineer, Thorvin Twinbeard is a dwarf who is working for Xanathar's Guild, making Xanathar a contraption which will pulverize those he petrifies.

Name: Trejo Pistol
Summary: The Trejo pistol (pronounced tray-ho), and its sub-variant, the Trejo machine pistol, is a Mexican pistol or machine pistol. The machine pistol sub-variant has the distinction of being the smallest fully-automatic weapon ever produced.

Name: Truman Burbank
Summary: Christoff: Well say something god dammit, you are on television... you are live to the whole world. Truman: In case I don't see ya, Good Afternoon, Good Evening and Good Night.

Name: Tsunemori Akane
Summary: Akane Tsunemori is an Inspector of the MWPSB (Ministry of Welfare's Public Safety Bureau) in Division 1, and the main protagonist of Psycho-Pass.

Name: Ursa Major (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Mikhail Ursus' mutant powers of turning into a bear manifested at an early age when he was recruited into Russia's Super Soldier program. Rising to the top of his class, he donned the name Ursa Major and became Russia's longest-surviving superhero.

Name: Walther PPK
Summary: The Walther PPK pistol is a blowback-operated semi-automatic pistol made famous by the James Bond movies. Today, PPK pistols are manufactured by Carl Walther GmbH Sportwaffen in Germany or under license from Walther in France and the United States. These pistols feature an exposed hammer, a double-action trigger mechanism, a single-column magazine, and a fixed barrel which also acts as the guide rod for the gun's single recoil spring.

Name: West Indian Manatee
Summary: The West Indian manatee (Trichechus manatus), also known as the sea cow, is a large species of marine mammal native to the Caribbean and the east coast of the United States. It is herbivorous, and primarily grazes on seagrass.

Name: White-Tailed Deer
Summary: White-tailed deer is the most widely-distributed wild ungulate in the Americas. Their native range ranges from Canada and the United States all the way down to Colombia, Venezuela, and even Ecuador.

Name: Aardvark
Summary: The aardvark (Orycteropus afer) is a nocturnal mammal native to sub-Saharan Africa. It uses its powerful claws to dig burrows, and primarily feeds on termites and other insects. Despite its appearance, it is most closely related to the elephant.

Name: African Wild Dog (Real World)
Summary: The African wild dog (Lycaon pictus), also called the painted wolf or Cape hunting dog, is a canine native to sub-Saharan Africa. It is the largest indigenous canine in Africa, and the only extant member of the genus Lycaon, which is distinguished from Canis by dentition highly specialised for a hypercarnivorous diet, and a lack of dewclaws.

Name: Amadeus Cho
Summary: Mere minutes after achieving the highest score ever on the Excello Soap Company’s “Brain Fight” internet game, earning the title “Mastermind Excello,” 16-year-old Amadeus Cho was approached by a woman called Agent Sexton, representing an unidentified agency wishing to train him. Following his refusal, his Arizona home was blown up, killing his parents and sister, but Amadeus escaped, arriving in Jackalope, New Mexico the following morning. Contacting Sexton, he dismissed her claim that a second agency was responsible. Adopting an orphaned coyote pup, Amadeus confronted a helicopter sent by his enemies, deflecting the aim of one of the attacker’s gun to distract another attacker, whose misfired missile, whether by accident or design, struck bystander Bruce Banner, triggering his transformation into the Hulk. The Hulk quickly disabled the helicopter and took Amadeus and the pup to safety before departing, earning the boy’s undying devotion.

Name: American Pit Bull
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Australopithecus
Summary: Australopithecus was the first bipedal ape to have ever existed and was the closest related animal to humans, apart from other humans themselves. Although they are the closest to us, they aren't close enough to be called human.

Name: Bailey Hoskins (Worst X-Man Ever)
Summary: In an alternate universe, Bailey Hoskins thought of himself as an unremarkable boy, part of no clique and having no notable hobbies, until the day his parents reveal to him that he may be a mutant. Excited at the prospects, he heads to Xavier's to find out about himself, and learns he only has the ability to blow himself up like a "human firework".

Name: Benjamin Franklin (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Benjamin Franklin is the historic founding father of the United States of America. His life remains mostly the same as in our real world, but he had somehow found a way to cheat death and remain as a form of electrical apparition. He became a frequent ally of Deadpool after assisting him in getting rid of the zombified presidents.

Name: Black Spiny-Tailed Iguana
Summary: The black spiny-tailed iguana (Ctenosaura similis) is a species of iguana native to Mexico and Central America, and has been introduced to Florida. It is the fastest species of lizard in the world.

Name: Blink (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Clarice Ferguson, first discovered her mutant abilities after a traumatic and bloody accident, which left her fearful of her own powers. Alongside other young mutants, she was captured by the techno-organic Phalanx, who sought to assimilate their abilities. In a selfless act of bravery, Clarice sacrificed herself to save her fellow captives—an act that deeply affected the survivors and inspired them to form the team known as Generation X.

Name: Blizzard (Gregor Shapanka)
Summary: Dr. Gregor Shapanka, Ph.D., an employee of Stark Industries, was conducting private research into a means for achieving physical immortality, who got fired for attempting to steal from Anthony Stark's vault.

Name: Bobby Singer
Summary: Robert Steven "Bobby" Singer (1950-2012) was a hunter, an old friend of John Winchester, and over time evolved into a father-figure for John's sons Sam and Dean. He was also one of the longest lasting recurring characters, appearing in every season so far.

Name: Bull Terrier
Summary: The bull terrier is a breed of terrier developed in the 19th century as a fighting dog. Over the years, the breed has shifted from this original purpose to become a companion and show dog. It is easily distinguished from other breeds by its long, egg-shaped head.

Name: Caitlyn (Arcane)
Summary: Caitlyn Kiramman is a scion of the Kiramman Clan, one of the ruling houses of Piltover. Eager to see the world for herself and disdainful of the traditional elitist lifestyle that her parents had raised her in, Caitlyn joined the Enforcers as a young woman to make a name for herself. When Marcus, the Sheriff of the Enforcers, and her parents-for very different reasons-started blocking her efforts to further investigate an undercity conspiracy, Caitlyn set off on her own to find answers, only to get much more than she bargained for.

Name: Caitlyn (League of Legends)
Summary: Tier: At least 10-B, 7-B with Weapons | At least 10-B, High 6-C with Weapons | At least 10-B, 4-B with Weapons | At least 10-B, At least 7-B with Weapons, Low 2-C via Hax

Name: Cane Corso
Summary: The Cane Corso is an Italian breed of mastiff. It is used for personal protection, tracking, law enforcement, as a guard dog, and as a companion dog.

Name: Capybara
Summary: The capybara (Hydrochoerus hydrochaeris) is a giant rodent native from South America. Capybaras are the largest living rodent and a member of the genus Hydrochoerus. They are close relatives include guinea pigs and rock cavies. Capybaras inhabits savannas and dense forests and lives near bodies of water. The capybaras are hunted for its meat and hide and also for grease from its thick fatty skin.

Name: Cassandra Nova (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Cassandra Nova Xavier is what the Shi'ar call "Mummudrai", the spirit that is the equal and opposite of a person. However, due to the amazing genetic potential of Professor Charles Xavier, his Mummudrai was able to create a physical form, effectively a twin. While gestating in her mother Sharon Xavier's, womb, Cassandra was recognized by Charles as an evil presence, and he preemptively tried to kill her with his nascent psychic abilities. Cassandra was barely able to defend herself and the shock of the roiling battle caused Sharon to have a miscarriage. Though the doctors pronounced her stillborn, Cassandra in fact survived and spent the next decades as a growing mass of cells in a sewer wall, building a new body for herself and planning her revenge on her brother, and has been a recurring threat towards the X-Men ever since.

Name: Cheetah
Summary: The cheetah is a feline and a member of the "big cat family". They hunt by ambush and running full speed towards the prey, then sinking their teeth into their throat until the prey suffocates. The cheetah has a weight of 77 to 143 pounds and is the fastest land animal in real life.

Name: Chimpanzee
Summary: The Chimpanzee is a primate and is the closest relative to humans (According to studies, their DNA is extremely similar to that of humans). They mainly eat fruit, vegetables and sometimes meat.

Name: Cioccolata
Summary: Cioccolata is a minor antagonist in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part V: Vento Aureo. A former doctor who was fired for "accidentally" killing a patient during surgery, he joins Passione alongside his "pet", Secco, as one of the Boss' Guard Squad members. Due to his malevolent nature, he is rarely called upon, but the Boss had no other choice but to call him to fight Bruno Bucciarati and his gang in Rome.

Name: Clouded Leopard
Summary: The clouded leopard (Neofelis nebulosa) is a wild cat inhabiting dense forests from the foothills of the Himalayas through mainland Southeast Asia into South China. Its head-and-body length ranges from 68.6 to 108 cm (27.0 to 42.5 in) with a 61 to 91 cm (24 to 36 in) long tail. It uses its tail for balancing when moving in trees and is able to climb down vertical tree trunks head first. It rests in trees during the day and hunts by night on the forest floor. They have two subspecies: the Mainland clouded leopard & Sunda clouded leopard, with the later being the largest.[1][2]

Name: Common Turkey
Summary: The common turkey (Meleagris gallopavo) is a wild game turkey in North America and a domesticated bird eaten in other countries, especially on holidays like Thankgiving and Christmas.[1]

Name: Constructed Commoner
Summary: Made by the Harpers at Twilight, Constructed Commoners are the residents of the Wisteria Vale demiplane. They are wood mannequins brought to life by magic which are able to act as if they're real humans. They feel no pain, are shielded from detection magic, and never get tired.

Name: Coyote
Summary: The coyote (Canis latrans) is a carnivorous animal that is native to North America. It is closely related to the Gray Wolf and is much smaller than the more famous canine. It mainly eats meat, though it may also eat fruits and vegetables occasionally. The coyote has 19 recognized subspecies, with one of the most common being the Western Coyote, and the largest subspecies being the Eastern Coyote, which is the result of various historical and recent matings with various types of wolves.

Name: Darren Cross (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Doctor Darren Cross was the protégé of Hank Pym, who usurped his mentor as CEO of Pym Technologies and rebranded it as Cross Technologies. Cross became obssessed with the Pym Particles and using Pym's technologies to achieve success, but the constant exposure to the particles negatively affected his mind. Cross had developed the Yellowjacket Suit and intended to sell it to HYDRA and the Ten Rings, but Pym and Hope Van Dyne joined forces with Ant-Man, who destroyed his entire research. Driven mad after losing everything he built, Cross wore the suit himself and became Yellowjacket, to get revenge by killing Ant-Man and his family. As Yellowjacket threatened Cassie Lang, he was confronted by Ant-Man, who neutralized him by shrinking him down to a sub-atomic level and destroying his suit.

Name: Destiny (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Irene Adler hailed from a prosperous Austrian family, born near the close of the 19th century. Raised in Salzburg, Austria, her mutant gift of precognition emerged at the tender age of 13. Without guidance in harnessing her newfound powers, she faced a deluge of disconcerting, alien sights and sounds. Struggling to preserve her mental faculties, Adler embarked on a journey to record her visions in diaries. a lifeline amidst the chaos. A few years later, Irene hired Raven Darkhölme, a consulting detective, to help her make sense of her diaries. They tried to use Irene's visions to change the future and fell in love in the process. But even though they could make money using Irene's abilities, they couldn't make big changes in society, which left them both frustrated.

Name: Diamondback (Willis Stryker)
Summary: Willis Stryker was born and raised in Harlem, New York. He grew up on the streets alongside Carl Lucas, his best friend and future partner, and founded the Rivals gang together, where he took on the name of Diamondback. Stryker eventually became convinced however, that Lucas had seduced his girlfriend Reva, and in a fit of jealousy, got his ex-girlfriend murdered and his friend jailed.

Name: Dobermann
Summary: The Dobermann is a German breed of medium-large working dog of pinscher type. It was originally bred in Thuringia in about 1890 by Louis Dobermann, a tax collector. It has a long muzzle and – ideally – an even and graceful gait. The ears were traditionally cropped and the tail docked, practices which are now illegal in many countries.

Name: Doctor Poison (Golden Age)
Summary: The first Doctor Poison was Maru, a Japanese princess, member of the war-time Villainy, Inc. and opponent of Wonder Woman. She used chemicals as weapons, and initially disguised herself as a male using a disturbing mask.

Name: Dogo Argentino
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Domestic Sheep
Summary: Since descending from the Asiatic Mouflon (Ovis Orentalis) and Bezoar Ibex (Capra aegagrus) in the middle east 10,500 years before present (YBP),[1][2] the raising of domestic sheep is responsible for much of the world's lamb supply, mutton supply,[1][3] wool,[1] sheep milk,[4][3] wool,[1][3] and cheese.[1][3][5] In 2011, there were more than 1 billion sheep in the world.[4] Their presence as the most common livestock affected the cultures that raised them.[6][7][8] Even domesticated, sheep preferably moves in flocks for protection.[9][10]

Name: Dr. Cassee Dannell
Summary: A young prodigy, Dr. Cassee Dannell was a facility member and field scientist at Varkenbluff. She secretly studied the occult as well, which lead her to the terrifying realization that one of the recent finds of her team is an eldritch horror's egg. Attempting to get the egg before it hatched she tried sneaking to the museum housing it, leading to her getting caught and fried from her job. Thus she hires a group of adventurers in order to finish off the soon to hatch egg, offering her Bag of Holding alongside gold to those who succeed.

Name: Egghead (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Dr. Elihas Starr was a scientist working at an US atomic research center. He was caught when trying to smuggle drafts of an atomic project, and then subsequently fired from the center, waiting to be judged for treason. However, the criminal world discovered his ordeal and offered him freedom if he was ready to put his intellect to the service of the crime lords. Taking on the name Egghead, Starr became a criminal mastermind, and arch enemy to Ant-Man.

Name: Ekko
Summary: Tier: At least 10-B, 9-C with Piltover Clock Hand, Low 2-C Environmental Damage Via Chronobreak | At least 10-B, likely higher, 9-C with QWQRE83 Chrono Blade, Low 2-C Environmental Damage Via Chronobreak

Name: Electric Eel
Summary: The electric eel (Electrophorus electricus), or poraque, is a South American electric fish plus the only member of its genus. Despite the name, the electric eel is a knifefish, not an eel. Its electric charge has been applied to eels that are nowhere near

Name: Eli Morrow (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Elias "Eli" Morrow was the maternal uncle of Robbie and Gabe Reyes and a former employee at Momentum Labs. Witnessing the experiments being done by his coworkers, Morrow began to crave the power for himself, and betrayed his colleagues, turning them into ghost-like entities before attacking Joseph Bauer in order to find the Darkhold, but Bauer fell into a coma before revealing its location, and Morrow was imprisoned at South Ridge Penitentiary. He was later kidnapped by Bauer's wife, Lucy in order to force Morrow to use the Darkhold and reverse the process. However, Morrow tricked her and managed to fulfill his original plan, entering the machine and obtaining the power of creating matter at his own will. In the final battle against the S.H.I.E.L.D., Morrow was killed by Ghost Rider, who revealed himself to be Robbie Reyes.

Name: Emperor Penguin
Summary: The emperor penguin (Aptenodytes forsteri) is the largest and heaviest living penguin in the world. It is native to Antarctica, and feeds primarily on fish, squid, and antarctic krill. Emperor penguin colonies can number in the hundreds to thousands and have an elaborate courtship and breeding process.

Name: Endoceras
Summary: Endoceras (name meaning "inner horn") is a genus of large endoceratid nautiloids, which are known for their long, straight shells. With an estimated full length of nearly 6 meters, they are considered the longest cephalopods in the fossil record.[1][2] Like others of its kind, Endoceras likely occupied the apex predator niche in the oceans during the Ordovician, hunting animals near the seafloor.

Name: Fennec Fox
Summary: The Fennec Fox is the smallest member of the canid family. Living in the deserts of North Africa, it survives by eating invertebrates and small animals. Its unique appearance and big ears have made it famous to the outside world.

Name: Francine Langstrom (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Francine Langstrom is the wife of Kirk Langstrom, Man-Bat. While she is currently living a normal life, she used to be as addicted to the Man-Bat serum as him, threatening Gotham's inhabitants as a monstrous, giant vampire bat.

Name: Genista
Summary: Genista is the Franxx piloted by Code:556 (Kokoro) and originally Code:214 (Futoshi), but due to the partner swapping, Futoshi was replaced with Code:326 (Mitsuru). The Franxx is owned by Squad 13, and it is named after a genus of bushes.

Name: German Shepherd
Summary: The German Shepherd is a medium to large-sized German Breed of herding dog that was later used for police and military work. It is also commonly kept as a companion.

Name: Giant Anteater
Summary: The giant anteater is the largest of the four extant species of anteater. Unlike other anteaters and sloths, the giant anteater is a mostly terrestrial animal. The giant anteater is recognizable for its long snout, bushy tail, long foreclaws, and distinctive fur markings. The giant anteater's bold marking serves as warning coloration. The giant anteater has been featured in pre-Colombian myths and folklore and popular culture.

Name: Goat
Summary: Domesticated goats (Capra aegagrus hircus) are a subspecies of goat bred from the vulnerable Wild Goat. Goats vary greatly in weight based on breed, ranging from 20-27 kg for small goat does to over 140 kg for larger bucks such as Boer goats.

Name: Graviton (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Dr. Franklin Hall was a scientist working at a private physics research facility called Research City in the Canadian Rockies on a practical teleportation device. In the midst of an experiment, Hall attempted to align a set of matrices and induce teleportation, but only succeeded in overloading the power handling capacity of his equipment, causing an explosion that intermingled his molecules with the sub-nuclear graviton particles that were being generated in a nearby series of companion particle accelerators. Recovering from the accident, Hall discovered that he could mentally control gravity. At first he tried to hide his vast powers, believing he would be shunned as a freak of nature, but the urge to use them was too great to resist, and soon Hall used his abilities openly. To his pleasure, people began to fear him, and he started to take whatever and whomever he desired.

Name: Gray Wolf
Summary: The Gray wolf is an infamous carnivorous animal found all in the Americas and Eurasia. It is known to humans more than almost any other predatory animal, with more importance to human culture than most others. Although the fear of wolves is common in humans, wolf attacks are very rare.

Name: Haast's Eagle
Summary: The Haast's eagle was the largest eagle to have ever existed. It existed until a few hundred years ago when its primary prey source was hunted to death by humans.

Name: Hallows' Eve (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Elizabeth Tyne went through a lot of hardship, an abusive father, kidnapped and prison, but she found love with Benjamin Reilly a clone of Spider-Man. She went through a lot of effort to help him become who he should be, including going to the dimension called Limbo. Tired of feeling useless she accepted a power that was given by Madelyne Pryor, now going by the name Hallows' Eve she tries to do everything she can to keep the relationship with Ben alive.

Name: Harpy Eagle
Summary: The Harpy Eagle is among the largest of the extant eagles in the wild. It resides in canopies ranging from southern Mexico all the way into Brazil, Bolivia, and Paraguay. Destruction of its natural habitat caused it to vanish from many parts of its former range and nearly extirpated it from many parts of Central America.

Name: Heatwave (DC Comics)
Summary: Mick Rory or better known as Heatwave is one of the Flash's Rogues and is utterly obsessed with fire to such as extent that in his youth he let his parents burn to death.

Name: Heimerdinger
Summary: A brilliant yet eccentric yordle scientist, Professor Cecil B. Heimerdinger is lauded as one of the most innovative minds and esteemed inventors Piltover has ever seen. Relentless in his work to the point of neurotic obsession, he is fascinated by mysteries that have confounded his contemporaries for decades, and thrives on answering the universe’s most impenetrable questions. Though his theories often appear opaque and esoteric, Heimerdinger believes knowledge should be shared, and is devoted to teaching all who desire it.

Name: Hesperornis
Summary: Hesperornis is a genus of bird adapted to an aquatic lifestyle, the name of which means "western bird." It lived around 83.6–72 million years ago, during the late Cretaceous. Most of the identified species have been found in North America, notably in what was once covered by the Western Interior Seaway such as Kansas and Canada, while one species has been discovered near Russia. While mostly suited to a marine environment, many later species also inhabited freshwater environments. It is thought to have had lobed toes similar to loons and grebes, but may have also had webbed toes. It is thought its anatomical structure meant it would belly-slide similar to seals,[1] but may also have been able to stand upright similar to cormorants.[2]

Name: Hinome Hawakata
Summary: Hinome is the secondary main protagonist of the Im: Great Priest Imhotep series. She's Imhotep's first friend after being set free from his punishment for 3,000 years. She's a rather unorthodox high school girl who had a dark past involving the Magai which ties into Imhotep's origins. However, she has a brave, kind, and fierce heart. Helping Imhotep in his endeavors despite being a mere human. Always being willing to stick by his side and cheering him on, making him better himself.

Name: Homo Erectus
Summary: Homo Erectus was an early species of human. It lived around the early Pleistocene and it seemed to be a migrant species. This hominid was remarkable in the fact that their species survived until just 50,000 years ago. This early hominid showed the ability of using fire (As torches, harden clay and cooking).

Name: Homo Habilis
Summary: Homo Habilis was a hominid presumed to be an intermediate animal crossing between the genus Australopithecus and Homo. It was given its name because it was believed to be the first homonid to use stone tools, having made basic carving implements used for removing meat from animals; however, it was discovered that Australopithecus were capable of using stone tools.

Name: Humboldt Squid
Summary: The Humboldt Squid (Dosidicus gigas) is a popularly fished species of squid in the waters of the eastern pacific.[1] It's the largest member of the flying squid family and abundant due to overfishing.[1][2] Despite being a well-studied animal, the IUCN has classified the conservation status of the squid as data deficient.[1]

Name: Humbug (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Disgruntled entomology professor Buck Mitty turned to a life of crime after quitting his job over budget cuts, using different tools and gadgets to his assistance, which put him frequently at odds with Spider-Man.

Name: Husky
Summary: The Siberian Husky is a breed of dog from, unsurprisingly, Siberia, bred for both working for humans and acting as a companion to them.

Name: Ijin Yu
Summary: Ijin Yu is the main protagonist of the Mercenary Enrollment manhwa. When Ijin was nine, he and his parents were involved in a plane crash. Although Ijin survived, he was orphaned and was stranded from his remaining family. Eventually he was taken in by an group called The Numbers. Ijin underwent harsh training, and he worked as a mercenary for about eight years, serving in the harshest battlefields across the world. Later, during a rescue mission, he saved a RoK major named Kang Hamchan, his team and a doctor. Kang Hamchan traced Ijin's family and helped him retire. Ijin underwent a six-month orientation from Major Kang to help him adjust to civilian life. He's currently living with his grandfather and his sister in Seoul. Aside from attending Shinan high school, Ijin works as a part-time bodyguard at the SW group's security team, along with classmate Koh Sukjoo.

Name: Ironheart (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Riri Williams is an MIT student, and one of the smartest people on earth. She was hired by the CIA to find vibranium, but later got taken by the Wakandans to find the Tolokanil base. She has created a suit of armor for herself, granting her the name Ironheart.

Name: Jack Russell (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Jack Russell is a werewolf dubbed Werewolf by Night. Afflicted with a curse that causes him to transform during a full moon, Russell strove to help other monsters in need and hunt monsters that were a danger to others. In order to assist his friend, Ted Sallis, Russell attended a gathering of monster hunters competing for the Bloodstone. Russell worked with Elsa Bloodstone to free Sallis, but in doing so exposed himself as a monster. Verussa Bloodstone captured him and forced him to transform, inadvertently unleashing the werewolf by night on her own forces. Russell spared Elsa and fled, reuniting with Sallis.

Name: Jinx (Arcane)
Summary: Jinx, born as Powder, is a notorious Zaunite criminal and Vi's younger sister. When she was a little girl, her parents were killed in a failed uprising against Piltover, leading Vander, the upspoken leader of the undercity, to adopt both her and Vi as his own daughters. After a series of events forced Jinx and her sister apart in more ways than one, she was fundamentally and irrevocably changed, transforming her into the crazed killer she is today.

Name: Joe Kido (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Joe Kido and Gomamon are main characters from Digimon Adventure 2020. Joe is one of the 8 chosen children of the Digimon Adventure 2020 continuity and is the crest bearer of of Sincerity. Despite his pessimistic attitude and appearing as a coward, Joe is actually quite kind and very brave.

Name: John Constantine (Classic)
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Kilgrave (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Kilgrave is the main villain of the Netflix series Jessica Jones. Real name being Kevin Thompson, he was a man who was experimented on by his parents since his childhood in order to treat a neurodegenerative disease, but the treatment ended up giving him the ability to control people's minds. Assuming the name Kilgrave, he began to use his powers for personal gain, eventually coming across Jessica Jones. He became obsessed and fascinated with Jones, even falling in love and hunting her down since she managed to overcome his thrall.

Name: Koushiro Izumi (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Koushiro Izumi and Tentomon are two of the main protagonists from Digimon Adventure 2020. Koushiro is the brains of the Chosen Children, constantly analyzing the world around him. However, his social skills are lacking due to his preference for computers over people.

Name: Labrador Retriever
Summary: The Labrador Retriever is according to the American Kernel Club, the most popular dog breed until the English Bulldog replaced it's top spot in 2022.[2][3] They have a friendly temperament and are regarded to be loyal, athletic and muscular gundog retrievers in adulthood.[2]

Name: Lynx (Real World)
Summary: A lynx is any of the four existing species (the Canada lynx, Iberian lynx, Eurasian lynx, or bobcat) within the medium-sized wild cat genus Lynx. The lynx is usually solitary, although a small group of lynx may travel and hunt together occasionally. Mating takes place in the late winter and once a year the female gives birth to between one and four kittens.

Name: Lystrosaurus
Summary: Lystrosaurus is an extinct genus of therapsid, a group of ancient reptiles that includes some of the closest relatives to mammals. Lystrosaurus lived during the Permian and early Triassic periods, approximately 255 to 250 million years ago. It was a herbivorous animal with a beak-like snout and a robust body. Lystrosaurus is notable for its resilience and ability to survive the Permian-Triassic mass extinction event, which wiped out many other species. Its fossils have been found on various continents, and it is often considered an example of a "disaster taxon" that rebounded after a major extinction event, helping to repopulate the Earth with life.

Name: Machinesmith (Marvel Comics)
Summary: At the age of fourteen, Samuel Saxon discovered one of Doctor Doom's robots abandoned in a subway tunnel, and took it piece by piece to his father's garage, where for months he studied its components until mastering its operating principles and building his own robot from scratch. His obsession with robots grew as he amassed an army of droids at his service, that he used for his crimes, only to entangle with Daredevil, outsmarting him vastly in their first encounter.

Name: Mad Mod
Summary: Neil Richards, otherwise known by his alias Mad Mod, is a reoccurring enemy of the Teen Titans. A criminal mastermind, capable of creating powerful illusions through his technology. He seems to be obsessed with 1960's and 70's British culture.

Name: Mandrill
Summary: The Mandrill (Mandrillus sphinx) is a primate and the world's largest monkeys. Mandrills mostly live in tropical rainforest and in very large groups and have an omnivorous diet consisting mostly of fruits and insects.

Name: Mechanica
Summary: Mechanica is a playable fighter in ARMS. She was born without extendable ARMS, so she uses a powered suit to compete in the ARMS Grand Prix.

Name: Megalopraptus
Summary: Megalograptus is a genus of eurypterid, an extinct group of aquatic arthropods. Fossils of Megalograptus have been recovered in deposits of Katian (Late Ordovician) age in North America.

Name: Millwall Brick
Summary: The Millwall brick (named after the football team) is an improvisational blunt stealth weapon made with several pages of paper, often from a newspaper, tightly rolled length-wise, and then folded in half to make a club.

Name: Mimi Tachikawa (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Mimi Tachikawa and her partner Palmon are members of the DigiDestined and thus major characters in Digimon Adventure 2020. Mimi is the Crest Bearer of Purity.

Name: Molecule Man
Summary: Owen Reece was a weak, shy boy in Brooklyn, New York who obsessively clung to his mother.[1] He grew into a weak-willed adult, made bitter and lonely by his mother's death, and full of fear and hatred of what he regarded as a deeply unfriendly world. Reece became a lowly laboratory technician working at a nuclear plant owned by the Acme Atomics Corporation. He was disgruntled by his job's long hours and low pay. One day, Reece accidentally activated an experimental particle generator, which bombarded him with an unknown form of radiation. The explosion horribly disfigured his face with scars in the shape of lightning bolts, but it also had a mutagenic effect on Reece, releasing his potential for psionic powers on a cosmic scale. Reece could now control all matter, even down to the molecular level, and all energy, and he now used his immense powers to take out his pent-up frustrations on the world under the moniker of Molecule Man.

Name: Mongrel Dog
Summary: The mongrel dog is called the pedigree dog, whose ancestry is generally unknown, which has characteristics of two or more types of breeds, or is descended from populations of wild or street dogs.

Name: Montana (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Jackson Brice was born in Bozeman, Montana. Along with Fancy Dan and the original Ox, he was a founding member of the Enforcers. He has great proficiency with the lariat. As a member of the Enforcers, he first came into conflict with Spider-Man when they were employed by the Big Man and have been fighting the wall-crawler ever since.

Name: Mother Night (MAX)
Summary: Suzie Fisher was a former showgirl with the power to hypnotize people using a magic stone. Wanting to kill her philandering husband Max and get the money he earned gambling, she worked with Sean, a boxing manager, to set up Logan aka "L'il Rick", an amateur fighter Sean was promoting, to kill Max and his mistress. After a bout, Suzie seduced Logan and used her hypnotic power to force Logan to kill Max and his mistress. Logan eventually realized what happened and killed Suzie and Sean in revenge.

Name: Ms. Marvel (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Kamran: Look at everything I've done, Kamala. What am I supposed to do now? How can I be normal? Ms. Marvel: There is no normal. There's just us and what we do with what we've been given.

Name: Mute Swan
Summary: The mute swan is the second largest waterfowl after the Trumpeter Swan, although the mute swan can be heavier. The mute swan is native to much of Eurosiberia and rarely in the far north of Africa. Populations of these birds have been introduced to North America and Australia.

Name: Mysterio (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Quentin Beck is a former Stark Industries employee who sought out to replace the late Tony Stark as Earth's next defender. Seeking to solidify a reputation for himself, Beck feigned several Elemental attacks across the world with the use of his drones, seeking attention and recognition from the public as a new superhero/supervillain named Mysterio.

Name: Naegleria Fowleri
Summary: Naegleria fowleri, also known as the Brain-Eating Amoeba, is a protozoan that causes a fulminant (sudden and severe) and fatal brain infection known as Naegleriasis.

Name: Neanderthal
Summary: The Neanderthals were an early species (or sub-species) of humans that lived during the Middle and Low Pleistocene in Europe and West-Asia until as recently as ~40,000 years ago.

Name: Ned Leeds (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Ned Leeds is the best friend of Peter Parker who, upon finding out his true identity as Spider-Man, decides to aid Peter in his crimefighting as his self-stylized "Guy in the Chair".

Name: Negative Man
Summary: The Negative Man (real name Larry Trainor) was an Air Force test pilot fused to an alien negative spirit and made radioactive, forcing him to wear lead-lined bandages, and influencing him to join the Doom Patrol. Chipper and optimistic, but easily frustrated, Larry's physical and emotional evolution was eased along by his teammates and friends over the years.

Name: Nokia Shiramine
Summary: Nokia "Akkino" Shiramine is a main protagonist in Digimon Story: Cyber Sleuth. She is one of Aiba and Arata's best friends. While she initially comes off as selfish, air-headed and even egotistical, she quickly proves herself to be a great tamer and effective leader who is genuinely passionate about the safety of Digimon and their rights.

Name: Noob Variants
Summary: Noob variants (Sometimes also called nooblet variants) are different variants of nooblet that the player runs into early in block tales. They tend to vary from ninjas like sharp nooblet to knights to even winged and cultist noobs. All nooblets, however, are characterized by resembling the Roblox noob in some way. These variants usually team up together against other enemies either with other variants or with the same type of variant; however, it is also possible for them to be alone.

Name: Olive Baboon
Summary: The Olive Baboon is a large omnivorous monkey found in Africa. It is considered a pest in many countries and hated for raiding houses and stealing food.

Name: Orangutan
Summary: The Orangutan is the only Great Ape besides humans native to Asia and the second largest. They are the third closest related animal to humans apart from Gorilla and Chimpanzee respectively.

Name: Otter (Real World)
Summary: Otters are carnivorous mammals in the subfamily Lutrinae. The 13 extant otter species are all semiaquatic, aquatic or marine, with diets based on fish and invertebrates. Lutrinae is a branch of the Mustelidae family, which also includes weasels, badgers, honey badgers, martens, minks, polecats, and wolverines.

Name: Patriofelis
Summary: Patriofelis ("Father of cats") is a genus of large carnivorous placental mammal that lived in North America during the Early to Middle Eocene epoch, about 50.3–46.2 million years ago. Despite its superficial resemblance to big cats, it is not a feline, nor is it a carnivoran either; instead, it was an oxyaenid, a group of carnivorous mammals that were apex predators during the Eocene. Unlike carnivorans, it had stiffened vertebrae similar to armadillos or pangolins, thought to be a tradeoff of flexibility for larger size.[1] In life, they would have been terrestrial apex predators adapted for hunting on the forest floor.[2]

Name: Polaris (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Lorna Dane is the illegitimate daughter of the mutant terrorist Magneto, possessing power to manipulate magnetic fields similar to him. Having fought for peaceful coexistence for most of her life, she has been a seasoned member of the X-Men along with her longtime lover Havok, under the codename Polaris, although her impressive abilities lead her to being mind controlled many times to battle her teammates and loved ones.

Name: Pteranodon
Summary: The pteranodon is a flying reptile that lived in the Cretaceous. They have a wingspan of 18 feet, some specimens have wingspans of 7 meters.

Name: Pulmonoscorpius
Summary: Pulmonoscorpius is a genus of large scorpion that lived in Scotland 336–326.4 million years ago, during the Mississippian subperiod in the early Carboniferous. Its name comes from the Latin word pulmonis, which means "lung," and the Greek word skorpios, which means "scorpion;"[1] a fitting name considering it possessed book lungs on its underside similar to modern scorpions, which indicated it was terrestrial. As it was not adapted to burrowing like later scorpions, it was likely a diurnal hunter with an active lifestyle.

Name: Purple Man
Summary: Yugoslav spy Zebediah Killgrave was on a mission to infiltrate an American military chemical refinery to steal an experimental new nerve gas when he was spotted by a guard who shot at him, but missed and hit a canister of the gas instead. The fumes sprayed all over Killgrave, turning his skin purple, and when he easily convinces the guards to let him go, he realizes he also gained the power to secrete pheromones that drain the will of his target until they follow his every command. Zebediah started using his powers to commit nefarious acts, working as a supervillain with the title of the Purple Man.

Name: Raccoon
Summary: Raccoons are the largest member of the procyonid family, having a body length of 40 to 70 cm. Raccoons vary considerably in weight, ranging from 5 to 26 kg, although they typically weigh 5 to 12 kg. Raccoons are a notorious pest species due to the spread of rabies.

Name: Riddle School
Summary: Riddle School is a series of flash based puzzle-solving games created by Jonochrome. The games revolves around an elementary school student, Phil Eggtree, trying to escape his school. The player must overcome several obstacles and use super clever thinking in order to help Phil achieve his goal.

Name: Scolar Visari
Summary: Scolar Visari was the founder of the Helghan Empire, the Autarch of Helghan, and the main antagonist of the Killzone series. He was vicious and violent, uniting the Helghan Nation through his charismatic and compelling leadership to become a major power on the interstellar stage.

Name: Sora Takenouchi (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Sora Takenouchi and Piyomon are main characters from Digimon Adventure 2020. Sora bears the crest of love, Piyomon is her partner Digimon. She is a "Chick" type Digimon who specializes in fire based attacks.

Name: Striped Hyena
Summary: The striped hyena (Hyaena hyaena) is a species of hyena native to North and East Africa, the Middle East, the Caucasus, Central Asia and the Indian subcontinent. It is the only extant species in the genus Hyaena.

Name: Sunless
Summary: Sunless (or Sunny), is the main character of Shadow Slave. Growing up in the outskirts and leading a life of deceit and focusing on his own survival, he initially has a bleak outlook on life, even resigning himself to his fate when he was infected by the Nightmare Spell. But then, inside his First Nightmare, he resolved to himself that he must survive, no matter what.

Name: Taiki Kudo and Shoutmon (Manga)
Key: '''Shoutmon''' | '''Shoutmon X2''' | '''Shoutmon X3''' | '''Shoutmon X4''' | '''Shoutmon X5''' | '''OmegaShoutmon''' | '''Shoutmon DX''' | '''Shoutmon X6''' | '''Shoutmon X7''' | '''Shoutmon EX6''' | '''Shoutmon X7 Superior Mode'''
Summary: To make the whole world happy!!! That's the King that I am for!!!

Name: The Lizard (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Dr. Curtis Connors was a military surgeon turned herpetologist who lost his right arm during the war and sought to restore it by performing genetic research on the regenerative capabilities of reptiles. The serum that should have been the cure has instead turned him into the Lizard, a crazed but cunning monster who plans to return the planet to reptiles, which he believes being their righftul owners. Spider-Man always managed to foil his plans and reverse him back to a human, but every attempt at erasing the Lizard forever proved uneffective, and it remained a looming threat which could manifest anytime.

Name: The Protagonist (Digimon World: DS)
Summary: The Protagonist of Digimon World: DS is a young boy who stumbled upon the Digital World while investigating rumors he heard about "Digital Monsters". Later found by ClavisAngemon after observing the Digimon instruct a group of aspiring Tamers, the boy was allowed to become a full-fledged Tamer himself, proving to be exceptionally capable. After Unknown D began brainwashing his fellow Tamers to turn them against each other, the protagonist took it upon himself to stop Unknown D and later save the entire Digital World.

Name: Toxie Doxie (Marvel Comics)
Summary: You get to understand there are haves and have-nots in this world, you know? And that the have-nots don't really have the same right to life as the people who worked hard to be selected for greatness. And when the have-nots accidentally enter a position of power, where they can prevent Darwinian victors from exercising their talents... That's just wrong.

Name: Ulysses Klaue (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Ulysses Klaue was a black-market arms dealer and smuggler as well as a gangster who had operated out of South Africa. He was a former acquaintance of Tony Stark from his weapons-dealing days, and was an associate of N'Jobu when he attempted to expose Wakanda to the rest of the world. In 2015, during an encounter with Ultron, Klaue sold his entire stockpile of the Vibranium to the A.I. before losing his arm in an argument with Ultron, and fled when the Avengers arrived.

Name: Velociraptor (Real World)
Summary: Velociraptor is a genus of small theropods living in the Cretaceous Period. They are one of the most popular species of Dinosaurs, even though their appearance is vastly misunderstood.

Name: Vermin (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Edward Whelan was once a young scientist working under Baron Zemo.
