It was among the earliest diapsids, the group of which including all modern reptiles, along with dinosaurs, pterosaurs, and marine reptiles such as plesiosaurs and ichthyosaurs. The first fossil was found in Garnett, Kansas, and inhabited conifer-fern forests around 302 million years ago, during the late Carboniferous period.[1]

Name: Pigeon
Summary: The pigeon is a part of the family Columbidae, being an omnivorus, bulky bird widespread in all places except Antarctica and the Sahara desert.[1] They typically nest at buildings or rocky cliffs and can be found in urban areas, farmlands, and the aforementioned rocky cliffs.[1] There are an estimated 400 million pigeons across the world and 250 species of pigeons.[1] Doves are smaller pigeons in layman's terms and they're scientifically similar as pigeons.[1]

Name: Pikaia
Summary: Pikaia is a genus of small invertebrate chordate, similar to modern lancelets. In the past it has been treated as the direct ancestor of vertebrates[1] or even the first fish,[2] but rather it was likely a stem chordate closely related to the line of chordates that would give rise to vertebrates.[3] It had a notochord and a body composed of segmets of muscle referred to as "myomeres," which is considered the major characteristics of chordates.[4] Its fossils have been found in the Burgess Shale in British Columbia, and it would have lived 513–505 million years ago, during the middle Cambrian.

Name: Pistol Shrimp
Summary: The pistol shrimp is a family of shrimps known for the effect of their snapping.

Name: Planarian
Summary: A Planarian is one of many flatworms of the class Turbellaria. It usually describes free-living flatworms of the order Tricladida, although this common name is also used for a wide number of free-living platyhelminthes. Planaria are common to many parts of the world, living in both saltwater and freshwater ponds and rivers. Some species are terrestrial and are found under logs, in or on the soil, and on plants in humid areas.

Name: Platypus
Summary: Platypuses are members of the echidna family known for possessing a tail resembling a beavers, a bill resembling a duck's, and webbed-feet resembling an otter's. When scientists first discovered them, they were believed to be a combination of multiple animals stitched together.

Name: Porcupine
Summary: Porcupines are large rodents coated with sharp, pointed quills. Unlike the quills of a hedgehog, porpupine quills have microscopic barbs that make them difficult to remove. Their quills serve as a very effective defense against predators of varying sizes.

Name: Poro
Summary: Poros are the mysterious, magical and most-loved inhabitants originating from the Howling Abyss.

Name: Portuguese Man O' War
Summary: The Portuguese Man O' War is a marine hydrozoan found throughout the Earth's oceans. Unlike jellyfish, the Portuguese Man O' War is a colonial organism rather than a single organism; the Man O' War is composed of many polyps that work together in a symbiotic relationship.

Name: Praying Mantis
Summary: Mantises are an order of insects that contains over 2,400 species in about 430 genera in 30 families. The largest family is the Mantidae. Mantises are distributed worldwide in temperate and tropical habitats. They have triangular heads with bulging eyes supported on flexible necks. Their elongated bodies may or may not have wings, but all Mantodea have forelegs that are greatly enlarged and adapted for catching and gripping prey; their upright posture, while remaining stationary with forearms folded, has led to the common name praying mantis.

Name: Prokaryotic Cell
Summary: A Prokaryotic Cell is a small, single-celled organism, measuring anywhere from 0.1–5.0 µm in diameter. They are one of the simplest lifeforms on Earth, and can reproduce asexually through a process similar to mitosis. Unlike other cells, they lack a nucleus, but store the entirety of their DNA in an irregularly-shaped region known as the nucleoid. They can also move around by wiggling their flagellum.

Name: Pug
Summary: The pug is a breed of dog which was originally bred in China for companionship. It is a friendly dog, and is great for families and children.

Name: Pulmonoscorpius
Summary: Pulmonoscorpius is a genus of large scorpion that lived in Scotland 336–326.4 million years ago, during the Mississippian subperiod in the early Carboniferous. Its name comes from the Latin word pulmonis, which means "lung," and the Greek word skorpios, which means "scorpion;"[1] a fitting name considering it possessed book lungs on its underside similar to modern scorpions, which indicated it was terrestrial. As it was not adapted to burrowing like later scorpions, it was likely a diurnal hunter with an active lifestyle.

Name: Purple (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: One of the many residents of the city of Harmony, Purple is an acolyte wizard that worships the God of Knowledge Oghma. They are one of several adventurers that ultimately solve the city's energy crisis.

Name: Quipper (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A carnivorous fish, the Quipper is able to adapt to any aquatic environment. They often go in swarms which go berserk whenever they draw a victim's blood.

Name: Rabbit (Real World)
Summary: Rabbits are a common prey animal and, in places where they are introduced, one of the most infamous invasive species on Earth. Rabbits are herbivorous, although a source from 1910 has stated that rabbits have eaten snails. Rabbits were raised as pets, livestock animals, and laboratory animals. European rabbits, which are the most common rabbit, weigh from 1.2 to 2 kg.

Name: Raccoon
Summary: Raccoons are the largest member of the procyonid family, having a body length of 40 to 70 cm. Raccoons vary considerably in weight, ranging from 5 to 26 kg, although they typically weigh 5 to 12 kg. Raccoons are a notorious pest species due to the spread of rabies.

Name: Rainbow Trout
Summary: The rainbow trout (Oncorhynchus mykiss), also known as the steelhead, is a large species of freshwater fish native to North America. It is a popular game fish, and the fastest freshwater fish in the world.

Name: Rat (Real World)
Summary: A rat is a small rodent. They are characterized by being larger than mice and having powerful incisors that they use to break apart structures. They are also one of the few animals that has managed to adapt and survive in almost any climate (The only continent that they don't live in is Antarctica).

Name: Red Fox
Summary: Red Fox (Vulpes vulpes), also called common fox, is the largest of the true foxes. Being present across the entire Northern Hemisphere including most of North America, Europe and Asia, plus parts of North Africa. Apart from its large size, the red fox is distinguished from other fox species by its ability to adapt quickly to new environments and has the largest natural distribution of any land mammal except human beings.

Name: Red Panda
Summary: The red panda (Ailurus fulgens), also known as the lesser panda, is a small mammal native to the eastern Himalayas and southwestern China. The red panda's place on the evolutionary tree has been debated, but modern genetic evidence places it in close affinity with raccoons, weasels, and skunks. It is not closely related to the giant panda, which is a bear, though both possess elongated wrist bones or "false thumbs" used for grasping bamboo.

Name: Red Sea Urchin
Summary: The red sea urchin (Mesocentrotus franciscanus) is a species of sea urchin endemic to the northeastern Pacific Ocean.

Name: Red Triangle Slug
Summary: The Red Triangle Slug is a species of slug native to eastern Australia. It can easily be identified by the red triangle marking on its back, but comes in various colorations, including white, off-white, yellow, dark grey, light grey, beige, pink, red, and olive green. Research is ongoing as to whether these variations are actually different subspecies or just natural variation. It is Australia's largest land slug, growing up to 15 centimeters in length.

Name: Red-Bellied Piranha
Summary: The red-bellied piranha (Pygocentrus nattereri) is an infamous fish found in the Amazon River. While docile unless startled, piranhas have built up a reputation with their ability to devour anything that crosses their path, stripping off bits of flesh until their prey is nothing but bone.

Name: Rhamphorhynchus
Summary: Rhamphorhynchus is a genus of small or moderately sized pterosaur, possessing a long tail. Its name comes from the Greek words rhamphos, meaning "beak," and rhynchus. meaning "snout." It lived throughout portions of Europe 150.8–148.5 million years ago, during the Late Jurassic, including Germany, England, Spain, and Tanzania, and remains of teeth thought to belong to it have been found in Portugal.[1] Fossil evidence suggests its diet consisted of fish and cephalopods,[2] may have been capable of swimming like modern aquatic birds.

Name: Riddle School
Summary: Riddle School is a series of flash based puzzle-solving games created by Jonochrome. The games revolves around an elementary school student, Phil Eggtree, trying to escape his school. The player must overcome several obstacles and use super clever thinking in order to help Phil achieve his goal.

Name: Rika Furude
Key: '''Piece Rika''' | '''Higher Layer/World of Gods/Sea of Fragments Rika and Frederica'''
Summary: nan

Name: Ringed Caecilian
Summary: Ringed Caecilians (Siphonops annulatus) are a species in the Siphonopidae family of Caecilians, a group of legless amphibians. This species inhabits South America in areas east of the Andes, and is thought to have the widest range of any terrestrial caecilian species. They live underground, inhabiting a wide range of areas, including grasslands, shrublands, and forests; they have also been found in human-inhabited areas such as gardens and plantations.

Name: Romeo Conbolt
Summary: Romeo Conbolt is the only son of Fairy Tail's Mage, Macao Conbolt, and a Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild.

Name: Satanic Leaf-Tailed Gecko
Summary: The Satanic leaf-tailed gecko (Uroplatus phantasticus) is a small species of gecko endemic to the rainforests of Madagascar. Despite their ominous name, they are generally peaceful animals, and primarily eat small insects, such as moths and crickets. They are currently at risk due to deforestation of their natural habitat, as well as being poached for the pet trade.

Name: Scissors
Summary: Scissors are tools used for cutting objects. They rely on 2 blades with a wedge in the middle, and use at least 2 fingers to get through the handle of itself to use it. Designs and uses vary from cutting thin materials like cloth and paper to cutting through chicken bone. The word shears are used to describe tools of the same kind, but larger.[1]

Name: Sea Gull
Summary: Sea gulls are birds infamous for their presence in beaches and attacks on beachgoers and tourists. The notoriety primarily goes to birds such as the Western Gull (pictured to the right).

Name: Secretary Bird
Summary: Secretary birds are a large, mostly terrestrial bird of prey endemic to Africa. It is usually found in the sub-Saharan grasslands and savannah. The secretary bird is identifiable by its eagle-like body on crane-like legs. Unlike most birds of prey, secretary birds tend to stomp their prey with their long legs, slashing at them with their talons.

Name: Selene (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Born 17,000 years ago, prior to retcons Selene was noted as being the first mutant. She is a special kind of mutant known as an External. Living for many years, Selene has the power of psychic vampirism which she uses to empower herself and give herself a youthful body, effectively making her immortal so long as she feeds.

Name: Serval
Summary: The serval (Leptailurus serval) is a wild cat native to Africa. It is widespread in sub-Saharan countries, except rainforest regions. Across its range, it occurs in protected areas, and hunting it is either prohibited or regulated in range countries.

Name: Seven-Armed Sea Star
Summary: The Seven-Armed Sea Star is a predatory sea star. It is the fastest sea star, moving at a speed of 46 mm/s.

Name: Shiba Inu
Summary: The Shiba Inu is a small, Japanese dog, originally bred for hunting small game. They nearly went extinct during World War 2, but since then, they have become very popular as a pet. Shibas are also the number one companion dog in Japan.

Name: Shrunken Bones (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Jerry Morgan was a scientist who shrank his own skeleton due to an unforeseen side effect of the shrinking gas he invented. He joined a group known as Headmen in their attempts to seek world domination through science, and most often acted as assistant to Arthur Nagan

Name: Silverfish (Real World)
Summary: Silverfish are small, primitive, wingless insects in the order Zygentoma. Its common name derives from the animal's silvery light grey colour, combined with the fish-like appearance of its movements. The scientific name indicates that the silverfish's diet consists of carbohydrates such as sugar or starches.

Name: Simosuchus
Summary: Simosuchus is a genus of notosuchian crocodyliform with the single species S. clarki. It's name means is Greek for "pug nosed crocodile," referring to is blunt snout akin the beloved dog breed. It lived 70–66 million years ago, during the late Cretaceous, in present day Madagascar. Unlike many other crocodylomorphs, its characteristics, such as maple leaf shaped teeth, indicate it was herbivorous.

Name: Snowy Owl
Summary: The snowy owl (Bubo scandiacus) is a large, white owl of the typical owl family. Snowy owls are native to Arctic regions in North America and Eurasia. Most owls sleep during the day and hunt at night, but the snowy owl is active during the day, especially in the summertime.

Name: Space Guppy
Summary: A fish like creature, the Space Guppy roams Wildspace and the Astral Sea. They have a unique ability where they can produce an air bubble around themselves, with it being able to sustain it and another tiny creature. This fact made so various races use it as a mount from time to time.

Name: Spiral Siphonophore
Summary: The spiral siphonophore is the longest animal in the world.

Name: Staghorn Coral
Summary: Staghorn coral (Acropora cervicornis) is a species of hard coral native to reefs across the western Atlantic, from as far north as Palm Beach down to the western coast of South America. It is one of the fastest growing coral species in the world. It is critically endangered due to catastrophic disease outbreaks and coral bleaching.

Name: Star-Nosed Mole
Summary: The star-nosed mole is a mole found in moist, low areas in the northern parts of North America. The star-nosed mole is named for its nose, which has 22 fingerlike appendages that allow it to feel out its environment thanks to sensory organs called "Eimer's organs."

Name: Stentor Coeruleus
Summary: Stentor Coeruleus are peculiar protists, filter-feeding unicellular microorganisms part of the ciliate genus known as Stentor, sometimes referred as trumpet animalcules due to the stretched shape reminding of this object. They are particularly known for the massive size their single cells can grow to, often reaching the size of a rice grain.

Name: Stonefish
Summary: The Stonefish are a group of fish in the genus Synanceia, which includes six species. They get their name from their skin texture and color, which provides them camouflage and gives them a resemblance to a rock. These fish are found throughout the Pacific and Indian Oceans in coral reefs, though some species can also inhabit rivers. They are infamous for their potent neurotoxin, which they can inject into threats through spines on their dorsal fins. These creatures do not use their fins to catch prey, however, instead vacuuming their prey into their mouths.

Name: Sunless
Summary: Sunless (or Sunny), is the main character of Shadow Slave. Growing up in the outskirts and leading a life of deceit and focusing on his own survival, he initially has a bleak outlook on life, even resigning himself to his fate when he was infected by the Nightmare Spell. But then, inside his First Nightmare, he resolved to himself that he must survive, no matter what.

Name: Swarm (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Fritz von Meyer is a former Nazi scientist who escaped the aftermath of World War II by fleeing to Argentina like many of his allies, where he spent his time researching the breeding patterns of local killer bees. In these studies, he discovered a breed of killer bees that knew no fear, were unusually passive, and highly intelligent, and created a device that he hoped would allow him to take control of them.

Name: Synagris Cornuta
Summary: Synagris Cornuta are large potter wasps. Several Synagris wasps are strongly sexually dimorphic and males bear notable morphological secondary sexual traits including metasomal lamellar or angular protruding structures and hornlike or tusklike mandibular and or clypeal projections.

Name: Takeru Takaishi (Adventure 2020)
Key: '''Takeru Takaishi''' | '''Patamon''' | '''Pegasusmon''' | '''Angemon''' | '''HolyAngemon''' / '''Holyangemon Priest Mode''' | '''Goddramon''' | '''Seraphimon and BlackSeraphimon''' | '''DanDevimon Shadow'''
Summary: Takeru and Patamon are main characters from Digimon Adventure 2020. Takeru is the crest bearer of Hope and the younger brother of Yamato Ishida.

Name: Tarantula-Hawk Wasp
Summary: The Tarantula Hawk Wasp is a spider wasp that preys on tarantulas. Tarantula hawks belong to any of the many species in the genera Pepsis and Hemipepsis. They are one of the largest parasitoid wasps, using their sting to paralyze their prey before dragging it to a brood nest as living food; a single egg is laid on the prey, hatching to a larva which eats the still-living prey.

Name: Taser
Summary: A Taser is an incapacitating weapon mainly used by the Police Force and Military forces for non-lethal arrests.

Name: Tasmanian Devil (Real World)
Summary: The Tasmanian Devil is the largest carnivorous marsupial after the extinction of the Thylacine aka Tasmanian tiger. Male Tasmanian Devils have a head and body length of 65.2 cm and weigh in at an average of 8 kg. Currently populations are endangered, with their populations slowly declining.

Name: Termite
Summary: Termites are eusocial insects that are classified at the taxonomic rank of infraorder Isoptera, or as epifamily Termitoidae within the cockroach order Blattodea. Like ants and some bees and wasps from the separate order Hymenoptera, termites divide labour among castes consisting of sterile male and female "workers" and "soldiers". All colonies have fertile males called "kings" and one or more fertile females called "queens".

Name: Textile Cone
Summary: The textile cone (Conus textile) is a species of cone snail, a group of venomous sea snails. Much like other cone snails, it is a predatory species that uses venom to hunt for prey. They inhabit waters along the Indian Ocean, notably of the East Coast of Africa and around Australia. Despite being prized by people for the vibrant colors on their shells, they are extremely dangerous, as they are among the most venomous animals on the planet.

Name: Thiomargarita Namibiensis
Summary: Thiomargarita Namibiensis is a protobacteria native to the coast of Namibia. It is currently the largest bacteria species ever discovered.

Name: Three-Toed Sloth
Summary: Three-toed sloths are the slowest land mammals in the world. They are notoriously lethargic, only showing activity at brief moments of time. While they may move to different trees, sloths may spend 20% of their lives in a single, specific tree. Three-toed sloths have a combined head-and-body length of around 45 cm and weigh 3.5-4.5 kg.

Name: Thylacine
Summary: The Thylacine is a carnivorous marsupial that once lived throughout Australia, New Guinea, and Tasmania. It is nicknamed the Tasmania wolf due to its canine like features that arose from convergent evolution; the Tasmanian tiger nickname comes from its striped appearance. These creatures first emerged around 1.77 million to 780,000 years ago, during the early Pleistocene.[1] Around 3,200 years ago, the Thylacine population on mainland Australia would have died off, the major causes thought to be human activity and the introduction of dingoes.[2] Populations would remain prevalent on the island of Tasmania up until the early 20th century, before extermination by farmers and bounty hunters, along with habitat loss, competition from wild dogs, and disease would devastate them (with possibly already low genetic diversity worsening their chances of survival).[3] The last Thylacine was captured and kept in Hobart Zoo until he died on September 7, 1936.

Name: Tick
Summary: Ticks are arachnids, part of the superorder Parasitiformes. Along with mites, they constitute the subclass Acari. Ticks are external parasites, living by feeding on the blood of mammals, birds, and sometimes reptiles and amphibians. Ticks evolved by the Cretaceous period, the most common form of fossilisation being amber immersion. Ticks are widely distributed around the world, especially in warm, humid climates.

Name: Titan Beetle
Summary: The titan beetle is a Neotropical longhorn beetle, the sole species in the genus Titanus, and one of the largest known beetles. The titan beetle is one of the largest beetles, with the largest reliable measured specimen being 16.7 cm in length, comparable to such beetles as Xixuthrus heros and the Hercules beetle.

Name: Tree Weta
Summary: Tree wētā are commonly encountered in forests and suburban gardens throughout most of New Zealand. They most commonly live in holes in trees formed by beetle and moth larvae or where rot has set in after a twig has broken off. The hole, called a gallery, is maintained by the wētā and any growth of the bark surrounding the opening is chewed away. They readily occupy a preformed gallery in a piece of wood (a "wētā motel") and can be kept in a suburban garden as pets. A gallery might house a harem of up to 10 adult females and one male.

Name: Tuatara
Summary: Tuataras (Sphenodon punctatus) are a species of reptile native to New Zealand. Their common name Tuatara comes from the Maori language and means "peaks on the back."[1] Although they resemble lizards, Tuataras are actually part of an order of reptiles called Rhynchocephalia, and moreover are the last surviving members of this once diverse group. Currently they are considered an At Risk Relict species in New Zeleand's Threat Classification System.[2] Tuataras were once widespread across New Zealand, but wild populations are now mostly limited to 32 islands off the coasts of the North Island and the Marlborough Sounds, with causes of their decline including poaching and the introduction of rats and other mammals to the islands.[3] However, extensive conservation efforts have helped to protect their populations, and there has been evidence that these efforts are proving fruitful.[4]

Name: Tullimonstrum
Summary: Tullimonstrum, colloquially known as the Tully monster or sometimes Tully's monster, is an extinct genus of soft-bodied bilaterian animal that lived in shallow tropical coastal waters of muddy estuaries during the Pennsylvanian geological period, about 300 million years ago.

Name: Turritopsis Dohrnii
Summary: Turritopsis Dohrnii, also known as the "immortal jellyfish," are jellyfish that are, as their nickname implies, biologically immortal. It achieves immortality by having the ability to revert itself into an immature polyp, de-aging itself in the process. Despite its inability to die of old age, it can still get killed by predators or disease.

Name: Vaaiki
Summary: Vaaiki is a nano bioweapon made to kill people very slowly, one of Wanna's many weapons made for torture. It acts as a virus; when it is inserted into the victim's body, it immediately puts them into a comatose state and shreds apart their viscera itself, all prolonging until it either kills the victim or is removed from their body. It is impervious to any kind of antibiotics, so the Wonderful Ones had to shrink down to microscopic size and fight it inside Vorkken's body.

Name: Vapor (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Ann Darnell, along with her brother James, was among the small group led by Simon Utrecht to simulate the crash that gave the Fantastic Four their powers and has remained with the U-Foes ever since as Vapor.

Name: Variable Neon Slug
Summary: The variable neon slug (Nembrotha kubaryana) is a colorful species of sea slug native to the coasts in the west Indo-Pacific. The variable neon slug ingests a mild toxin from the sea squirts it eats, and is capable of using it defensively to ward off predators. The variable neon slug's striking coloration is due to aposematism, a natural phenomenon in which an animal has a vibrant coloration in order to warn predators that they are either toxic or distasteful to consume.

Name: Velvet Ant
Summary: Velvet Ants are a species of wasp.

Name: Velvet Worm
Summary: Velvet Worms are members of the Onychophora phylum. They are soft-bodied invertebrates with surprisingly predatory properties. When hunting, they produce sticky strings that keep prey in place for consumption.

Name: Venus Flytrap
Summary: The Venus Flytrap is a carnivorous plant native to North and South Carolina. It obtains food through two leaves that resemble a mouth, bristling with sensitive hairs that cause the leaves to clamp shut when something bends them. The cilia, or the finger-like projects on the edges of the leaves, keep larger insects from escaping as it secretes digestive juices to break down the insect, a process which can take several days.

Name: Venus' Flower Basket
Summary: Venus' flower basket (Euplectella aspergillum) is a species of hexactinellid sea sponge, endemic to deep ocean waters off the coast of the Philippines and Japan. Sea sponges are as simple as animals can get. The nanostructures of the Venus' flower basket were claimed to be potentially useful for more efficient, low-cost solar cells.

Name: Virginia Opossum
Summary: The Virginia opossum is a species of opossum that resides in North America; in fact, it is the only native marsupial in North America. Opossums are famously known for their act of feigning death in order to deceive its opponents. This act led to the expression "playing possum."

Name: Volcana (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Marsha Rosenberg and her friend Mary MacPherran were given superpowers by Doctor Doom during the events of Secret Wars, and joined his team under the name of Volcana, where she met and fell in love with Molecule Man.

Name: Warrior Wasp
Summary: The Warrior Wasp is a genus of eusocial paper wasps found in the tropical forests of the Americas. Commonly known as drumming wasps, they are known for their aggressive behavior, a threat display consisting of multiple insects guarding a nest beating their wings in a synchronized fashion, and an extremely painful sting.

Name: Water Bear
Summary: The water bear is a micro-animal known for its immense resilience.

Name: Waterwraith
Summary: The Waterwraith is a mysterious water-based boss character in Nintendo's Pikmin 2.

Name: Werner Werman (Cuphead Show)
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:WernerWermanIntro.ogg

Name: Wildcat
Summary: The wildcat is a species complex comprising two small wild cat species: the European wildcat and the African wildcat. The European wildcat (Felis silvestris) are natives of continental Europe, Scotland, Turkey and the Caucasus. It inhabits forests from the Iberian Peninsula, Italy, Central and Eastern Europe to the Caucasus. While the African wildcat (Felis lybica) is a small wildcat species native to Africa, West and Central Asia up to Rajasthan in India and Xinjiang in China. Unlike their descendants, wildcats are wild and can't be tamed.

Name: Wishiwashi
Summary: Wishiwashi is a Water Type Pokémon from Alola. Usually, it is a weak and delicious Pokémon. But if it is threatened, it will call upon its kin to form into its gigantic School form.

Name: Xenobot
Summary: Xenobots, named after the African clawed frog (Xenopus laevis), are self-healing microbots that are designed and programmed by a computer and built from the ground up using biological cells. A xenobot is a biological machine under 1 millimeter wide and small enough to travel inside human bodies. They are made of skin cells and heart cells, stem cells harvested from frog embryos.

Name: Xerces Blue Butterfly
Summary: The Xerces blue butterfly was a species of butterfly endemic to the sand dunes of California. Due to a loss in habitat and subsequent extirpation of its main food sources, lotus flowers and lupin, the Xerces blue became extinct in the early 1940s. It has since become the most famous example of an invertebrate becoming extinct due to human activity.

Name: Yellowjacket (Real World)
Summary: Yellowjacket is the common name in North America for predatory social wasps of the genera Vespula and Dolichovespula. Members of these genera are known simply as "wasps" in other English-speaking countries.

Name: Aardvark
Summary: The aardvark (Orycteropus afer) is a nocturnal mammal native to sub-Saharan Africa. It uses its powerful claws to dig burrows, and primarily feeds on termites and other insects. Despite its appearance, it is most closely related to the elephant.

Name: African Bullfrog
Summary: The African bullfrog (Pyxicephalus adspersus) is a large species of bullfrog. Bullfrogs are known for their aggressive behavior, often for the sake of social dominance. It is a large frog, with males weighing 1.4 kg (3.1 lb), though they can easily exceed 2 kg (4.4 lb).

Name: African Wild Dog (Real World)
Summary: The African wild dog (Lycaon pictus), also called the painted wolf or Cape hunting dog, is a canine native to sub-Saharan Africa. It is the largest indigenous canine in Africa, and the only extant member of the genus Lycaon, which is distinguished from Canis by dentition highly specialised for a hypercarnivorous diet, and a lack of dewclaws.

Name: Air Gun
Summary: Air guns, also known as air rifles, are guns that make use of diabolo-shaped pellets or spherical pellets called "BBs." They represent the oldest pneumatic technology, dating back to 1580. Air guns are used for hunting, pest control, recreational shooting (also known as plinking), and competitive sports such as the Olympics.

Name: Akagi (5 Ronin)
Summary: Ronin Akagi returns home from war to find his house burnt to ashes, and his wife and seven year old son dead at the hands of the Daimyo. Vowing revenge, he endlessly stalks the soldiers of Daimyo to slaughter them mercilessly, considering himself already dead.

Name: Alabai
Summary: The Central Asian Shepherd Dog, also known as alabai is a livestock guardian dog breed. Traditionally, the breed was used for guarding sheep and goat herds, as well as to protect and for guard duty. This breed presents a robust dog of greater than average size with great strength and power.

Name: Alligator Snapping Turtle
Summary: Alligator snapping turtles (Macrochelys temminckii) are turtles notorious for their powerful bites. They are identified by their spiked, plated carapaces, which helps to set them apart from common snapping turtles.

Name: Almiraj
Summary: The Almiraj at a first glance appears simply as a rabbit with the horn of a unicorn, and while that asessment is true they can still be quite dangerous due to their unpredictable nature and their inante teleportation ability which earned them the nickname Blink Rabbit. An even more dangerous variant of the Almiraj is the Psionic one which has a 10% to appear when ever an Almiraj gives birth, this Almiraj has various abilities such as Detonate and Molecular Agitation which makes it a formidable foe.

Name: Amadeus Cho
Summary: Mere minutes after achieving the highest score ever on the Excello Soap Company’s “Brain Fight” internet game, earning the title “Mastermind Excello,” 16-year-old Amadeus Cho was approached by a woman called Agent Sexton, representing an unidentified agency wishing to train him. Following his refusal, his Arizona home was blown up, killing his parents and sister, but Amadeus escaped, arriving in Jackalope, New Mexico the following morning. Contacting Sexton, he dismissed her claim that a second agency was responsible. Adopting an orphaned coyote pup, Amadeus confronted a helicopter sent by his enemies, deflecting the aim of one of the attacker’s gun to distract another attacker, whose misfired missile, whether by accident or design, struck bystander Bruce Banner, triggering his transformation into the Hulk. The Hulk quickly disabled the helicopter and took Amadeus and the pup to safety before departing, earning the boy’s undying devotion.

Name: American Bullfrog
Summary: The American Bullfrog is one of several species of bullfrog. Bullfrogs are known for their aggressive behavior, often for the sake of social dominance. Bullfrogs measure about 3.6 to 6 in (9 to 15 cm) from snout to vent. They grow fast in the first eight months of life, typically increasing in weight from 5 to 175 g (0.18 to 6.17 oz), and large, mature individuals can weigh up to 500 g (1.1 lb). In some cases bullfrogs have been recorded as attaining 800 g (1.8 lb) and measuring up to 8 in (20 cm) in length.

Name: American Eel
Summary: The American eel (Anguilla rostrata) is a species of freshwater eel native to Atlantic coastlines, from as far north as Greenland, as far south as Venezuela, and as far inland as the Great Lakes. Unlike many other fish, they can survive in both freshwater and saltwater environments.

Name: American Lobster
Summary: The American lobster (Homarus americanus) is a species of lobster native to the eastern coast of the United States and Canada. It is the heaviest crustacean in the world, and can grow more than 4 feet in length and 20 kilograms in weight.[1]

Name: American Pit Bull
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: AMT Baby AutoMag
Summary: The AMT Baby AutoMag is a very rare limited production American .22 Long Rifle pistol.

Name: Angelfish
Summary: The Angelfish (Pterophyllum) is a freshwater fish from the family Cichlidae.

Name: Annie Hastur
Summary: Dangerous, yet disarmingly precocious, Annie is a child mage with immense pyrokinetic power. Even in the shadows of the mountains north of Noxus, she is a magical outlier. Her natural affinity for fire manifested early in life through unpredictable, emotional outbursts, though she eventually learned to control these tricks. Her favorite includes the summoning of her beloved teddy bear, Tibbers, as a fiery beast hellbent on destruction. Lost in the perpetual innocence of childhood, Annie wanders the dark forests, always looking for someone to play with.

Name: Anomalocaris
Summary: Anomalocaris (abnormal shrimp) was an extremely ancient species of animal vaguely related to arthropods. It is considered one of the first apex predators. It was presumed to have lived around 500 million years ago during the Cambrian era, with the first complete fossil having been discovered within the Burgess Shale.

Name: Anurognathus
Summary: Anurognathus is a genus of small pterosaur of the Anurognathid family that lived during the late Jurassic of Germany. Its name comes from the Greek words ανоυρα, which means "frog," and γναθος, which means "jaw." It is among the smallest pterosaurs behind the likes of Nemicolopterus, but the later may have been larger as the specimen found was a juvenile or subadult. Its large eyes and broad wings were suited for a maneuverable insectivore that hunted in lowlight levels.

Name: Arapaima
Summary: Arapaimas are freshwater fish residing in the Amazon River and one of the largest species of freshwater fish.[1] Arapaima normally reach lengths of up to 2 meters, although in rare cases they can exceed 2.5 meters and over 100 kg.[2][1]

Name: Archaeopteryx
Summary: Archaeopteryx is a transitional genus between dinosaurs and birds and is widely considered to be the first bird. It was one of few dinosaur creatures to have its color determined, in which case it had a 95% likelihood of being black. Archaeopteryx are small birds with the capability of flight; they can reach a length of 50 cm and a weight of 0.8-1 kg.

Name: Argentine Ant Mega-Colony
Summary: The absence of aggression within Argentine ant colonies was first reported in 1913 by Newell & Barber, who noted “…there is no apparent antagonism between separate colonies of its own kind”. Later studies showed that these “supercolonies” extend across hundreds or thousands of kilometers in different parts of the introduced range, first reported in California in 2000, then in Europe in 2002, Japan in 2009, and Australia in 2010. Several subsequent studies used genetic, behavioral, and chemical analyses to show that introduced supercolonies on separate continents actually represent a single global supercolony.

Name: Arkadimon (Cyber Sleuth)
Key: '''Arkadimon Baby''' | '''Arkadimon Rookie''' | '''Arkadimon Champion''' | '''Arkadimon Ultimate''' | '''Arkadimon Mega''' | '''Arkadimon Ultra'''
Summary: Arkadimon is one of the main antagonists of Digimon Story: Cyber Sleuth Hacker's Memory. It was imprisoned in Underzero but was freed when the worlds connected. Reacting to Ryuji's negative emotions, It becomes his partner Digimon and causes havoc in both Eden and the Real world.

Name: Arkarua
Summary: Arkarua is a Precambrian fossil organism of unknown age that is found in Ediacarian rock in Australia. Arkarua may be an echinoderm, making Arkarua the earliest known echinoderm and among the oldest non-sponge animal fossils in existence. Its status as an echinoderm is, however, debated since all casts of arkarua show no hint of their internal structure.

Name: Arthropleura (Real World)
Summary: Arthropleura Armata is an extinct millipede and an arthropod that lived in what is now northeastern North America and Scotland around 315 to 299 million years ago, during the late Carboniferous Period, and could reach lengths of 2.5 meters.

Name: Asian Giant Hornet
Summary: The Asian giant hornet is the world's largest hornet. It is native to temperate and tropical East Asia, South Asia, Mainland Southeast Asia, parts of the Russian Far East, and was found in the Pacific Northwest in late 2019, with no reports since to suggest that they have become established there. They prefer to live in low mountains and forests, while almost completely avoiding plains and high-altitude climates.

Name: Atlantic Hagfish
Summary: The Atlantic Hagfish (Myxine glutinosa) is a jawless eel-like fish found in the Atlantic Ocean. Atlantic hagfish are best known for their ability to produce a slimy mucus when provoked. Hagfish mucus is being researched for potential uses, as the proteins that it contains can be made into a strong fiber.

Name: Atlas Moth
Summary: The Atlas Moth is a moth from the genus Attacus, it is one of the largest moths in the world with a wingspan measuring 24cm

Name: Australian Box Jellyfish
Summary: The Australian Box Jellyfish (Chironex fleckeri) is the largest species of Box Jellyfish. It inhabits waters along the coast of Australia, along with New Guinea, the Philippines, Malaysia, Singapore, and Vietnam. Like other Box Jellyfish, it has four eye-clusters with 24 eyes. They pose a danger to humans due to their potent venom and near transparent bodies, the latter of which makes them hard to spot in the water.

Name: Australopithecus
Summary: Australopithecus was the first bipedal ape to have ever existed and was the closest related animal to humans, apart from other humans themselves. Although they are the closest to us, they aren't close enough to be called human.

Name: Awakened Shrub
Summary: Brought to life by magic, the Awakened Shrub is a magical plant. They mainly appear through casters using the Awaken spell, although other similar magic can create them as well.

Name: Axolotl
Summary: Axolotls are a species of underwater salamander that are at the brink of extinction in the wild, yet are often seen in labs and as exotic pets. Axolotls are used as model animals in scientific research for their amazing ability to regenerate lost limbs and even bits of vital organs.

Name: Bacteria (Kane Pixels)
Summary: Bacteria, are a species of entity that are recurring characters in the analog horror series The Backrooms. Bacteria resemble tall, thin, black humanoids that appear to be made of wires. Bacteria first was shown in The Backrooms: Found Footage, the first episode of the series, in which one chases and presumably kills Kane Pints. It exhibits similar behavior in the episodes Found Footage #2 and Pitfalls and is seen climbing on the ceiling in The Backrooms- Motion Detected. In Autopsy Report, more is learned about the nature of Bacteria, with it being implied to be a mutated strain of the hay bacillus disease. Despite all this, much about Bacteria is still left to be seen.

Name: Bacteriophage
Summary: Bacteriophages are one of the most common organic beings in the whole world, with an estimated number of 1031 on the planet. They are a kind of virus that infects bacteria and use them to reproduce.

Name: Bailey Hoskins (Worst X-Man Ever)
Summary: In an alternate universe, Bailey Hoskins thought of himself as an unremarkable boy, part of no clique and having no notable hobbies, until the day his parents reveal to him that he may be a mutant. Excited at the prospects, he heads to Xavier's to find out about himself, and learns he only has the ability to blow himself up like a "human firework".

Name: Bald Eagle
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Bald-Faced Hornet
Summary: The bald-faced hornet is a eusocial wasp of the cosmopolitan family Vespidae.

Name: Banana Slug
Summary: The banana slug is the common name for a genus of slugs native to the Pacific Northwest. These slugs are predominantly yellow in coloration, resembling a banana, but can have darker spots or patches. Banana slugs are hermaphrodites, and fill a niche in their ecosystem as a decomposer. Although generally non-threatening, banana slugs boast a few advantages such as Surface Scaling and High-Low Regeneration.

Name: Banded Archerfish
Summary: The banded archerfish is a brackish water perciform fish under the genus Toxotes, and is one of three species of archerfish confirmed to fire off jets of water as a method of hunting prey. These jets of water seemingly accelerate once they're fired off by the archerfish. While it is possible to keep the banded archerfish as a pet, it generally isn't advisable to do so as, due to their preference of capturing live prey, they are difficult to feed.

Name: BB Gun
Summary: BB Guns are a type of air gun that fire spherical pellets called "BBs." They were initially invented in 1886 for youth gun training. BB pellets typically are fired from 0.177 caliber BB guns and have a weight range from 5.1 to 5.4 grain (0.33 to 0.35 grams).

Name: Bedbug
Summary: Bed bugs are Parasitic insects, similar to the Flea and Mosquito. These insects feed exclusively on blood and may survive a year without eating. Adult Cimex are light brown to reddish-brown, flat, oval, and have no hind wings. The front wings are vestigial and reduced to pad-like structures. Adults grow to 4–5 mm long and 1.5–3 mm wide.

Name: Beelzebufo
Summary: Beelzebufo is a genus of giant frog, represented by the single species Beelzebufo ampinga. It lived in Madagascar around 70 million years ago, during the late Cretaceous. It is closely related to Ceratophryidae, the family that includes modern South American Horned Frogs.[1] In fact, Beelzebufo relation to Ceratophryidae hints at South America's connection with Madagascar.[2]

Name: Beewolf
Summary: Beewolves are solitary, predatory wasps, most of which prey on bees, hence their common name. The adult females dig tunnels in the ground for nesting, while the territorial males mark twigs and other objects with pheromones to claim the territory from competing males.

Name: Benjamin Franklin (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Benjamin Franklin is the historic founding father of the United States of America. His life remains mostly the same as in our real world, but he had somehow found a way to cheat death and remain as a form of electrical apparition. He became a frequent ally of Deadpool after assisting him in getting rid of the zombified presidents.

Name: Beretta ARX160
Summary: The Beretta ARX160 is an Italian modular rifle manufactured by Beretta. Developed for the Italian Armed Forces as part of the Soldato Futuro (English: "Future Soldier") program, the ARX160 was launched in 2008 as a commercial weapon system independent from the Soldato Futuro ensemble, complete with a companion single-shot 40×46mm NATO low-velocity grenade launcher, called the GLX160, which can be mounted underneath the rifle or used with an ad hoc stock system as a stand-alone weapon.

Name: Betta Fish
Summary: The Betta fish or Siamese fighting fish (Betta splendens) is a freshwater fish native to Southeast Asia, namely Cambodia, Laos, Myanmar, Malaysia, Thailand, and Vietnam. It is the only species in the genus Betta (which includes 76 species) to be called such as a common name due to its popularity in the pet trade.

Name: Black Fox (Marvel Comics)
Summary: A master thief past his prime, Black Fox had taught best of the best in his heydays, but only looks now to save up for his retirement to the French Riviera.

Name: Black Mamba
Summary: The Black Mamba is the fastest snake in the world and is also the 2nd longest venomous snake after the King Cobra. Black mambas typically grow 2-3 meters long, although some specimens are known to have reached 4.3-4.5 meters. The snake typically weighs around 1.6 kg. A study on seven black mambas showed a weight range of 520 grams to 2.4 kg dependinng on the snake's length.

Name: Black Spiny-Tailed Iguana
Summary: The black spiny-tailed iguana (Ctenosaura similis) is a species of iguana native to Mexico and Central America, and has been introduced to Florida. It is the fastest species of lizard in the world.

Name: Blink (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Clarice Ferguson, first discovered her mutant abilities after a traumatic and bloody accident, which left her fearful of her own powers. Alongside other young mutants, she was captured by the techno-organic Phalanx, who sought to assimilate their abilities. In a selfless act of bravery, Clarice sacrificed herself to save her fellow captives—an act that deeply affected the survivors and inspired them to form the team known as Generation X.

Name: Blizzard (Gregor Shapanka)
Summary: Dr. Gregor Shapanka, Ph.D., an employee of Stark Industries, was conducting private research into a means for achieving physical immortality, who got fired for attempting to steal from Anthony Stark's vault.

Name: Blobfish
Summary: The Blobfish refers to any species of fish within the Psychrolutidae family. They typically live in the deep waters off the coast of southeastern Australia and Tasmania. It lives in New Zealand as well.

Name: Blue Glaucus
Summary: The blue glaucus is a species of sea slug native to oceans worldwide. It is notable for its deadly venom, which it integrates into its system via consuming the Portuguese Man O’War. Although having lackluster strength, the blue glaucus makes up for it with potent venom.

Name: Blue Ringed Octopus
Summary: The blue-ringed octopus is a small species of octopus native to the coasts, reefs, and tide pools in and around Australia. The blue-ringed octopus is diminutive in size, weighing around 28 grams and being around 20 centimetres from head to tentacle tip. Despite this, it is notable for being one of the most venomous creatures on Earth, with a single octopus carrying enough venom to kill 26 adult humans within minutes.

Name: Bobby Singer
Summary: Robert Steven "Bobby" Singer (1950-2012) was a hunter, an old friend of John Winchester, and over time evolved into a father-figure for John's sons Sam and Dean. He was also one of the longest lasting recurring characters, appearing in every season so far.

Name: Bombardier Beetle
Summary: Bombardier Beetles are best known for their unique defense mechanism. In order to defend themselves from predators, bombardier beetles spray a hot caustic fluid at predators in an effort to make them back off. They can swivel their rear end up to 270º, allowing them to aim their defense mechanism nearly anywhere including right in front of them.

Name: Boomslang
Summary: The Boomslang is a highly-venomous species of Colubridae snake native to Sub-Saharan Africa.

Name: Bootlace Worm
Summary: The bootlace worm is a species of ribbon worm and one of the longest known animals, with specimens up to 55 m (180 ft) long being reported, although this has not been confirmed. Its mucus is highly toxic. The bootlace worm is in the phylum Nemertea or ribbon worms. It is the most common nemertean found along the coasts of Britain.

Name: Bow (Real World)
Summary: Bows are among the earliest weapons known to man. A bow is a simplistic weapon in design; simply put, a lightweight arrow is shot with the pull of a string. While bows were made obsolete in favor of guns in war, bows are still used in hunting and sporting events (particularly the Olympic sport of archery). More recently, compound bows were developed, boasting stronger draw weights than modern recurve bows. Multiple arrows can be fired in a single shot, although generally multiple arrows being fired at once aren't as effective as firing a single shot.

Name: Broadclub Cuttlefish
Summary: The broadclub cuttlefish is the second largest species of cuttlefish after Sepia apama. It is also the most common species of cuttlefish found in coral reefs, living in depths of up to 30 meters.

Name: Brown Pelican
Summary: Brown Pelicans are one of the 8 members of the genus Pelecanus. The genus is known for its gluttony and willingness to eat nearly anything. Surprisingly, Brown Pelicans are more grounded in terms of their prey variety.

Name: Bull Terrier
Summary: The bull terrier is a breed of terrier developed in the 19th century as a fighting dog. Over the years, the breed has shifted from this original purpose to become a companion and show dog. It is easily distinguished from other breeds by its long, egg-shaped head.

Name: Bulldog
Summary: The Bulldog, also known as the British Bulldog or English Bulldog, is a medium-sized dog breed. It is a muscular, hefty dog with a wrinkled face and a distinctive pushed-in nose. Bulldogs are popular pets; they were the fifth most popular purebreed in the US in 2017 according to the American Kennel Club.

Name: Bullet Ant
Summary: The bullet ant is an ant named for its extremely potent sting. It inhabits humid lowland rainforests from Nicaragua and the extreme east of Honduras and south to Paraguay. Worker ants are 18–30 mm (0.7–1.2 in) long and resemble stout, reddish-black, wingless wasps. Paraponera is predatory, and like all primitive poneromorphs, does not display polymorphism in the worker caste; the queen ant is not much larger than the workers. They are not aggressive ants but are vicious when defending the nest, when they produce a stridulating sound and sting with ferocity.

Name: Burmese Python
Summary: The Burmese python is a python that is once considered a subspecies of the Indian python before it was split into its own species in 2009. While Burmese pythons are Vulnerable species in its native range in India, Burmese pythons have taken an invasive stronghold in Florida, with its presence mostly extirpating many native species within their range.

Name: Caitlyn (Arcane)
Summary: Caitlyn Kiramman is a scion of the Kiramman Clan, one of the ruling houses of Piltover. Eager to see the world for herself and disdainful of the traditional elitist lifestyle that her parents had raised her in, Caitlyn joined the Enforcers as a young woman to make a name for herself. When Marcus, the Sheriff of the Enforcers, and her parents-for very different reasons-started blocking her efforts to further investigate an undercity conspiracy, Caitlyn set off on her own to find answers, only to get much more than she bargained for.

Name: Caitlyn (League of Legends)
Summary: Tier: At least 10-B, 7-B with Weapons | At least 10-B, High 6-C with Weapons | At least 10-B, 4-B with Weapons | At least 10-B, At least 7-B with Weapons, Low 2-C via Hax

Name: California Condor Louse
Summary: The California condor louse (Colpocephalum californici) was a species of louse that parasitized the California condor. When all remaining California condors in the wild were taken into captivity for a captive breeding program, they were chemically deloused, and as a result, the species went extinct in one of the most documented cases of conservation-induced extinction.

Name: California Market Squid
Summary: The California Market Squid (Loligo Opalescens) is a species of market squid abundant along the coast of Baja, Mexico to Southeast Alaska.[1] 50 US tons of this squid is harvested at a time by fishermen, and even more squid are harvested through the days and years of the Pacific coast of North America.[2]

Name: California Sea Cucumber
Summary: The California sea cucumber (Apostichopus californicus), also known as the giant California sea cucumber, is a species of sea cucumber native to the eastern Pacific Ocean. They are commonly caught and harvested for consumption, and recommended by the Monterey Bay Aquarium Seafood Watch as the most sustainable species of sea cucumber.

Name: California Sea Lion
Summary: The California sea lion (Zalophus californianus) is a species of eared seal native to the coastlines of western North America. It is the fastest species of seal in the world, and can swim up to 25 miles per hour.

Name: Canada Goose
Summary: Canada Geese, more commonly referred to as Canadian Geese, are geese best known for their successful habituation in human-altered areas. They have become a pest species due to its aggression towards humans and other species of animals.

Name: Candidatus Carsonella ruddii
Summary: Candidatus Carsonella ruddii is the smallest bacterium and living organism of the entire world discovered so far. It is an endosymbiotic bacterium found in insects.

Name: Cane Corso
Summary: The Cane Corso is an Italian breed of mastiff. It is used for personal protection, tracking, law enforcement, as a guard dog, and as a companion dog.

Name: Cane Toad
Summary: The Cane Toad is a notorious invasive species in Australia and various parts of Oceania. Cane toads are a poisonous toad that secretes bufotoxin through its glands, which is especially dangerous to dogs. If you live around cane toads and your pet shows excessive drooling, extremely red gums, head-shaking, crying, loss of coordination, and/or convulsions, take it to a vet immediately.

Name: Capybara
Summary: The capybara (Hydrochoerus hydrochaeris) is a giant rodent native from South America. Capybaras are the largest living rodent and a member of the genus Hydrochoerus. They are close relatives include guinea pigs and rock cavies. Capybaras inhabits savannas and dense forests and lives near bodies of water. The capybaras are hunted for its meat and hide and also for grease from its thick fatty skin.

Name: Caracal
Summary: The caracal (Caracal caracal) is a medium-sized wild cat native to Africa, the Middle East, Central Asia, and arid areas of Pakistan and northwestern India. It is characterised by a robust build, long legs, a short face, long tufted ears, and long canine teeth.

Name: Caribbean Monk Seal Nasal Mite
Summary: The Caribbean monk seal nasal mite (Halarachne americana) was a species of endoparasitic mite that parasitized the nasal airways of the Caribbean monk seal. Following the extinction of the Caribbean monk seal in 1952, the mite was unable to adapt and subsequently went extinct.

Name: Cassandra Nova (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Johnny Storm: And I’ll tell you who ‘her’ is. Cassandra Nova, a megalomaniacal psychotic asshole, a finger-lickin’ dead-inside pixie slab of third rate dime-store nut-milk, and I’ll tell you what she can do. Deadpool: I’m listening. Johnny Storm: She can lick my goddamn cinnamon ring clean and kick rocks all the way to bald hell. In fact, I don’t give a shit if she removes all my skin and pops me like some nightmarish blood balloon. If the last thing I do in this godforsaken cum gutter existence is light that fuck box on fire, I still won’t die happy.

Name: Cassandra Nova (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Cassandra Nova Xavier is what the Shi'ar call "Mummudrai", the spirit that is the equal and opposite of a person. However, due to the amazing genetic potential of Professor Charles Xavier, his Mummudrai was able to create a physical form, effectively a twin. While gestating in her mother Sharon Xavier's, womb, Cassandra was recognized by Charles as an evil presence, and he preemptively tried to kill her with his nascent psychic abilities. Cassandra was barely able to defend herself and the shock of the roiling battle caused Sharon to have a miscarriage. Though the doctors pronounced her stillborn, Cassandra in fact survived and spent the next decades as a growing mass of cells in a sewer wall, building a new body for herself and planning her revenge on her brother, and has been a recurring threat towards the X-Men ever since.

Name: Cassowary
Summary: Cassowaries are known as the third tallest bird (behind the emu and ostrich) and the second heaviest bird (behind the ostrich). Cassowaries, however, are #1 in the aggression department, having been known to attack humans, occasionally fatally. If you see a cassowary, do not crouch or turn your back against it; instead, keep a good eye on the cassowary and move away. Female cassowaries average at a weight of 58.5 kg while males average in at 29-34 kg. Of all birds, the cassowary is among the most closely related to their dinosaur ancestors.

Name: Central Bearded Dragon
Summary: Central bearded dragons (Pogona vitticeps) are small reptiles, native to the Australian Outback. They are omnivorous, and commonly kept as pets worldwide. Central bearded dragons, while seeming and being largely harmless, have some surprising capabilities that shouldn’t be overlooked, such as Small Size (Type 0) and Poison Manipulation.

Name: Cephalaspis
Summary: Cephalaspis is a genus (single-species) of primitive fish known as osteostracans. Its name comes from the Greek words kephalḗ (κεφαλή), which means "head," and aspís (ἀσπίς), which means "shield." Its most notable feature was its large, shield-like head which its name is derived. It lived in rivers 415–398 million years ago, during the early Devonian. With eyes on the top of its head and a mouth on its underside, it was a bottom feeder much like a Plecostomus or catfish, straining food into its jawless mouth. It would have likely fed on worms and crustaceans in the mud, along with feeding on detritus.

Name: Chameleon (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Born a Russian citizen named Dmitri Smerdyakov (Russian: Дмитрий Смердяков), he was the half-brother of Sergei Kravinoff.

Name: Chameleon (The Real World)
Summary: Chameleons are lizards found in Africa, Asia, and Europe.

Name: Charles Xavier
Summary: Charles Xavier (also known as Professor X) is a fictional superhero who appears in American comic books published by Marvel Comics as well as in a number of television and movie adaptations. The character was created in 1963 by writer Stan Lee and artist Jack Kirby, and has been a frequent if not regular character in most X-Men-related fiction since the beginning.

Name: Cheetah
Summary: The cheetah is a feline and a member of the "big cat family". They hunt by ambush and running full speed towards the prey, then sinking their teeth into their throat until the prey suffocates. The cheetah has a weight of 77 to 143 pounds and is the fastest land animal in real life.

Name: Chicken
Summary: The Chicken is an incredibly important domesticated bird and one of the few animals much more numerous than humans, at over 24 billion.

Name: Chihuahua
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:Chihuahua_bark.mp3

Name: Chimpanzee
Summary: The Chimpanzee is a primate and is the closest relative to humans (According to studies, their DNA is extremely similar to that of humans). They mainly eat fruit, vegetables and sometimes meat.

Name: Chinese Red-Headed Centipede
Summary: The Chinese red-headed centipede (Scolopendra subspinipes mutilans), also known as the Chinese red head, is a centipede from East Asia and Australasia. It averages 20 cm (8 inches) in length, weighs 3 grams, and lives in damp environments.

Name: Cioccolata
Summary: Cioccolata is a minor antagonist in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part V: Vento Aureo. A former doctor who was fired for "accidentally" killing a patient during surgery, he joins Passione alongside his "pet", Secco, as one of the Boss' Guard Squad members. Due to his malevolent nature, he is rarely called upon, but the Boss had no other choice but to call him to fight Bruno Bucciarati and his gang in Rome.

Name: Clouded Leopard
Summary: The clouded leopard (Neofelis nebulosa) is a wild cat inhabiting dense forests from the foothills of the Himalayas through mainland Southeast Asia into South China. Its head-and-body length ranges from 68.6 to 108 cm (27.0 to 42.5 in) with a 61 to 91 cm (24 to 36 in) long tail. It uses its tail for balancing when moving in trees and is able to climb down vertical tree trunks head first. It rests in trees during the day and hunts by night on the forest floor. They have two subspecies: the Mainland clouded leopard & Sunda clouded leopard, with the later being the largest.[1][2]

Name: Cockroach
Summary: Cockroaches are insects from the order Blattodea, which also contains termites. About 30 species of cockroaches are associated with human habitats, with four of them being considered pests. American cockroaches, which are common pests, have an average length of 4 cm and are 7 mm tall. The heaviest species of cockroach, the giant burrowing cockroach, can weigh up to 35 grams and can grow up to 8 cm long.

Name: Coconut Crab
Summary: The Coconut Crab is a species of terrestrial hermit crab. Reaching up to 4.1 kg, and a legspan of up to 1 m (3 feet, 3 inches), they are the largest known land arthropods on earth. It can be found on islands in the Pacific and Indian Oceans.

Name: Coelophysis
Summary: Coelophysis is a genus of small, carnivorous dinosaurs that lived during the Late Triassic period. The name "Coelophysis" means "Hollow Form" and refers to the hollow bones that were a notable characteristic of this dinosaur.

Name: Colt Single Action Army
Summary: The Colt Single Action Army, also known as the Single Action Army, SAA, Model P, Peacemaker and M1873, is a single-action revolver with a revolving cylinder holding six metallic cartridges. It was designed for the U.S. government service revolver trials of 1872 by Colt's Patent Firearms Manufacturing Company—today's Colt's Manufacturing Company—and was adopted as the standard military service revolver until 1892.

Name: Comet the Super-Horse (Pre-Crisis)
Summary: Comet the Super-Horse is the pet horse of Supergirl. Originally a centaur in ancient Greece named Biron, he was given a potion by the witch Circe after he saved her from water poisoning. The potion was intended to turn him into a full human but instead it turned him into a full horse. As compensation Circe granted Biron superpowers and immortality, but he was then sealed in an asteroid by a sorcerer who tried to poison Circe. Years later Supergirl traveled to this asteroid and her ship's passing broke the forcefield that was trapping him, and they became friends.

Name: Common Basilisk
Summary: Basilisks are creatures that, in myths, are either serpentine creautes or creatures that are visibly similar to cockatrices. Real-life basilisks, however, are completely different from the basilisks in European folktales; in fact, basilisks are actually lizards with the capability of running across water. Basilisks usually attain this feat by running bipedally, hence their nickname "the Jesus Christ lizard."

Name: Common Earthworm
Summary: The Common Earthworm (Lumbricus terrestris) is a species of earthworm that, while not the most abundant earthworm, is the most well-known earthworm. It has served as an example earthworm in science labs (including dissection).

Name: Common Snapping Turtle
Summary: Common snapping turtles (Chelydra serpentin) is a species of large freshwater turtle in the family Chelydridae. Its natural range extends from southeastern Canada, southwest to the edge of the Rocky Mountains, as far east as Nova Scotia and Florida.

Name: Common Starfish
Summary: The Common Starfish (Asterias Rubens) is the most common and well-known species of starfish in the north-east Atlantic Ocean. It typically can be found in depths ranging from intertidal zones to about 650 feet (200 meters) below sea level. They usually have a brownish or orange coloration, although deeper specimens are more pale. The common starfish is typically found on rocky and gravelly substrates where it is found preying on mollusks such as mussels and bivalves.

Name: Common Turkey
Summary: The common turkey (Meleagris gallopavo) is a wild game turkey in North America and a domesticated bird eaten in other countries, especially on holidays like Thankgiving and Christmas.[1]

Name: Condiment King (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Mitchell Mayo, once an average guy went inexplicably crazy and donned the identity of the Condiment King to cause crime. He was shown tormenting multiple policemen with his special designed sauce, until he was swiftly defeated by Batgirl and Robin. He was then taken to Arkham Asylum, where he eventually was able to work in the kitchen and fuel his obsession, as well as improve upon his formula. This was further aided by Poison Ivy, who taught him vast knowledge on roots, herbs, and spices. Years later, he would get out of Arkham and be "jokerized". Jokerization is stated to amplify the infected's personality, which actually made Mitchell a credible threat. This would almost cause the Birds of Prey to lose to him, as they though he was a joke. It is later stated due to the nature of Condiment King's obsession/portrayal as a joke, juries and parole boards don't take him seriously, thus allowing him to be set free on Gotham again and again. During Final Crisis Aftermath, Mitchell was one of Immortus' followers, The Army of the Endangered, and was cybernetically enhanced by the brilliant Professor Achilles Milo. He was the one to introduce the "Human Flame" to the group, which would be a mistake. Human Flame would rebel, and along with Seductress, kill every member of The Army of the Endangered, including Mitchell.

Name: Constructed Commoner
Summary: Made by the Harpers at Twilight, Constructed Commoners are the residents of the Wisteria Vale demiplane. They are wood mannequins brought to life by magic which are able to act as if they're real humans. They feel no pain, are shielded from detection magic, and never get tired.

Name: Cookiecutter Shark
Summary: The Cookiecutter Shark (Isistius brasiliensis) is a species of small dogfish shark that tends to inhabit deep waters. The males reach 42 centimeters (17 inches) long, while females can reach longer lengths of 56 centimeters (22 inches). These ectoparasites are named for the round, "cookie cutter" shaped bites that they leave in creatures such as fish and marine mammals; however, they are also known to feed on smaller animals, consuming them whole. They inhabit warm waters, spending daytime at depths of 3,500 meters at the deepest, and can even reach the surface at night.

Name: Cottonmouth (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Cornell Stokes, also known as Cottonmouth, is a crime boss stationed in Harlem, New York City. His negative influence on the people of Harlem led him to be opposed by Luke Cage.

Name: Coyote
Summary: The coyote (Canis latrans) is a carnivorous animal that is native to North America. It is closely related to the Gray Wolf and is much smaller than the more famous canine. It mainly eats meat, though it may also eat fruits and vegetables occasionally. The coyote has 19 recognized subspecies, with one of the most common being the Western Coyote, and the largest subspecies being the Eastern Coyote, which is the result of various historical and recent matings with various types of wolves.

Name: Crawling Claw
Summary: Crawling Claws are the dismembered hands of murderous humanoids, animated by evil spellcasters to continue the slaughter they wrought in life. Essentially, a ritual is done to place the soul of a creature in the severed hand, allowing it to work as a laborer for evil casters. Notably, these evil beings are immune to the powers of others concerning undead- and indeed, since their soul is totally under the supervision of their caster, they cannot be affected by such powers, making them ideal servants.

Name: Crazy Jane
Summary: Crazy Jane is the dominant alternate personality of Kay Challis, who has dissociative identity disorder, with a total of 64 unique identities. As a result of exposure to the alien Dominators' "gene bomb," each of her 64 alternate personalities has a different super-power. While Jane initially believed that she was the only one without a metahuman ability, this was later proven false. She eventually discovered that she had the ability to heal others (whether this healing is primarily emotional or physical is unknown).

Name: Crossbow
Summary: A crossbow is a type of elastic ranged weapon in similar principle to a bow, consisting of a bow-like assembly mounted horizontally on a main frame called a tiller, which is handheld in a similar fashion to the stock of a long gun. It shoots arrow-like projectiles called bolts or quarrels. The medieval European crossbow was called by many other names, most of which were derived from the word ballista, an ancient Greek torsion siege engine similar in appearance.

Name: Crow (Real World)
Summary: The Crow is a black corvid present worldwide. They are omnivorous and have an incredibly diverse diet, being able to adapt extremely well to human life, human change and urban cities. They are also present in many cultures due to their appearance and way of living.

Name: Crown-of-Thorns Sea Star
Summary: The crown-of-thorns sea star is a species of sea star endemic to coral reefs around the Indo-Pacific region. It is infamous for preying upon hard corals and being highly destructive to surrounding reefs. It is also difficult to remove due to its venomous spines, which contain a saponin that can cause sharp stinging pain, swelling, persistent bleeding, and nausea. The Pokémon Toxapex is based on this sea star.

Name: Cthulhu macrofasciculumque
Summary: Cthulhu macrofasciculumque is a organism used in the stomach of termites and was found in its hindgut. It is a parabasalid, a group of protists best known for their ability to break down lignocellulose and their common cellular structure accentuated by the presence of multiple flagella. C. macrofasciculumque has a bundle of twenty flagella on its anterior end, and may have a singular flagella on its posterior end. It is named after the popular fictional character Cthulhu.

Name: Dagger (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Tandy Bowen’s life started in privilege, but it was a life without the love of her parents, that made her decide to run away from home. While living on the streets she met Tyrone Johnson, but they were both kidnapped by scientists that wanted test subjects for their new experimental drugs. Although most of the test subjects died, Tandy and Tyrone survived, and as a side effect awakened powers. Now under the alias of Dagger, she becomes a personification of light that promises to rid the streets of all drugs in an attempt to stop what happened to her from happening to anyone else.

Name: Darren Cross (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Doctor Darren Cross was the protégé of Hank Pym, who usurped his mentor as CEO of Pym Technologies and rebranded it as Cross Technologies. Cross became obssessed with the Pym Particles and using Pym's technologies to achieve success, but the constant exposure to the particles negatively affected his mind. Cross had developed the Yellowjacket Suit and intended to sell it to HYDRA and the Ten Rings, but Pym and Hope Van Dyne joined forces with Ant-Man, who destroyed his entire research. Driven mad after losing everything he built, Cross wore the suit himself and became Yellowjacket, to get revenge by killing Ant-Man and his family. As Yellowjacket threatened Cassie Lang, he was confronted by Ant-Man, who neutralized him by shrinking him down to a sub-atomic level and destroying his suit.

Name: Death Cap
Summary: The death cap, scientifically named Amanita Phalloides, is one of the most poisonous mushrooms in the world. It is believed that eating as little as half a mushroom is enough to kill a healthy adult. It has been involved in the majority of deaths from mushroom poisoning and may have been the couse of death of Roman Emperor Claudius in 54 AD. Its primary toxic constituent is α-amanitin, which causes damage to the liver and kidneys and leads to hepatic and renal failure that can be fatal.

Name: Deathstalker
Summary: The Deathstalker is a species of scorpion carrying potent neutrotoxins within its deadly sting. Its venom can cause extreme pain in adult humans, although it isn't usually lethal to healthy adult humans. Children, elderly, and infirm people, however, may be at greater risk of death. Beneficially, however, chlorotoxin, one component of deathstalker venom, has shown potential of treating brain tumors, and the venom is capable of detecting cancer cell clusters as few as 200 cells.

Name: Destiny (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Irene Adler hailed from a prosperous Austrian family, born near the close of the 19th century. Raised in Salzburg, Austria, her mutant gift of precognition emerged at the tender age of 13. Without guidance in harnessing her newfound powers, she faced a deluge of disconcerting, alien sights and sounds. Struggling to preserve her mental faculties, Adler embarked on a journey to record her visions in diaries. a lifeline amidst the chaos. A few years later, Irene hired Raven Darkhölme, a consulting detective, to help her make sense of her diaries. They tried to use Irene's visions to change the future and fell in love in the process. But even though they could make money using Irene's abilities, they couldn't make big changes in society, which left them both frustrated.

Name: Devil's Hole Pupfish
Summary: The Devil's Hole pupfish (Cyprinodon diabolis) is the rarest fish in the world. It is only found within Devil's Hole, a small water-filled cavern within Ash Meadows National Wildlife Refuge in Nevada. As of spring 2019, there are only 139 living pupfish.

Name: Diamondback (Willis Stryker)
Summary: Willis Stryker was born and raised in Harlem, New York. He grew up on the streets alongside Carl Lucas, his best friend and future partner, and founded the Rivals gang together, where he took on the name of Diamondback. Stryker eventually became convinced however, that Lucas had seduced his girlfriend Reva, and in a fit of jealousy, got his ex-girlfriend murdered and his friend jailed.

Name: Didelphodon
Summary: Didelphodon is a genus of stagodont metatherians, a group that includes marsupials and their relatives. It's name means, "possum tooth." It had a high bite force relative to its body size, indicating a durophagous diet, acting as a predator to small shelled animals and vertebrates, and a scavenger feeding on carrion.[1] Studies also indicate that it may have been semi-aquatic. It lived in North America around 73–66 million years ago, during the late Cretaceous.

Name: Dimetrodon
Summary: The Dimetrodon was among the earliest land animals, belonging to a proto-mammalian group known as synapsids. Dimetrodons were predatory creatures, with larger dimetrodons often being apex predators. Despite being confused with dinosaurs, Dimetrodons had a temporal range between 295 and 272 million years ago and were more closely related to mammals than modern reptiles, although they were not direct ancestors.

Name: Dingo (Real World)
Summary: The Dingo is a dog that is found in Australia. Its taxonomic classification is debated. It is a medium-sized canine that possesses a lean, hardy body adapted for speed, agility, and stamina.

Name: Dinopithecus
Summary: Dinopithecus was a giant baboon that lived in Africa from the Pliocene to the Pleistocene. It is thought to have been bigger than a large man, one of the largest Primates to have ever existed. They lived alongside Homo Erectus; some argue that Homo Erectus drove them to extinction by killing all the young and sub-adults of their species as evidenced by ninety juvenile giant baboon bodies thought to have been killed by the human.

Name: Diplocaulus
Summary: Diplocaulus is a genus of lepospondyl amphibian recognizable by its boomerang-shaped head. Its name means meaning "double stalk," referring to the tabular horn-like protrusions on its skull. A number of ideas have been postulated as to the purpose of the "horns" along the back and sides of its head, such as supporting skin flaps or gills, counterbalance, or possibly defense. The most recent theory is that it provided lift and reduced drag while swimming.[1] This amphibian lived in freshwater environments around 306-255 million years ago from the late carboniferous to late Permian.

Name: Django Freeman
Summary: Tier: 10-A. 9-C with firearms. 8-C with preparation

Name: Dobermann
Summary: The Dobermann is a German breed of medium-large working dog of pinscher type. It was originally bred in Thuringia in about 1890 by Louis Dobermann, a tax collector. It has a long muzzle and – ideally – an even and graceful gait. The ears were traditionally cropped and the tail docked, practices which are now illegal in many countries.

Name: Dobsonfly
Summary: Dobsonflies are a subfamily of insects, Corydalinae, part of the Megalopteran family Corydalidae. The larvae are aquatic, living in streams, and the adults are often found along streams as well. The nine genera of dobsonflies are distributed in the Americas, Asia, and South Africa.

Name: Doctor Poison (Golden Age)
Summary: The first Doctor Poison was Maru, a Japanese princess, member of the war-time Villainy, Inc. and opponent of Wonder Woman. She used chemicals as weapons, and initially disguised herself as a male using a disturbing mask.

Name: Dodo
Summary: The Dodo is an extinct species of flightless bird closely related to modern pigeons that inhabited the Mauritian Islands until the 1600s, when Dutch settlers arrived on the island and hunted them to extinction.

Name: Dogo Argentino
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Domestic Cat
Summary: The Cat, also known as housecat, alley cat or Domestic Cat, is small, furry mammal. It is a subspecies F. s. catus belonging to the species Felis silvestris in the family Felidae. This animal is the most popular pet in the world.

Name: Domestic Sheep
