Summary: Since descending from the Asiatic Mouflon (Ovis Orentalis) and Bezoar Ibex (Capra aegagrus) in the middle east 10,500 years before present (YBP),[1][2] the raising of domestic sheep is responsible for much of the world's lamb supply, mutton supply,[1][3] wool,[1] sheep milk,[4][3] wool,[1][3] and cheese.[1][3][5] In 2011, there were more than 1 billion sheep in the world.[4] Their presence as the most common livestock affected the cultures that raised them.[6][7][8] Even domesticated, sheep preferably moves in flocks for protection.[9][10]

Name: Dorothy Spinner
Summary: Dorothy Spinner was a member of the Doom Patrol with the ability to draw imaginary beings from her mind into the real world.

Name: Dr. Cassee Dannell
Summary: A young prodigy, Dr. Cassee Dannell was a facility member and field scientist at Varkenbluff. She secretly studied the occult as well, which lead her to the terrifying realization that one of the recent finds of her team is an eldritch horror's egg. Attempting to get the egg before it hatched she tried sneaking to the museum housing it, leading to her getting caught and fried from her job. Thus she hires a group of adventurers in order to finish off the soon to hatch egg, offering her Bag of Holding alongside gold to those who succeed.

Name: Dracula Ant
Summary: Mystrium camillae, also known as the Dracula ant, is a species of ant endemic to the Indo-Australian region. Its jaw snap is the fastest recorded animal movement, snapping at speeds up to 200 mph.

Name: Driver Ant
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Dung Beetle
Summary: Dung Beetles are among the strongest insects in the world and are the strongest animals on earth in terms of body weight to lift ratio. At a bare minimum, dung beetles are capable of rolling dung ten times their own weight. They can bury dung 250 times their own weight in one night, and the strongest dung beetle, the taurus scarab (Onthophagus taurus) can pull a weight of up to 1141 times their own weight.

Name: Earwig
Summary: Earwigs make up the insect order Dermaptera. With about 2,000 species in 12 families, they are one of the smaller insect orders. Earwigs have characteristic cerci, a pair of forceps-like pincers on their abdomen, and membranous wings folded underneath short, rarely used forewings, hence the scientific order name, "skin wings". Some groups are tiny parasites on mammals and lack the typical pincers. Earwigs are found on all continents except Antarctica.

Name: Ebola Virus
Summary: The Ebola virus is a deadly virus native to West Africa. It commonly infects primates, such as chimpanzees, gorillas, and humans. It was first discovered in 1976, near the Ebola River in the Democratic Republic of the Congo. The Ebola virus is spread through contact with bodily fluids, and can cause a slew of dangerous symptoms within its host, including hemorrhaging, muscular and abdominal pain, and in up to 83% to 90% of cases, death.

Name: Egghead (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Dr. Elihas Starr was a scientist working at an US atomic research center. He was caught when trying to smuggle drafts of an atomic project, and then subsequently fired from the center, waiting to be judged for treason. However, the criminal world discovered his ordeal and offered him freedom if he was ready to put his intellect to the service of the crime lords. Taking on the name Egghead, Starr became a criminal mastermind, and arch enemy to Ant-Man.

Name: Ekko
Summary: Tier: At least 10-B, 9-C with Piltover Clock Hand, Low 2-C Environmental Damage Via Chronobreak | At least 10-B, likely higher, 9-C with QWQRE83 Chrono Blade, Low 2-C Environmental Damage Via Chronobreak

Name: Ekko (Arcane)
Summary: nan

Name: Elasti-Girl
Summary: Rita Farr, alias Elasti-Girl (later Elasti-Woman), is a member of the Doom Patrol able to grow to an enormous size. She married her teammate Mento and they adopted Beast Boy.

Name: Electric Eel
Summary: The electric eel (Electrophorus electricus), or poraque, is a South American electric fish plus the only member of its genus. Despite the name, the electric eel is a knifefish, not an eel. Its electric charge has been applied to eels that are nowhere near

Name: Eli Morrow (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Elias "Eli" Morrow was the maternal uncle of Robbie and Gabe Reyes and a former employee at Momentum Labs. Witnessing the experiments being done by his coworkers, Morrow began to crave the power for himself, and betrayed his colleagues, turning them into ghost-like entities before attacking Joseph Bauer in order to find the Darkhold, but Bauer fell into a coma before revealing its location, and Morrow was imprisoned at South Ridge Penitentiary. He was later kidnapped by Bauer's wife, Lucy in order to force Morrow to use the Darkhold and reverse the process. However, Morrow tricked her and managed to fulfill his original plan, entering the machine and obtaining the power of creating matter at his own will. In the final battle against the S.H.I.E.L.D., Morrow was killed by Ghost Rider, who revealed himself to be Robbie Reyes.

Name: Emperor Penguin
Summary: The emperor penguin (Aptenodytes forsteri) is the largest and heaviest living penguin in the world. It is native to Antarctica, and feeds primarily on fish, squid, and antarctic krill. Emperor penguin colonies can number in the hundreds to thousands and have an elaborate courtship and breeding process.

Name: Endoceras
Summary: Endoceras (name meaning "inner horn") is a genus of large endoceratid nautiloids, which are known for their long, straight shells. With an estimated full length of nearly 6 meters, they are considered the longest cephalopods in the fossil record.[1][2] Like others of its kind, Endoceras likely occupied the apex predator niche in the oceans during the Ordovician, hunting animals near the seafloor.

Name: English Mastiff
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:English_mastiff_barking_sound.mp3

Name: Eryops
Summary: Eryops is a large semi aquatic temnospondyl amphibian, the name of which comes from the Greek words ἐρύειν (eryein), which means 'drawn-out,' and ὤψ (ops), which means 'face.' The sole species Erypos megacephalus. It lived in the southwestern United States 299–278 million years ago, predominantly during the early Permian in what is now Texas,[1] while older specimens found in New Mexico from the late Carboniferous.[2] It inhabited lowlands around various bodies of freshwater, where it would hunt. Among the largest animals of it's time, they could reach 1.5 to 2 meters long on average,[2] and the largest could grow to 3 meters in length, with a mass of 102-222 kg.[3] Based on the structure of its vertebrae, limb girdle and ribs, this heavily built creature was well adapted for traversing land for prolonged periods of time.[4]

Name: Escapade (Marvel Comics)
Summary: When young Shela Sexton discovered both her mutant abilities and gender identity in quick succession, she was shunned by her parents and ran away with her best friend, Morgan Red. Determined to carve out her own path, she later emerged as the tech-clad thief known as Escapade, using her powers to target corrupt organizations and individuals—while Morgan provided crucial technical support.

Name: Etruscan Shrew
Summary: The Etruscan Shrew is the smallest mammal in terms of mass and one of the smallest mammals in the world. Its body length is second only to Kitti's hog-nosed bat in terms of body length. The Etruscan shrew is 3 to 5.2 cm long without its tail and weighs in at 1.3 to 2.5 grams.

Name: Euparkeria
Summary: Euparkeria is a form of Eucrocopod archosauriform reptile, distantly related to but not a direct ancestor of archosaurs (the group that includes crocodiles, dinosaurs, and pterosaurs). It was once thought to be capable of bipedal locomotion as a facultative biped, but later studies showed it was not possible for the creature to stand quadrupedally.[1] Its semi-erect gate does, however, provide insight into the evolution of a fully upright, erect gate in archosaurs, with later adaptations in bones around the hip arising in them.[2] It lived in present-day South Africa during the early to mid Triassic throughout the late Olenekian and early Anisian ages.

Name: European Flounder
Summary: The European flounder (Platichthys flesus) is a species of flounder native to European coastal waters and the Mediterranean Sea, but has also spread to Iran and the eastern coast of North America. It is an expert at camouflaging itself against the seabed, and uses this ability to act as an ambush predator and hide from its own predators.

Name: European Honeybee
Summary: The European honeybee (Apis mellifera) is a species of honeybee native to the Old World, but has since spread to every continent barring Antarctica due to human introduction. They are eusocial animals that work in colonies using their inner electromagnetic fields to gather pollen from flowers, storing it in the hive. Female worker bees are known to forage for pollen and defend the hive, while the males, called "drones", exist solely to mate with the queen and die off shortly after. They are known for being pollinators, one of the first domesticated insects, and their ability to leave their stingers in an attacker's body as it injects venom.

Name: European Hornet
Summary: The European Hornet is the largest eusocial wasp native to Europe.

Name: Eurypterus
Summary: Eurypterus is an extinct genus of eurypterid, a group of organisms commonly called "sea scorpions". The genus lived during the Silurian period, from around 432 to 418 million years ago. Eurypterus is by far the most well-studied and well-known eurypterid and its fossil specimens probably represent more than 90% of all known eurypterid specimens

Name: Executioner Wasp
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Federal Riot Gun
Summary: The Federal Riot Gun, or FRG, is a US-manufactured firearm by Federal Laboratories Inc., designed to fire non-lethal munitions. Its ammunition include 37 and 38mm baton and tear gas rounds. The baton rounds were cylindrical, rubber projectiles.

Name: Fennec Fox
Summary: The Fennec Fox is the smallest member of the canid family. Living in the deserts of North Africa, it survives by eating invertebrates and small animals. Its unique appearance and big ears have made it famous to the outside world.

Name: Fire Ant
Summary: Fire ants are several species of ants in the genus Solenopsis. Most notorious of these species is the RIFA, an aggressive invasive species native to the Amazon but are found in massive numbers in the south and southeastern US. These ants are notorious pests, with $750 million spent annually on RIFA-caused agricultural issues, including medical bills, livestock loss, and crop loss.

Name: Firestorm (Ronnie Raymond) (Post-Crisis)
Key: '''Ronnie Raymond''' | '''Firestorm (Ronnie Raymond + Other Person)''' | '''Firestorm (Jason Rusch + Ronnie Raymond)'''
Summary: The original Firestorm was distinguished by his integrated dual identity. High school student Ronnie Raymond and Nobel Prize-winning physicist Martin Stein were caught in a nuclear accident that allowed them to fuse into the "nuclear man" Firestorm. Due to Stein's being unconscious during the accident, Raymond was prominently in command of the Firestorm form with Stein as a voice of reason inside his mind. The banter between the two was a hallmark of their adventures.

Name: Flea
Summary: Fleas, the common name for the order Siphonaptera, includes 2,500 species of small flightless insects that survive as external parasites of mammals and birds. Fleas live by consuming blood, or hematophagy, from their hosts. Adult fleas grow to about 3 mm long, are usually brown, and have bodies that are "flattened" sideways or narrow, enabling them to move through their host's fur or feathers. They lack wings, but have strong claws preventing them from being dislodged, mouthparts adapted for piercing skin and sucking blood, and hind legs extremely well adapted for jumping.

Name: Floating Eye
Summary: One of the fastest creatures in the sea this small fish is a terrible fighter whose main food source is plankton left overs of other hunters. It often uses it eye to paralyse a creature and then have other hunters devour it and in return it eats the left overs.

Name: Flying Monkey
Summary: At first it was one monkey. It scared away the doves and built a little home in the headman's eaves. The children loved it. Then it was a dozen monkeys, tearing at the children's hair and making them drop their sweets and bits of cocount. The children hated it, and oh how they cried. Now it's hundred monkeys! They must be stopped, before they drive everyone out of the village!

Name: Francine Langstrom (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Francine Langstrom is the wife of Kirk Langstrom, Man-Bat. While she is currently living a normal life, she used to be as addicted to the Man-Bat serum as him, threatening Gotham's inhabitants as a monstrous, giant vampire bat.

Name: French Bulldog
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:French_Bulldog_Barking_Sound_Effects_Barking_Sounds_For_Dogs_Playing_-_Barking_Space_(720p,_h264,_youtube).ogg

Name: Frog (League Of Legends)
Summary: Frog is an mysterious creature in League Of Legends. It is seen jumping off cliffs all the time but still surviving and is possibly growing up to be the Gromp

Name: Garden Snail
Summary: The garden snail (Cornu aspersum) is a species of mollusk that is notorious for being one of the slowest land creatures on Earth. Their slowness makes garden snails a food source for many predators, such as small mammals, birds, lizards, frogs, centipedes, predatory insects, and predatory snails.

Name: Genista
Summary: Genista is the Franxx piloted by Code:556 (Kokoro) and originally Code:214 (Futoshi), but due to the partner swapping, Futoshi was replaced with Code:326 (Mitsuru). The Franxx is owned by Squad 13, and it is named after a genus of bushes.

Name: German Shepherd
Summary: The German Shepherd is a medium to large-sized German Breed of herding dog that was later used for police and military work. It is also commonly kept as a companion.

Name: Gharial
Summary: The Gharial (Gavialis gangeticus) is a species of crocodylomorph adapted to a predominantly piscivorous lifestyle. They are known for their long and thin jaws, with the males sporting a lump on the tip of their snouts which resembles an earthen pot called a "ghara" (hence the name "Gharial"). This lump forms following sexual maturity in males. They are among the largest crocodilians alive today, with females can reach 4.5 meters long, while males can reach 6 meters long; average adult mass is 160-180 kg, while males can reach a mass of 600 kg, and the largest found was 977 kg.

Name: Giant Anteater
Summary: The giant anteater is the largest of the four extant species of anteater. Unlike other anteaters and sloths, the giant anteater is a mostly terrestrial animal. The giant anteater is recognizable for its long snout, bushy tail, long foreclaws, and distinctive fur markings. The giant anteater's bold marking serves as warning coloration. The giant anteater has been featured in pre-Colombian myths and folklore and popular culture.

Name: Giant Barrel Sponge
Summary: The giant barrel sponge (Xestospongia muta) is a species of sea sponge native to coral reefs in and around the Caribbean. It is one of the largest species of sponge in the world, and plays an important role in the ecosystem as a home for various invertebrates and as a food source for parrotfish.

Name: Giant Brain Coral
Summary: The Giant Brain Coral is a species of hard coral native to reefs in and around the Gulf of Mexico and the Caribbean. It is a colonial organism, made up of large groups of polyps, which attach themselves to one another and harden. Giant brain coral can grow up to 6 feet in height, and can live up to 900 years in the wild.

Name: Giant Fire Beetle
Summary: The Giant Fire Beetle is an oversized beetle species. They get their name from their ability to emit a bright light, with it coming from glands on their body. This glands can be harvested and used as light sources for adventurers.

Name: Giant Golden-Crowned Flying Fox
Summary: The giant golden-crowned flying fox (Acerodon jubatus), also known as the golden-capped fruit bat, is a species of mega-bat native to the Philippines, which gets its name from the fur color around its head. They are known to be among the largest bats in the world, with a wingspan of 1.5-1.7 meters.[1] It is listed as an endangered species, with one of the major causes being hunting by humans for bushmeat, and habitat loss due to deforestation.[2]

Name: Giant Water Bug
Summary: Water bugs occur all over the world outside the polar regions, with about 2,000 species altogether. The Nepomorpha can be distinguished from related Heteroptera by their missing or vestigial ocelli. Also, as referred to by the obsolete name Cryptocerata, their antennae are reduced, with weak muscles, and usually carried tucked against the head.

Name: Gila Monster (Real World)
Summary: Gila Monsters (Heloderma suspectum) are carnivorous lizards found throughout the southwestern United States. They are among the three varieties of venomous lizards in the world, along with the Mexican Beaded Lizard (a close relative) and the Komodo Dragon; it is also the only venomous lizard native to the United States. Unlike venomous snakes that have venom glands behind their eyes, Gila Monsters generate and store venom in modified salivary glands.[1]

Name: Goat
Summary: Domesticated goats (Capra aegagrus hircus) are a subspecies of goat bred from the vulnerable Wild Goat. Goats vary greatly in weight based on breed, ranging from 20-27 kg for small goat does to over 140 kg for larger bucks such as Boer goats.

Name: Godzilla (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Godzilla is the name of the titular character of a Marvel comic series of the same name. The Marvel Godzilla was awakened by nuclear weapon testing in the Pacific Ocean and attacked Tokyo in 1956. Over the ensuing years, Godzilla became the lesser of two evils, fending off malevolent monsters that would attack Japan. By unknown means, he was eventually trapped in an iceberg and managed to break free once the iceberg reached Alaska in the 1970's.

Name: Golden Eagle
Summary: The Golden Eagle is a famous bird of prey native to most of the world. It has been trained by falconers and Steppe cultures for hundreds of years.

Name: Goldfish
Summary: The goldfish (Carassius auratus) is a domesticated version of carp, originally bred in China. It is one of the most commonly kept aquarium fish.

Name: Goliath Birdeater
Summary: The Goliath Birdeater, also called the Goliath bird-eating spider the translation from its original name Tarantula Goliath, These spiders can have a leg span of up to 28 cm (11 in), a body length of up to 11.9 cm (4.7 in) and can weigh up to 175 g (6.2 oz). Birdeaters are one of the few tarantula species that lack tibial spurs, located on the first pair of legs of most adult males.

Name: Goose (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Goose is a Flerken that was the former pet of Mar-Vell before her death. Years later, she finds and joins Carol Danvers and Nick Fury, who initially believe she's just a normal cat.

Name: Gorilla
Summary: The Gorilla is the largest genus of primate that currently roams the Earth, and is one of the closest living relatives to humans apart from chimps. Gorillas are found in Sub-Saharan Africa, and they can cover a wide range of elevations.

Name: Graviton (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Dr. Franklin Hall was a scientist working at a private physics research facility called Research City in the Canadian Rockies on a practical teleportation device. In the midst of an experiment, Hall attempted to align a set of matrices and induce teleportation, but only succeeded in overloading the power handling capacity of his equipment, causing an explosion that intermingled his molecules with the sub-nuclear graviton particles that were being generated in a nearby series of companion particle accelerators. Recovering from the accident, Hall discovered that he could mentally control gravity. At first he tried to hide his vast powers, believing he would be shunned as a freak of nature, but the urge to use them was too great to resist, and soon Hall used his abilities openly. To his pleasure, people began to fear him, and he started to take whatever and whomever he desired.

Name: Gray Wolf
Summary: The Gray wolf is an infamous carnivorous animal found all in the Americas and Eurasia. It is known to humans more than almost any other predatory animal, with more importance to human culture than most others. Although the fear of wolves is common in humans, wolf attacks are very rare.

Name: Great Barracuda
Summary: The great barracuda (Sphyraena barracuda) is a species of scrombid fish endemic to subtropical waters worldwide. It is renowned for its ferocity and intimidating appearance.

Name: Great Horned Owl
Summary: The great horned owl is a large owl that is endemic to the Americas. It is a highly adaptable owl, having been found in nearly every climate in the Americas hence their wide natural range. Its opportunistic diet is so great that one author wrote, "Almost any living creature that walks, crawls, flies, or swims, except the large mammals, is the great horned owl's legitimate prey."

Name: Greater Roadrunner
Summary: The greater roadrunner is a long-legged bird in the family, Cuculidae, from the Aridoamerica region in the Southwestern United States and Mexico.

Name: Green and Black Poison Dart Frog
Summary: The green and black poison dart frog (Dendrobates auratus) is a species of dart frog native to parts of Central and South America. It is notable for its bright coloration and the highly concentrated toxins it secretes through its skin.
ID: Green and Black Poison Dart Frog-TheRealWorld-10

Name: Green Anole
Summary: The green anole (Anolis carolinensis) is a species of small anole native to the southern United States. They are characterized by their small stature and distinctive coloration.

Name: Grey Side-Gilled Sea Slug
Summary: The grey side-gilled sea slug is a species of sea slug native to the coasts off of New Zealand. It is notable among sea slugs for its usage of the extremely lethal toxin tetrodotoxin as a defense mechanism.

Name: Grey Squirrel
Summary: Eastern Grey Squirrels, also known simply as Grey Squirrels, are a species of squirrels. Although they are known to be herbivorous, they ave eaten other food items such as insects, frogs, small rodents (including mice), small birds, bird eggs, and bird young. While grey squirrels are native to the Eastern US, they are seen as a major invasive species in Europe, especially in Britain where it is illegal to release a grey squirrel in the wild.

Name: Guanlong
Summary: Guanlong is a genus of small proceratosaurid theropod family that lived during the late Jurassic in China. Its name comes from the Chinese words 冠, which means "crown", and 龍, which means "dragon." Its most distinctive feature is the crest on its head, which due to its fragile nature, was most likely for display.[1] It is the earliest discovered tyrannosauroid, and distantly related to the much larger and more famous Tyrannosaurus rex, which would emerge 92 million years later.

Name: Guido Mista
Summary: Guido Mista is a major character in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part V: Vento Aureo. He joins the Neopolitian gang Passione after his vigilantism almost gets him sent for twenty years in prison, but is saved by Bruno Bucciarati. He becomes involved in the week-long mission of protecting Trish Una and eventually to assassinate the Boss of Passione himself.

Name: Gyarados
Summary: Gyarados is a Water/Flying Pokémon introduced in Generation I. It is the evolved form of Magikarp. Extremely vicious, enormously destructive, ferociously violent, and horribly brutal, it has a very aggressive nature. Although rarely seen in the wild, once it appears it goes on a rampage. When this happens, it doesn't calm until it has burned everything down and razed the fields and mountains around it. Not even harsh storms are able to stop its rage, and there are records of this Pokémon's rampages lasting a whole month. A single Gyarados has enough destructive power to totally annihilate even a major city. Gyarados is attracted to violence and tends to appear when there is a world conflict or war. When humans begin to fight, it will appear and burn everything to the ground with intensely hot flames. During past wars Gyarados would appear and leave blazing ruins in its wake, and in ancient literature there is a record of a Gyarados that razed a village when violence flared. When Magikarp evolves into Gyarados, its brain cells undergo a structural transformation. It is said that this transformation is to blame for this Pokémon's wildly violent nature.

Name: Haast's Eagle
Summary: The Haast's eagle was the largest eagle to have ever existed. It existed until a few hundred years ago when its primary prey source was hunted to death by humans.

Name: Habrobracon Hebetor
Summary: Habrobracon hebetor is a minute wasp of the family Braconidae that is an ectoparasitoid of several species of moth caterpillars. Well known hosts include the larval stage of the Indian mealmoth, the late larval stage of the Mediterranean flour moth and the almond moth, and the dried fruit moth This parasitoid has been used commercially as a way to control pests without using chemical insecticides.

Name: Hallows' Eve (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Elizabeth Tyne went through a lot of hardship, an abusive father, kidnapped and prison, but she found love with Benjamin Reilly a clone of Spider-Man. She went through a lot of effort to help him become who he should be, including going to the dimension called Limbo. Tired of feeling useless she accepted a power that was given by Madelyne Pryor, now going by the name Hallows' Eve she tries to do everything she can to keep the relationship with Ben alive.

Name: Hallucigenia
Summary: Hallucinogenia is a genus of panarthropod belonging to the group known as lobopods, which also includes modern water bears, velvet worms, and true arthropods. Its name comes from its "bizarre and dream-like appearance," with the various unusual and perplexing characteristics it had. When first discovered, it was thought to be an annelid, but was later identified as a lobopodian.[1] It has been found throughout Canada and China, along with fragments of spine elsewhere throughout Burgess shale-type deposits.[2] It lived during the middle Cambrian, leading a benthic lifestyle in deeper parts of the oceans.

Name: Harpy Eagle
Summary: The Harpy Eagle is among the largest of the extant eagles in the wild. It resides in canopies ranging from southern Mexico all the way into Brazil, Bolivia, and Paraguay. Destruction of its natural habitat caused it to vanish from many parts of its former range and nearly extirpated it from many parts of Central America.

Name: Heatwave (DC Comics)
Summary: Mick Rory or better known as Heatwave is one of the Flash's Rogues and is utterly obsessed with fire to such as extent that in his youth he let his parents burn to death.

Name: Heimerdinger
Summary: A brilliant yet eccentric yordle scientist, Professor Cecil B. Heimerdinger is lauded as one of the most innovative minds and esteemed inventors Piltover has ever seen. Relentless in his work to the point of neurotic obsession, he is fascinated by mysteries that have confounded his contemporaries for decades, and thrives on answering the universe’s most impenetrable questions. Though his theories often appear opaque and esoteric, Heimerdinger believes knowledge should be shared, and is devoted to teaching all who desire it.

Name: Helmut Zemo (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Colonel Helmut Zemo was a member of a death squad in Sokovian Armed Forces who lost his family to Ultron during the Battle of Sokovia. Zemo blamed the Avengers and sought revenge on them. He knew the Avengers could not be beaten through force, and instead attempted to manipulate them into destroying each other and took advantage of the friction between the Avengers during the signing of the Sokovia Accords by committing acts of terrorism and framing James Barnes, causing further conflict between Steve Rogers and Tony Stark. Zemo would eventually be caught by the Black Panther and imprisoned.

Name: Henneguya Salminicola
Summary: Henneguya Salminicola is a multi-cellular micro-organism discovered to be the first multi-cellular animal to not rely on oxygen for breathing. Given its lack of mitochondria, its method of producing energy is unknown. The samples used in the discovery of its lack of oxygen requirement were extracted from chinook salmon, although it is also found in coho, pink, sockeye, and chum salmon and rainbow trout.

Name: Herrerasaurus
Summary: Herrerasaurus is a dinosaur that lived during the Late Triassic period, approximately 231 to 228 million years ago.[1] It is considered one of the earliest known dinosaurs and belongs to the group called theropods, which includes famous dinosaurs like Tyrannosaurus rex and Velociraptor.[1] Herrerasaurus was first discovered in the Ischigualasto Formation of northwestern Argentina in the 1960s.[1] The name "Herrerasaurus" is derived from the name of the rancher Victorino Herrera, who owned the land where the fossils were found.[1]

Name: Hesperornis
Summary: Hesperornis is a genus of bird adapted to an aquatic lifestyle, the name of which means "western bird." It lived around 83.6–72 million years ago, during the late Cretaceous. Most of the identified species have been found in North America, notably in what was once covered by the Western Interior Seaway such as Kansas and Canada, while one species has been discovered near Russia. While mostly suited to a marine environment, many later species also inhabited freshwater environments. It is thought to have had lobed toes similar to loons and grebes, but may have also had webbed toes. It is thought its anatomical structure meant it would belly-slide similar to seals,[1] but may also have been able to stand upright similar to cormorants.[2]

Name: Hikari Yagami (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Hikari and Gatomon are main characters from the Digimon Adventure 2020. Hikari is the crest bearer of Light and her partner Digimon is Tailmon.

Name: Hinome Hawakata
Summary: Hinome is the secondary main protagonist of the Im: Great Priest Imhotep series. She's Imhotep's first friend after being set free from his punishment for 3,000 years. She's a rather unorthodox high school girl who had a dark past involving the Magai which ties into Imhotep's origins. However, she has a brave, kind, and fierce heart. Helping Imhotep in his endeavors despite being a mere human. Always being willing to stick by his side and cheering him on, making him better himself.

Name: Homo Erectus
Summary: Homo Erectus was an early species of human. It lived around the early Pleistocene and it seemed to be a migrant species. This hominid was remarkable in the fact that their species survived until just 50,000 years ago. This early hominid showed the ability of using fire (As torches, harden clay and cooking).

Name: Homo Floresiensis
Summary: Homo Floresiensis or commonly nicknamed the Hobbit was a human species that lived from 190,000 years ago to around 50,000 years ago on the islands of Indonesia. They are famous for being very small, smaller than the range for normal modern humans and even Chimpanzees. They display the affect that Island Dwarfism has on animals, including humans.

Name: Homo Habilis
Summary: Homo Habilis was a hominid presumed to be an intermediate animal crossing between the genus Australopithecus and Homo. It was given its name because it was believed to be the first homonid to use stone tools, having made basic carving implements used for removing meat from animals; however, it was discovered that Australopithecus were capable of using stone tools.

Name: Homunculus (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Homunculi are small contructs of magic users, created to act as assistants in their experiments. Indeed, such constructs are merely an extension of the master- it shares the thoughts and senses it has with its master, and the two are one being. They are telepathically bonded to their masters, and will never willingly leave them.

Name: Honey Badger
Summary: The Ratel or Honey Badger is an animal native to Africa and Asia known for its impressive durability and aggression.

Name: Horned Lizard
Summary: Horned lizards also known as horny toads or horntoads is a genus of North American lizards and the type genus of the family phrynosomatidae.

Name: House Centipede
Summary: House centipedes are small, typically yellowish-grey centipedes with up to 15 pairs of long legs. Originating in the Mediterranean region, the species has spread to other parts of the world, where it can live in human homes, thus gaining the name house centipede. It is an insectivore; it kills and eats other arthropods, such as insects and arachnids.

Name: Housefly
Summary: Houseflies (Musca domestica) are one of the most commonly known insects to date. Like their names suggest, houseflies typically reside in houses or warm environments. A nuisance to humans, they frequently like to disturb people during their daily lives, and eat human food that has been softened by the flies' saliva, deposit faeces, and regurgitate semi-digested food. On average, a housefly can weigh around 7 milligrams.

Name: Humboldt Squid
Summary: The Humboldt Squid (Dosidicus gigas) is a popularly fished species of squid in the waters of the eastern pacific.[1] It's the largest member of the flying squid family and abundant due to overfishing.[1][2] Despite being a well-studied animal, the IUCN has classified the conservation status of the squid as data deficient.[1]

Name: Humbug (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Disgruntled entomology professor Buck Mitty turned to a life of crime after quitting his job over budget cuts, using different tools and gadgets to his assistance, which put him frequently at odds with Spider-Man.

Name: Hummingbird
Summary: Hummingbirds are birds native to the Americas and comprise the biological family Trochilidae. With approximately 366 species and 113 genera, they occur from Alaska to Tierra del Fuego, but most species are found in Central and South America. As of 2024, 21 hummingbird species are listed as endangered or critically endangered, with numerous species declining in population.

Name: Humpback Anglerfish
Summary: The humpback anglerfish (Melanocetus johnsonii) is a deep-sea fish of the teleost order Lophiiformes. It is a bony fish named for its characteristic method of predation, in which a fleshy growth from the fish's head acts as a lure towards other fish.

Name: Huntsman Spider
Summary: Huntsman Spiders are eight-eyed spiders. The eyes appear in two largely forward-facing rows of four on the anterior aspect of the prosoma. Many species grow very large – in Laos, male giant huntsman spiders (Heteropoda maxima) attain a legspan of 25–30 centimetres. Persons unfamiliar with spider taxonomy commonly confuse large species with tarantulas, but huntsman spiders can generally be identified by their legs, which, rather than being jointed vertically relative to the body, are twisted in such a way that in some attitudes the legs extend forward in a crab-like fashion.

Name: Husky
Summary: The Siberian Husky is a breed of dog from, unsurprisingly, Siberia, bred for both working for humans and acting as a companion to them.

Name: Hyacinth Macaw
Summary: The Hyacinth Macaw (Anodorhynchus hyacinthinus), or hyacinthine macaw, is a parrot native to central and eastern South America. With a length (from the top of its head to the tip of its long pointed tail) of about one meter it is longer than any other species of parrot. It is the largest macaw and the largest flying parrot species.

Name: Hydra (The Real World)
Summary: Hydra is a genus of small underwater carnivorous hydrozoans. Hydras are notable for their regeneration (which is also the origin of their name), as well as the fact that they appear to be immortal.

Name: Hyneria
Summary: Hyneria is a genus of lobe finned fish, named after the village of Hyner in Pennsylvania where it was first discovered.[1] It lived in the Famennian part of the Devonion period, which was around 371.1 to 359.3 million years ago, and was an apex predator in freshwater environments it inhabited.

Name: Ichthyostega
Summary: Ichthyostega is a stem-tetrapod that appeared 365-360 million years ago during the late Devonian period. Like other stem-tetrapods such as Tiktaalik and Acanthostega, it served as a transitional link between fish and tetrapods, combining fish and tetrapod-like features.

Name: Iguana
Summary: Iguanas are herbivorous lizards native to Central and South America, although invasive populations have appeared in Southern Florida, Hawaii, and the Caribbean. Iguanas are one of the many reptiles domesticated as pets. Iguanas have gotten the name "gallina de palo" ("bamboo chicken" or "chicken of the trees") due to the chicken-like flavor of iguana meat.

Name: Ijin Yu
Summary: Ijin Yu is the main protagonist of the Mercenary Enrollment manhwa. When Ijin was nine, he and his parents were involved in a plane crash. Although Ijin survived, he was orphaned and was stranded from his remaining family. Eventually he was taken in by an group called The Numbers. Ijin underwent harsh training, and he worked as a mercenary for about eight years, serving in the harshest battlefields across the world. Later, during a rescue mission, he saved a RoK major named Kang Hamchan, his team and a doctor. Kang Hamchan traced Ijin's family and helped him retire. Ijin underwent a six-month orientation from Major Kang to help him adjust to civilian life. He's currently living with his grandfather and his sister in Seoul. Aside from attending Shinan high school, Ijin works as a part-time bodyguard at the SW group's security team, along with classmate Koh Sukjoo.

Name: Inland Taipan
Summary: The Inland taipan (Oxyuranus microlepidotus) is a species of highly venomous snake, and moreover, has the most toxic venom of any snake species alive today.[1] They are, however, not the deadliest snake in the world because of its fairly shy nature (in spite of its ironic nickname "Fierce snake") and the fact that people rarely encounter them.[1] They inhabit the semiarid environments of central and eastern Australia,[1] hunting small mammals. Generally they reach 1.8 meters in length, but can get to 2.5 meters long as well. When threatened or when hunting, the inland taipan is able to strike rapidly and accurately.[2] When defending itself, will curl into an S-shape to threaten a would be attacker, and strike if the threat does not heed this warning.[2]

Name: Invisible Woman (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Dr. Susan "Sue" Richards (née 'Storm) was a college student before she was exposed to high levels of cosmic radiation when boyfriend and scientist, Dr. Reed Richards, took her with her younger brother, Johnny Storm and pilot Ben Grimm, into space in the stolen rocket Marvel-1. The radiation mutated her and her friends, turning her invisible and allowing her to create forcefields. Together they became the Fantastic Four, a team of adventurers who explored space, time and alternate dimensions and saved the world along the way from science-based threats, with Sue going by the name the Invisible Woman.

Name: Iron Man (Marvel Comics)
Key: '''Human''' | '''Extremis Enhanced and RepulsorTech Node''' | '''With Iron Man Armors''' | '''Cosmic Iron Man'''
Summary: Iron Man, or Tony Stark, is the main hero of a comic by the same name. Stark: an inventive genius, industrialist, and multi-billionaire, went to Vietnam to oversee a field test for one of his transistorized weapons, that his company Stark Industries made.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 63
Summary: Considered as "Tony's Masterpiece", the Godbuster was created by Tony Stark within the virtual reality known as the eScape. Unbound by his own human restrains, Tony used the full extent of his imagination to craft the armor and destroy the motherboard.

Name: Ironclad Beetle
Summary: Ironclad Beetles are a subfamily of beetles. These beetles are apparently fungivores and associated with rotting wood, and as the common name implies, have one of the hardest of all arthropod exoskeletons; in some species, it is almost impossible to drive an insect pin through their bodies without using a small drill to make a hole first.

Name: Ironheart (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Riri Williams is an MIT student, and one of the smartest people on earth. She was hired by the CIA to find vibranium, but later got taken by the Wakandans to find the Tolokanil base. She has created a suit of armor for herself, granting her the name Ironheart.

Name: J. Jonah Jameson
Summary: J. Jonah Jameson is the bossy and irascible editor-in-chief of the Daily Bugle. His dislike of superhumans, most particularly the Spider-Man (which stems from a combination of envy, distrust, and his son's accomplishments being overshadowed) leads him to tirelessly defame and vilify him at every opportunity with his newspaper, to the point where he has sometimes worked with supervillains to try and take him down.

Name: Jack Carver
Summary: Jack, a former United States Army Special Forces soldier, has left his past behind and offers his services as a freelance boat charter in the South Pacific. He is employed by a reporter named Valerie Constantine to take her to a mysterious island, once occupied by the Japanese during the war, claiming to study its little-known World War II ruins. When Valerie goes ashore alone on a jetski, Jack anchors down shortly before his boat is destroyed by a missile launched by an army of mercenaries occupying the island.

Name: Jack Russell (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Jack Russell is a werewolf dubbed Werewolf by Night. Afflicted with a curse that causes him to transform during a full moon, Russell strove to help other monsters in need and hunt monsters that were a danger to others. In order to assist his friend, Ted Sallis, Russell attended a gathering of monster hunters competing for the Bloodstone. Russell worked with Elsa Bloodstone to free Sallis, but in doing so exposed himself as a monster. Verussa Bloodstone captured him and forced him to transform, inadvertently unleashing the werewolf by night on her own forces. Russell spared Elsa and fled, reuniting with Sallis.

Name: Jayce (Arcane)
Summary: Jayce Talis is a scientist and innovator, and, after years of success leading the city's scientific and consequently its economic progress, is currently the Head of the Council of Piltover.

Name: Jean Grey (Marvel Comics)
Key: '''Jean Grey''' | '''Phoenix Force''' | '''White Phoenix of the Crown'''
Summary: Jean Grey-Summers (born Jean Elaine Grey) is a fictional superhero appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics. The character has been known under the aliases Marvel Girl, Phoenix, and Dark Phoenix. Created by writer Stan Lee and artist Jack Kirby, the character first appeared in The X-Men #1 (September 1963).

Name: Jean-Luc Picard
Key: '''TV Picard''' | '''Movie Picard''' | '''Piloting auxiliary crafts''' | '''Assimilated into the Borg'''
Summary: Jean-Luc Picard, known to the Borg Collective by his designation of Locutus, was a celebrated Starfleet officer, archaeologist and diplomat who served during the latter two thirds of the 24th century. The highlights of his career were centered around assignments as commanding officer of the Federation starships: USS Stargazer, USS Enterprise-D, and the USS Enterprise-E. In these roles, Picard not only witnessed the major turning points of recent galactic history, but also played a key role in them, from making first contact as captain of the Federation's flagship with 27 alien species, including the Ferengi and the Borg.

Name: Jerusalem Cricket
Summary: Jerusalem crickets are a group of large, flightless insects of the genus Stenopelmatus. They are native to the western United States and parts of Mexico. Despite their common names, these insects are neither true crickets nor true bugs, nor are they native to Jerusalem. These nocturnal insects use their strong mandibles to feed primarily on dead organic matter but can also eat other insects.

Name: Jinx (Arcane)
Summary: Jinx, born as Powder, is a notorious Zaunite criminal and Vi's younger sister. When she was a little girl, her parents were killed in a failed uprising against Piltover, leading Vander, the upspoken leader of the undercity, to adopt both her and Vi as his own daughters. After a series of events forced Jinx and her sister apart in more ways than one, she was fundamentally and irrevocably changed, transforming her into the crazed killer she is today.

Name: Joe Kido (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Joe Kido and Gomamon are main characters from Digimon Adventure 2020. Joe is one of the 8 chosen children of the Digimon Adventure 2020 continuity and is the crest bearer of of Sincerity. Despite his pessimistic attitude and appearing as a coward, Joe is actually quite kind and very brave.

Name: John Constantine (Classic)
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Jumping Spider (Real World)
Summary: Jumping spiders have some of the best vision among arthropods and use it in courtship, hunting, and navigation. Although they normally move unobtrusively and fairly slowly, most species are capable of very agile jumps, notably when hunting, but sometimes in response to sudden threats or crossing long gaps. Both their book lungs and the tracheal system are well-developed, and they use both systems (bi-modal breathing). Jumping spiders are generally recognized by their eye pattern.

Name: Juramaia
Summary: Juramaia is a shrew-like mammal from the Jurassic period. Juramaia's discovery showed that placental mammals and marsupials diverged 160 million years ago: 35 million years earlier than previously thought. It has a body length of 7 to 10 cm, similar in size to the southern short-tailed shrew.

Name: Kangal Dog
Summary: The Kangal dog is a breed of guard dog originating from Kangal Province, Sivas, Turkey, used to defend both livestock herds and human families. Unlike many other domestic dogs, Kangals are rather antisocial and do not like being around too many people.

Name: Kikiki
Summary: Kikiki is a genus of fairyfly wasps containing a single species, Kikiki huna, known from Hawaii, Costa Rica, Nagarcoil and Trinidad. At 0.15 mm, it is the smallest flying insect known as of 2019. It is a close relative of wasps in the genus Tinkerbella.

Name: Kilgrave (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Kilgrave is the main villain of the Netflix series Jessica Jones. Real name being Kevin Thompson, he was a man who was experimented on by his parents since his childhood in order to treat a neurodegenerative disease, but the treatment ended up giving him the ability to control people's minds. Assuming the name Kilgrave, he began to use his powers for personal gain, eventually coming across Jessica Jones. He became obsessed and fascinated with Jones, even falling in love and hunting her down since she managed to overcome his thrall.

Name: Killer Bee
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: King Cobra (Real World)
Summary: The King Cobra is the longest venomous snake and is also one of the deadliest. King cobras have a typical length of 3.18 to 4 meters and a typical weight of 6 kg.

Name: Kiwi
Summary: The Kiwi is a small ground-dwelling bird endemic to New Zealand. Internationally recognized as the country's national animal, it lends its name to the country's rugby league team and is a colloquial demonym for New Zealanders. Despite its cultural significance, it is endangered, with fewer than 100,000 left out of its historical population of almost 12 million.

Name: Knight Anole
Summary: The knight anole (Anolis equestris) is the largest species of anole in the world, and can grow up to 20 inches long. While originally native to Cuba, it has since been introduced to southern Florida.

Name: Koala (Real World)
Summary: Koalas are arboreal marsupials native to Australia. Koalas are often mistakenly called koala bears despite being more closely related to wombats. Koalas are asocial animals, and bonding only occurs between mothers ad dependent joeys. Koalas have a body length of 60-85 cm and weigh from 4 to 15 kg (8.8 to 33.1 lbs).

Name: Kolibri Pistol
Summary: The Kolibri (German for "hummingbird") is the world's smallest and weakest production firearm, which fires the 2mm Kolibri (also known as the 2.7mm Kolibri Car Pistol or 2.7×9 mm Kolibri), the smallest commercially available centerfire cartridge. It was designed and sold by an Austrian watchmaker by the name of Franz Pfannl, who marketed them as "ladies' self-defense weapons". About a thousand of these tiny pistols were made between about 1910 and the beginning of World War I in 1914, when production had to stop as the economy turned to a war footing.

Name: Koushiro Izumi (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Koushiro Izumi and Tentomon are two of the main protagonists from Digimon Adventure 2020. Koushiro is the brains of the Chosen Children, constantly analyzing the world around him. However, his social skills are lacking due to his preference for computers over people.

Name: Kumimanu Fordycei
Summary: Kumimanu Fordycei is the largest and heaviest penguin to have ever lived, living in New Zealand during the eocene over 55 million years ago.[1]

Name: Kākāpō
Summary: The Kākāpō (Strigops habroptila) is a species of ground dwelling parrot native to New Zealand. It is the largest species of parrot by mass, and is the only flightless parrot, with their wings mostly used for balance and to aid in jumping between branches.[1] They are nocturnal, and feed on a wide variety of plant life in their environment. Due to human activities and the introduction of predatory mammals, especially following European settlement, the Kākāpō is critically endangered, with only 247 live specimens as of 2023. However, recovery programs have been showing progress in the last few decades.

Name: Labrador Retriever
Summary: The Labrador Retriever is according to the American Kernel Club, the most popular dog breed until the English Bulldog replaced it's top spot in 2022.[2][3] They have a friendly temperament and are regarded to be loyal, athletic and muscular gundog retrievers in adulthood.[2]

Name: Largemouth Bass
Summary: The largemouth bass (Micropterus salmoides) is a large species of freshwater fish native to North America. It is commonly caught recreationally by fishermen. Due to this, it has spread far outside its natural range due to fishermen introducing it elsewhere, such as Namibia and Japan.

Name: Leatherback Sea Turtle
Summary: The leatherback sea turtle (Dermochelys coriacea) is a critically endangered species of sea turtle native to oceans worldwide. They are the largest living turtle, the fastest living reptile, and the fourth largest living reptile, behind three crocodilian species.

Name: Leopard
Summary: The leopard is a big cat that lives in Africa, Asia, and the Caucasus. Unlike the other big cats that it lives with, the lion, and the cheetah, who rely on either using their strength to overpower animals and using their speed to chase animals respectively. The leopard relies on ambushing their prey from trees.

Name: Leopard Seal
Summary: Leopard seals are the third largest species of pinniped, behind the walrus and the elephant seal. Leopard seals are named after their spotted coat and are known to have eaten a wide range in prey, ranging from penguins to other seals. Leopard seals are 2.4-3.5 meters long and weigh around 200 to 600 kg.

Name: Lion's Mane Jellyfish
Summary: The Lion's Mane Jellyfish is one of the largest known species of jellyfish. Its range is confined to cold, boreal waters of the Arctic, northern Atlantic, and northern Pacific Oceans.

Name: Llama
Summary: Llamas are very social animals and live with other members of their species as a herd. The wool produced by a llama is very soft and lanolin-free. Llamas are intelligent and can learn simple tasks after a few repetitions. When using a pack, they can carry about 25 to 30% of their body weight for 8 to 13 km (5–8 miles).

Name: Loggerhead Sea Turtle
Summary: Loggerhead sea turtles are the largest hard-shelled turtle, exceeding the average and maximum sizes of the green sea turtle and the Galapagos tortoise. It is also the second largest turtle after the leatherback sea turtle. On average, they a weight range of 80 to 200 kg and a straight-line carapace length range of 70 to 95 cm. The largest recorded turtle had a weight of 545 kg and a total length of 213 cm.

Name: Luna Maximoff (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The daughter of Quicksilver and Crystal, she is named after the moon, having been born there. Luna is the first child to be born to a mutant and Inhuman, the genetic markers denoting these subgroups in humanity supposedly "canceled out" in her, leaving her a normal human.

Name: Lynx (Real World)
Summary: A lynx is any of the four existing species (the Canada lynx, Iberian lynx, Eurasian lynx, or bobcat) within the medium-sized wild cat genus Lynx. The lynx is usually solitary, although a small group of lynx may travel and hunt together occasionally. Mating takes place in the late winter and once a year the female gives birth to between one and four kittens.

Name: Lystrosaurus
Summary: Lystrosaurus is an extinct genus of therapsid, a group of ancient reptiles that includes some of the closest relatives to mammals. Lystrosaurus lived during the Permian and early Triassic periods, approximately 255 to 250 million years ago. It was a herbivorous animal with a beak-like snout and a robust body. Lystrosaurus is notable for its resilience and ability to survive the Permian-Triassic mass extinction event, which wiped out many other species. Its fossils have been found on various continents, and it is often considered an example of a "disaster taxon" that rebounded after a major extinction event, helping to repopulate the Earth with life.

Name: Machinesmith (Marvel Comics)
Summary: At the age of fourteen, Samuel Saxon discovered one of Doctor Doom's robots abandoned in a subway tunnel, and took it piece by piece to his father's garage, where for months he studied its components until mastering its operating principles and building his own robot from scratch. His obsession with robots grew as he amassed an army of droids at his service, that he used for his crimes, only to entangle with Daredevil, outsmarting him vastly in their first encounter.

Name: Mad Mod
Summary: Neil Richards, otherwise known by his alias Mad Mod, is a reoccurring enemy of the Teen Titans. A criminal mastermind, capable of creating powerful illusions through his technology. He seems to be obsessed with 1960's and 70's British culture.

Name: Madame Xanadu (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Madame Xanadu is an immortal sorceress with great skill in seeing the future. Thanks to this ability, she was the one to put together the team known as the Justice League Dark, to stop the Enchantress from destroying the world.

Name: Makarov Pistol
Summary: The Makarov pistol or PM (Russian: Пистолет Макарова, Pistolet Makarova, literally Makarov's Pistol) is a Russian semi-automatic pistol. Under the project leadership of Nikolay Fyodorovich Makarov, it became the Soviet Union's standard military and police side arm in 1951, and still sees widespread use in modern-day Russia.

Name: Mallard
Summary: The Mallard (Anas platyrhynchos) is a medium-sized dabbling duck that breeds throughout subtropical Americas, Eurasia, and North Africa. It's an omnivorous species and are flexible in it's choice of food as they eat things like bread, fish, small amphibians, and small bugs and insects. They typically live in areas which have bodies of water in it like marshes, wetlands, and even lakes or rivers.

Name: Man-Bat (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Studying methods to cure deafness by experimenting on bats, brilliant biologist Kirk Langstrom accidentally unveiled a formula that would go on to create one of Batman's most tragic foes, Man-Bat.

Name: Mandrill
Summary: The Mandrill (Mandrillus sphinx) is a primate and the world's largest monkeys. Mandrills mostly live in tropical rainforest and in very large groups and have an omnivorous diet consisting mostly of fruits and insects.

Name: Maned Wolf
Summary: The maned wolf (Chrysocyon brachyurus) is a large canine of South America. The maned wolf, known locally as Lobo Guará, is found in Argentina, Brazil, Bolivia, Peru, Paraguay and is almost extinct in Uruguay. Its markings resemble those of foxes, but it is neither a fox nor a wolf.[1]

Name: Mantidfly
Summary: Mantidflies are a family of small to moderate-sized insects in the order Neuroptera. There are many genera with around 400 species worldwide, especially in the tropics and subtropics. Only 5 species of Mantispa occur in Europe. They are not mantises or flies, but lacewings.

Name: Mantis Shrimp
Summary: Large marine crustaceans that are known to have the fastest "punch." They get the peacock part of their name from how colorful these animals are. They can range from sizes of 3 to 18 cm (1.2 to 7.1 inches) and weighs 12 to 90 grams.[1]

Name: Max (Sharkboy and Lavagirl)
Summary: Max is a fictional character who appears as the main protagonist of the movie The Adventures of Sharkboy and Lavagirl. He is a lonely boy who uses his dreams to escape reality. He records these dreams in his Dream Journal which was given to him by his grandfather. Max as the Daydreamer is the most powerful person on Planet Drool. Sharkboy and Lavagirl try to help Max remember this as he is the only one who can save Planet Drool.

Name: Mayfly
Summary: Mayflies are aquatic insects belonging to the order Ephemeroptera. This order is part of an ancient group of insects termed the Palaeoptera, which also contains dragonflies and damselflies. Over 3,000 species of mayfly are known worldwide, grouped into over 400 genera in 42 families.

Name: Mazothairos (Real World)
Summary: Mazothairos is an extinct genus of very large insect from the Carboniferous period. It was a member of the order Palaeodictyoptera. Although it is only known from very fragmentary remains it is estimated to have had a wingspan of about 22 inches, making it one of the largest-known insects, only being rivaled in size by the largest members of the order Meganisoptera, such as Meganeura.

Name: Mechanica
Summary: Mechanica is a playable fighter in ARMS. She was born without extendable ARMS, so she uses a powered suit to compete in the ARMS Grand Prix.

Name: Megalara Garuda
Summary: Megalara garuda, colloquially referred to as the "king of wasps, is a large wasp and the only species in the genus Megalara, family Crabronidae, tribe Larrini. It is only known from the Mekongga Mountains in the southeastern part of the Indonesian island of Sulawesi. It was described in 2012 by Lynn Kimsey, director of the Bohart Museum of Entomology and professor of entomology at the University of California, Davis, and Michael Ohl, curator and head of entomology at the Museum für Naturkunde, Berlin. Rosichon Ubaidillah from the Indonesian Institute of Sciences also contributed the discovery.

Name: Megalopraptus
Summary: Megalograptus is a genus of eurypterid, an extinct group of aquatic arthropods. Fossils of Megalograptus have been recovered in deposits of Katian (Late Ordovician) age in North America.

Name: Megamouth Shark
Summary: The megamouth shark (Megachasma pelagios) is a species of mackerel shark endemic to deep waters worldwide. Like the whale shark and the basking shark, it is a filter feeder, and harmless to humans.

Name: Meganeura (Real World)
Summary: Meganeura is a genus of extinct insects from the Late Carboniferous (approximately 300 million years ago), which resembled and are related to the present-day dragonflies and damselflies. With wingspans ranging from 65 cm (25.6 in) to over 70 cm (28 in), M. monyi is one of the largest-known flying insect species. Meganeura were predatory, with their diet mainly consisting of other insects. Meganeura belongs to the Meganeuridae, a family including other similarly giant dragonfly-like insects ranging from the Late Carboniferous to Middle Permian.

Name: Megarachne
Summary: Megarachne is an extinct genus of eurypterid, a group of organisms commonly called "sea scorpions," in the Mycteroptid family. Its name meaning "Great Spider" is now something of a misnomer because it was thought to be a large spider when first identified, and would have been the largest form of spider no less. Later studies, however, demonstrated it was in fact a eurypterid, based on multiple characteristsics such as a cuticular mucrone and a raised lunule.[1] As eurypterids go, it was no record breaker in terms of size, at 54 cm in length.

Name: Mesosaurus
Summary: Mesosaurus is a species of Parareptilian that lived around 299-271 million years ago during the early Permian period.[1] It's name from Greek and means "middle lizard." One of the earliest reptiles to return to a semi aquatic lifestyle, it likely was similar in behavior to modern marine iguanas. It dwelled in freshwater environments such as rivers, lakes and ponds,[1] along with some hypersaline environments,[2] with the pachyostosis helping it maintain Neutral Buoyancy, while the structure of its ribs likely helped it to dive.[1] Along with these adaptations, it is evidenced to give birth to live young.[3]

Name: Mexican Free-Tailed Bat
Summary: The Mexican Free-Tailed Bat, also known as the Brazilian Free-Tailed Bat, is possibly the fastest mammal known on Earth, with a ground speeds of over 160 km/h. This makes it faster than even cheetahs despite their immense size difference. Due to their small size (9 cm in length and 7-12 grams), Mexican free-tailed bats are insectivorous creatures, eating a variety of insects such as moths, dragonflies, wasps, flies, ants, beetles, and true bugs.

Name: Microbat
Summary: Microbats are a Suborder of bats that are significantly smaller than megabats, but possess more carnivorous traits, use echolocation, and are much faster. They can represent vampires, well-known creatures in pop-culture, due to Vampire Bats, who are known for sucking the blood of large mammals.

Name: Microraptor
Summary: Microraptor is a genus of small dromaeosaurid theropod dinosaur that lived in China during the early Cretaceous, 125-120 million years ago. It is famous for its four-wing structure, similar to a biplane, that may have allowed to glide or even fly, likely between the tops of trees. The pigment of its feathers were also able to be determined, with a study showing its feathers were glossy and of black color similar to some modern birds.[1]

Name: Millwall Brick
Summary: The Millwall brick (named after the football team) is an improvisational blunt stealth weapon made with several pages of paper, often from a newspaper, tightly rolled length-wise, and then folded in half to make a club.

Name: Mimi Tachikawa (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Mimi Tachikawa and her partner Palmon are members of the DigiDestined and thus major characters in Digimon Adventure 2020. Mimi is the Crest Bearer of Purity.

Name: Mission Sub-1
Summary: The Mission SUB-1 was designed to be the most accurate crossbow on the market. The name "SUB-1" means "under 1 inch".

Name: Molecule Man
Summary: Owen Reece was a weak, shy boy in Brooklyn, New York who obsessively clung to his mother.[1] He grew into a weak-willed adult, made bitter and lonely by his mother's death, and full of fear and hatred of what he regarded as a deeply unfriendly world. Reece became a lowly laboratory technician working at a nuclear plant owned by the Acme Atomics Corporation. He was disgruntled by his job's long hours and low pay. One day, Reece accidentally activated an experimental particle generator, which bombarded him with an unknown form of radiation. The explosion horribly disfigured his face with scars in the shape of lightning bolts, but it also had a mutagenic effect on Reece, releasing his potential for psionic powers on a cosmic scale. Reece could now control all matter, even down to the molecular level, and all energy, and he now used his immense powers to take out his pent-up frustrations on the world under the moniker of Molecule Man.

Name: Mongoose
Summary: Mongooses are small mammals popularized by Rudyard Kipling's "Rikki-Tikki-Tavi." They are known as a natural predator of venomous snakes, most famously cobras. Despite this, the mongoose is a small creature, with the 29 species ranging in weight from 320 grams to 5 kg.

Name: Mongrel Dog
Summary: The mongrel dog is called the pedigree dog, whose ancestry is generally unknown, which has characteristics of two or more types of breeds, or is descended from populations of wild or street dogs.

Name: Montana (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Jackson Brice was born in Bozeman, Montana. Along with Fancy Dan and the original Ox, he was a founding member of the Enforcers. He has great proficiency with the lariat. As a member of the Enforcers, he first came into conflict with Spider-Man when they were employed by the Big Man and have been fighting the wall-crawler ever since.

Name: Mosquito (Real World)
Summary: Mosquito refers to a large family comprised of 3,500 species of flies, notable for biting and sucking the blood of many animals. They are also renowned for being the deadliest animal in the world, due to the diseases it can spread (A few examples are: Zika Virus, West Nile Virus, Dengue fever, Yellow fever, Malaria, and Chikungunya).

Name: Mother Night (MAX)
Summary: Suzie Fisher was a former showgirl with the power to hypnotize people using a magic stone. Wanting to kill her philandering husband Max and get the money he earned gambling, she worked with Sean, a boxing manager, to set up Logan aka "L'il Rick", an amateur fighter Sean was promoting, to kill Max and his mistress. After a bout, Suzie seduced Logan and used her hypnotic power to force Logan to kill Max and his mistress. Logan eventually realized what happened and killed Suzie and Sean in revenge.

Name: Motormouth (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Young orphan Harley Davis was abandoned on the streets of London's East End, and rough-housed her way to the cusp of adulthood, at which point her foul-mouthed demeanor had earned her the nickname Motormouth.

Name: Mouse
Summary: Mice are an important prey species to many creatures, including large arthropods, birds, and small mammals. Mice are generally small creatures; house mice, for instance, have a body length of 7.5 to 10 cm and a weight of 40-45 grams. Beyond their importance in nature, mice are used for lab testing, primarily in the field of medical science where they are used to test various drugs and chemicals. Mice are currently the laboratory animal species most closely related to the humans for which the knockout technique (a technique involving altering genetic code) can easily be applied.

Name: Ms. Marvel (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Kamran: Look at everything I've done, Kamala. What am I supposed to do now? How can I be normal? Ms. Marvel: There is no normal. There's just us and what we do with what we've been given.

Name: Muskellunge
Summary: The muskellunge (Esox masquinongy) is a large species of freshwater fish native to North America, and is also a common sport fish. Unlike many other freshwater fish, the muskellunge has numerous rows of sharp teeth used for shredding apart their prey. It is an apex predator in its natural habitat, and only the presence of adult humans threaten it.

Name: Mute Swan
Summary: The mute swan is the second largest waterfowl after the Trumpeter Swan, although the mute swan can be heavier. The mute swan is native to much of Eurosiberia and rarely in the far north of Africa. Populations of these birds have been introduced to North America and Australia.

Name: Mysterio (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Quentin Beck is a former Stark Industries employee who sought out to replace the late Tony Stark as Earth's next defender. Seeking to solidify a reputation for himself, Beck feigned several Elemental attacks across the world with the use of his drones, seeking attention and recognition from the public as a new superhero/supervillain named Mysterio.

Name: Myxobolus shekel
Summary: Myxobolus shekel are the smallest animals and invertabrates ever found.[1] They're a part of the Myxozoans taxonomic group, which are parasites of aquatic, cold-blooded vertabrates and invertabrates. However, Myxozoans are most commonly found in wild and cultured freshwater bony fishes and marine fishes.[2]

Name: Naegleria Fowleri
Summary: Naegleria fowleri, also known as the Brain-Eating Amoeba, is a protozoan that causes a fulminant (sudden and severe) and fatal brain infection known as Naegleriasis.

Name: Neanderthal
Summary: The Neanderthals were an early species (or sub-species) of humans that lived during the Middle and Low Pleistocene in Europe and West-Asia until as recently as ~40,000 years ago.

Name: Ned Leeds (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Ned Leeds is the best friend of Peter Parker who, upon finding out his true identity as Spider-Man, decides to aid Peter in his crimefighting as his self-stylized "Guy in the Chair".

Name: Negative Man
Summary: The Negative Man (real name Larry Trainor) was an Air Force test pilot fused to an alien negative spirit and made radioactive, forcing him to wear lead-lined bandages, and influencing him to join the Doom Patrol. Chipper and optimistic, but easily frustrated, Larry's physical and emotional evolution was eased along by his teammates and friends over the years.

Name: NERDS (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Formed by the Wererat Mr. Honeycomb to solve Harmony city's energy crisis, the NERDS are a group of six adventurers whom each helped the Order of Zimandius to save the city, with them stopping Emo the Beholder from sapping all the color of the world.

Name: Neutrophil
Summary: Neutrophils are the most common form of Granulocyte in the human body, and are an integral part of the greater immune system. They form through hematopoiesis in human bone marrow, with Neutrophils being specially developed to target and attack foreign bacteria and fungi.

Name: Nine-Banded Armadillo
Summary: The nine-banded armadillo is a mid-sized animal found throughout North, Central, and South America, making it the most widespread species of armadillo. The nine-banded armadillo is a mostly nocturnal insectivore that can live in areas ranging from mature and secondary rainforests to grasslands and shrublands. This adaptability allows the nine-banded armadillo to expand into areas as far north as Nebraska, with the possibility of spreading into areas from North Carolina to Rhode Island in the future.

Name: No-Girl (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Martha Johansson was a young telepathic mutant who ran from home once she discovered her powers, only to be captured by the U-Man shortly after. John Sublime extracted her brain from her body, placed her inside a life support tank, and used drugs to force her to use her powers for his own misdeeds before she was rescued by the X-Men. Martha was then enrolled into the Xavier Institute and eventually trained as an X-Men under the alias No-Girl.

Name: Nokia Shiramine
Summary: Nokia "Akkino" Shiramine is a main protagonist in Digimon Story: Cyber Sleuth. She is one of Aiba and Arata's best friends. While she initially comes off as selfish, air-headed and even egotistical, she quickly proves herself to be a great tamer and effective leader who is genuinely passionate about the safety of Digimon and their rights.

Name: Noob Variants
Summary: Noob variants (Sometimes also called nooblet variants) are different variants of nooblet that the player runs into early in block tales. They tend to vary from ninjas like sharp nooblet to knights to even winged and cultist noobs. All nooblets, however, are characterized by resembling the Roblox noob in some way. These variants usually team up together against other enemies either with other variants or with the same type of variant; however, it is also possible for them to be alone.

Name: Nothosaurus
Summary: Nothosaurus is a genus of sauropterygian reptiles that lived around 240–210 million years ago, throughout the mid to late Triassic. Its name comes from the Greek words νόθος (nothos), which means "illegitimate," and σαῦρος (sauros), which means "lizard." It was widespread throughout the world, with 12 species having been found in North Africa, Europe, and China, inhabiting the ancient Tethys Ocean and its shores. These sea reptiles were likely related to plesiosaurs and pliosaurs that would later emerge, with Nothosaur-like reptiles thought to have given rise to them.

Name: Nuralagus
Summary: Nuralagus is a genus of extinct leporid, with the only known species being Nuralagus rex. It is notable for being the largest known lagomorph and an example of insular gigantism.[1] The creatures lived during the Pilocene on Menorca, an island in the Balaeric Islands archipelago in the Mediterranean Sea. It is thought its ancestors found their way to this island during the Messinian Salinity Crisis, which connected the island to mainland Europe, before the island was isolated once more by the Zanclean Flood. It is thought to have gone extinct when sea levels dropped around the Pliocene-Pleistocene boundary, connecting Menorca with the island of Mallorca and allowing other mammals to cross over, which outcompeted it.[2]

Name: Ocean Sunfish
Summary: The Ocean Sunfish, also known as the Mola mola, is a large species of fish that inhabits tropical and temperate waters worldwide. They are the largest bony fish in the world, and have a maximum recorded length and weight of 4.2 meters from fin to fin and 2300 kilograms, respectively. Ocean sunfish typically feed on small fish, jellyfish, and crustaceans, and can jump three meters out of the water in order to rid themselves of parasites.

Name: Ocellaris Clownfish
Summary: The Ocellaris clownfish (Amphiprion ocellaris) is a species of clownfish native to the Indo-Pacific. It forms a symbiotic relationship with sea anemones for protection in exchange for cleaning it.

Name: Ocelot
Summary: The ocelot (Leopardus pardalis) is a medium-sized spotted wild cat that is native to the southwestern United States, Mexico, Central and South America, and to the Caribbean islands of Trinidad and Margarita. It prefers areas close to water sources with dense vegetation cover and high prey availability.

Name: Olive Baboon
Summary: The Olive Baboon is a large omnivorous monkey found in Africa. It is considered a pest in many countries and hated for raiding houses and stealing food.

Name: Olm
Summary: Olms are an aquatic cave salamander with the appearance of an elongated axolotl. The olm is the only exclusively cave-dwelling chordate found in Europe. Olms are most notable for their adaptations to life in complete darkness.

Name: Opabinia
Summary: Opabinia regalis is an extinct, stem group arthropod found in the Middle Cambrian Burgess Shale Lagerstätte (505 million years ago) of British Columbia.

Name: Orangutan
Summary: The Orangutan is the only Great Ape besides humans native to Asia and the second largest. They are the third closest related animal to humans apart from Gorilla and Chimpanzee respectively.

Name: Ornitholestes
Summary: Ornitholestes is a genus of small theropod dinosaur from the late Jurassic, living on the supercontinent of Laurasia in modern day North America around 154 million years ago. Its name means "bird robber," with the second part of the name in honor of Adam Hermann, preparator for the American Museum of Natural History. Ornitholestes could reach around 2 meters long,[1] or longer at around 2.08 meters. More recent studies indicate it likely had feathers, much like other coelurosaurs, theropods more closely related to modern birds than carnosaurs like Allosaurus.

Name: Otter (Real World)
Summary: Otters are carnivorous mammals in the subfamily Lutrinae. The 13 extant otter species are all semiaquatic, aquatic or marine, with diets based on fish and invertebrates. Lutrinae is a branch of the Mustelidae family, which also includes weasels, badgers, honey badgers, martens, minks, polecats, and wolverines.

Name: Overdrive (Marvel Comics)
Summary: James Beverley was once a boy who dreamed to become a superhero like his hero Spider-Man. However, after failing to obtain superpowers in any way and proving himself to be inept at martial arts, he resigned himself to become a motorist like his father. However, after an accident left him seriously injured, he was approached by Mr. Negative, who sought his talents as a driver and promised to enhance his abilities through a swarm of nanobacteria that would allow him to transform any vehicle he came into contact with, as well as heal his injuries.

Name: Pacific Viperfish
Summary: The pacific viperfish (Chauliodus macouni) is a species of deep-sea fish in the family Stomiidae. This is the largest species of viperfish, reach around 1 foot long. They are known to inhabit mesopelagic and bathypelagic waters (the twilight and midnight zones), and carry out diel migration to shallower waters. They are known for their large fangs, which are long enough that their mouths are held partially open, and aid in catching prey.

Name: Paintball Marker
Summary: Paintball markers, also known as paintball guns, are recreational weapons used in the game of paintball, but they are also used in riot control and non-lethal suppression.

Name: Patriofelis
Summary: Patriofelis ("Father of cats") is a genus of large carnivorous placental mammal that lived in North America during the Early to Middle Eocene epoch, about 50.3–46.2 million years ago. Despite its superficial resemblance to big cats, it is not a feline, nor is it a carnivoran either; instead, it was an oxyaenid, a group of carnivorous mammals that were apex predators during the Eocene. Unlike carnivorans, it had stiffened vertebrae similar to armadillos or pangolins, thought to be a tradeoff of flexibility for larger size.[1] In life, they would have been terrestrial apex predators adapted for hunting on the forest floor.[2]

Name: Peregrine Falcon
Summary: The Peregrine Falcon is a species of falcon that is renowned for its hunting ability and characteristic diving maneuver.

Name: Peteinosaurus
Summary: Peteinosaurus is a genus of small pterosaur that lived around 218-215 million years ago, during the late Triassic. Its name comes from the Greek words peteinos, which means "winged," and sauros, which means "lizard." It is among the earliest pterosaurs and among the smallest.

Name: Petrolacosaurus
Summary: Petrolacosaurus is a genus of small diapsid reptile, belong to the group Araeoscelidia. Its name means "rock lake lizard."
