It was among the earliest diapsids, the group of which including all modern reptiles, along with dinosaurs, pterosaurs, and marine reptiles such as plesiosaurs and ichthyosaurs. The first fossil was found in Garnett, Kansas, and inhabited conifer-fern forests around 302 million years ago, during the late Carboniferous period.[1]

Name: Pig (Real World)
Summary: Domestic pigs are pigs raised for meat, leather, or simply as pets. Pigs that either escape or get released into the wild are known as feral pigs and regain their fur. These feral pigs are considered an invasive species and are often targeted by hunters.

Name: Pigeon
Summary: The pigeon is a part of the family Columbidae, being an omnivorus, bulky bird widespread in all places except Antarctica and the Sahara desert.[1] They typically nest at buildings or rocky cliffs and can be found in urban areas, farmlands, and the aforementioned rocky cliffs.[1] There are an estimated 400 million pigeons across the world and 250 species of pigeons.[1] Doves are smaller pigeons in layman's terms and they're scientifically similar as pigeons.[1]

Name: Pikaia
Summary: Pikaia is a genus of small invertebrate chordate, similar to modern lancelets. In the past it has been treated as the direct ancestor of vertebrates[1] or even the first fish,[2] but rather it was likely a stem chordate closely related to the line of chordates that would give rise to vertebrates.[3] It had a notochord and a body composed of segmets of muscle referred to as "myomeres," which is considered the major characteristics of chordates.[4] Its fossils have been found in the Burgess Shale in British Columbia, and it would have lived 513–505 million years ago, during the middle Cambrian.

Name: Pistol Shrimp
Summary: The pistol shrimp is a family of shrimps known for the effect of their snapping.

Name: Planarian
Summary: A Planarian is one of many flatworms of the class Turbellaria. It usually describes free-living flatworms of the order Tricladida, although this common name is also used for a wide number of free-living platyhelminthes. Planaria are common to many parts of the world, living in both saltwater and freshwater ponds and rivers. Some species are terrestrial and are found under logs, in or on the soil, and on plants in humid areas.

Name: Platypus
Summary: Platypuses are members of the echidna family known for possessing a tail resembling a beavers, a bill resembling a duck's, and webbed-feet resembling an otter's. When scientists first discovered them, they were believed to be a combination of multiple animals stitched together.

Name: Polaris (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Lorna Dane is the illegitimate daughter of the mutant terrorist Magneto, possessing power to manipulate magnetic fields similar to him. Having fought for peaceful coexistence for most of her life, she has been a seasoned member of the X-Men along with her longtime lover Havok, under the codename Polaris, although her impressive abilities lead her to being mind controlled many times to battle her teammates and loved ones.

Name: Porcupine
Summary: Porcupines are large rodents coated with sharp, pointed quills. Unlike the quills of a hedgehog, porpupine quills have microscopic barbs that make them difficult to remove. Their quills serve as a very effective defense against predators of varying sizes.

Name: Poro
Summary: Poros are the mysterious, magical and most-loved inhabitants originating from the Howling Abyss.

Name: Portuguese Man O' War
Summary: The Portuguese Man O' War is a marine hydrozoan found throughout the Earth's oceans. Unlike jellyfish, the Portuguese Man O' War is a colonial organism rather than a single organism; the Man O' War is composed of many polyps that work together in a symbiotic relationship.

Name: Praying Mantis
Summary: Mantises are an order of insects that contains over 2,400 species in about 430 genera in 30 families. The largest family is the Mantidae. Mantises are distributed worldwide in temperate and tropical habitats. They have triangular heads with bulging eyes supported on flexible necks. Their elongated bodies may or may not have wings, but all Mantodea have forelegs that are greatly enlarged and adapted for catching and gripping prey; their upright posture, while remaining stationary with forearms folded, has led to the common name praying mantis.

Name: Prokaryotic Cell
Summary: A Prokaryotic Cell is a small, single-celled organism, measuring anywhere from 0.1–5.0 µm in diameter. They are one of the simplest lifeforms on Earth, and can reproduce asexually through a process similar to mitosis. Unlike other cells, they lack a nucleus, but store the entirety of their DNA in an irregularly-shaped region known as the nucleoid. They can also move around by wiggling their flagellum.

Name: Protoceratops
Summary: Protoceratops was a herbivorous ceratopsian during the late cretaceous period and a smaller predecessor to Triceratops, albeit moderately large compared to humans.[1] Protoceratops unlike other ceratopsians didn't have eye horns or a large nose.[1] While smaller for a ceratopsian, they still weighed 180 kg (400 lb) and had a length of 1.8 m.[1] Protoceratops is a well-known dinosaur since its fossils are common.[2]

Name: Pteranodon
Summary: The pteranodon is a flying reptile that lived in the Cretaceous. They have a wingspan of 18 feet, some specimens have wingspans of 7 meters.

Name: Pug
Summary: The pug is a breed of dog which was originally bred in China for companionship. It is a friendly dog, and is great for families and children.

Name: Pulmonoscorpius
Summary: Pulmonoscorpius is a genus of large scorpion that lived in Scotland 336–326.4 million years ago, during the Mississippian subperiod in the early Carboniferous. Its name comes from the Latin word pulmonis, which means "lung," and the Greek word skorpios, which means "scorpion;"[1] a fitting name considering it possessed book lungs on its underside similar to modern scorpions, which indicated it was terrestrial. As it was not adapted to burrowing like later scorpions, it was likely a diurnal hunter with an active lifestyle.

Name: Puma Concolor
Summary: The cougar (Puma concolor), also commonly known as the puma, mountain lion, panther or catamount, is a large felid of the subfamily Felinae native to the Americas. Its range, from the Canadian Yukon to the southern Andes of South America, is the widest of any large wild terrestrial mammal in the Western Hemisphere. An adaptable, generalist species, the cougar is found in most American habitat types. It is the biggest cat in North America, and the second-heaviest cat in the New World after the jaguar. Secretive and largely solitary by nature, the cougar is properly considered both nocturnal and crepuscular, although daytime sightings do occur. The cougar is more closely related to smaller felines, including the domestic cat (subfamily Felinae), than to any species of subfamily Pantherinae, of which only the jaguar is native to the Americas.

Name: Purple (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: One of the many residents of the city of Harmony, Purple is an acolyte wizard that worships the God of Knowledge Oghma. They are one of several adventurers that ultimately solve the city's energy crisis.

Name: Purple Man
Summary: Yugoslav spy Zebediah Killgrave was on a mission to infiltrate an American military chemical refinery to steal an experimental new nerve gas when he was spotted by a guard who shot at him, but missed and hit a canister of the gas instead. The fumes sprayed all over Killgrave, turning his skin purple, and when he easily convinces the guards to let him go, he realizes he also gained the power to secrete pheromones that drain the will of his target until they follow his every command. Zebediah started using his powers to commit nefarious acts, working as a supervillain with the title of the Purple Man.

Name: Quipper (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A carnivorous fish, the Quipper is able to adapt to any aquatic environment. They often go in swarms which go berserk whenever they draw a victim's blood.

Name: Rabbit (Real World)
Summary: Rabbits are a common prey animal and, in places where they are introduced, one of the most infamous invasive species on Earth. Rabbits are herbivorous, although a source from 1910 has stated that rabbits have eaten snails. Rabbits were raised as pets, livestock animals, and laboratory animals. European rabbits, which are the most common rabbit, weigh from 1.2 to 2 kg.

Name: Raccoon
Summary: Raccoons are the largest member of the procyonid family, having a body length of 40 to 70 cm. Raccoons vary considerably in weight, ranging from 5 to 26 kg, although they typically weigh 5 to 12 kg. Raccoons are a notorious pest species due to the spread of rabies.

Name: Rainbow Trout
Summary: The rainbow trout (Oncorhynchus mykiss), also known as the steelhead, is a large species of freshwater fish native to North America. It is a popular game fish, and the fastest freshwater fish in the world.

Name: Rat (Real World)
Summary: A rat is a small rodent. They are characterized by being larger than mice and having powerful incisors that they use to break apart structures. They are also one of the few animals that has managed to adapt and survive in almost any climate (The only continent that they don't live in is Antarctica).

Name: Red Fox
Summary: Red Fox (Vulpes vulpes), also called common fox, is the largest of the true foxes. Being present across the entire Northern Hemisphere including most of North America, Europe and Asia, plus parts of North Africa. Apart from its large size, the red fox is distinguished from other fox species by its ability to adapt quickly to new environments and has the largest natural distribution of any land mammal except human beings.

Name: Red Kangaroo
Summary: The red kangaroo (Macropus rufus) is a species of marsupial native to Australia. It is the largest living marsupial, and the largest land-dwelling mammal in Australia. They are notable for their powerful jumps and kicks, which can deliver over 850 PSI of pressure.

Name: Red Panda
Summary: The red panda (Ailurus fulgens), also known as the lesser panda, is a small mammal native to the eastern Himalayas and southwestern China. The red panda's place on the evolutionary tree has been debated, but modern genetic evidence places it in close affinity with raccoons, weasels, and skunks. It is not closely related to the giant panda, which is a bear, though both possess elongated wrist bones or "false thumbs" used for grasping bamboo.

Name: Red Sea Urchin
Summary: The red sea urchin (Mesocentrotus franciscanus) is a species of sea urchin endemic to the northeastern Pacific Ocean.

Name: Red Triangle Slug
Summary: The Red Triangle Slug is a species of slug native to eastern Australia. It can easily be identified by the red triangle marking on its back, but comes in various colorations, including white, off-white, yellow, dark grey, light grey, beige, pink, red, and olive green. Research is ongoing as to whether these variations are actually different subspecies or just natural variation. It is Australia's largest land slug, growing up to 15 centimeters in length.

Name: Red-Bellied Piranha
Summary: The red-bellied piranha (Pygocentrus nattereri) is an infamous fish found in the Amazon River. While docile unless startled, piranhas have built up a reputation with their ability to devour anything that crosses their path, stripping off bits of flesh until their prey is nothing but bone.

Name: Regina Mills
Summary: Queen Regina, more commonly known as The Evil Queen and more recently, The Good Queen, is one of the main characters of Once Upon a Time, as well as the main fairytale antagonist. Filled with a deep hatred for Snow White ever since a tragic incident years ago, Regina makes it her life's mission to destroy the happy endings of the former and everyone else in the fairytale world. Her hatred for people led her to create the dark curse which sent all fairytale characters to a small town named Storybrooke. There she lives as Mayor Regina Mills, the stern adoptive mother of Henry Mills who sets out to stop his birth mother and Snow White's daughter, Emma Swan, from breaking her curse. Once the curse is broken, Regina finds herself in a vulnerable state and goes on a path of redemption to win back Henry's love. With this, she is eventually able to make the full transition from villain to hero.

Name: Rhamphorhynchus
Summary: Rhamphorhynchus is a genus of small or moderately sized pterosaur, possessing a long tail. Its name comes from the Greek words rhamphos, meaning "beak," and rhynchus. meaning "snout." It lived throughout portions of Europe 150.8–148.5 million years ago, during the Late Jurassic, including Germany, England, Spain, and Tanzania, and remains of teeth thought to belong to it have been found in Portugal.[1] Fossil evidence suggests its diet consisted of fish and cephalopods,[2] may have been capable of swimming like modern aquatic birds.

Name: Riddle School
Summary: Riddle School is a series of flash based puzzle-solving games created by Jonochrome. The games revolves around an elementary school student, Phil Eggtree, trying to escape his school. The player must overcome several obstacles and use super clever thinking in order to help Phil achieve his goal.

Name: Rika Furude
Key: '''Piece Rika''' | '''Higher Layer/World of Gods/Sea of Fragments Rika and Frederica'''
Summary: nan

Name: Ringed Caecilian
Summary: Ringed Caecilians (Siphonops annulatus) are a species in the Siphonopidae family of Caecilians, a group of legless amphibians. This species inhabits South America in areas east of the Andes, and is thought to have the widest range of any terrestrial caecilian species. They live underground, inhabiting a wide range of areas, including grasslands, shrublands, and forests; they have also been found in human-inhabited areas such as gardens and plantations.

Name: Rogue (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Anna Marie is a mutant who ran from home because of her aunt's controlling nature. As a runaway, already going by the name Rogue, she is found by Mystique who adopted her. She founds out in the worst way that she is a mutant by almost killing her first boyfriend, realizing that she couldn't have a normal life anymore she joins Brotherhood of Evil Mutants. On one of her missions she fights Ms. Marvel and by mistake permanently absorbs her powers almost killing her in the process. Didn't take long to realize that Carol Danvers memories were affecting her to the point of controlling her, so she asks Charles Xavier for help, after a long time of training and living her life as if she was cursed, she finally managed to control her powers and have a love life with Gambit.

Name: Romeo Conbolt
Summary: Romeo Conbolt is the only son of Fairy Tail's Mage, Macao Conbolt, and a Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild.

Name: Ruger 10/22
Summary: The Ruger 10/22 is a semi-automatic rimfire rifle. It was created and distributed in 1964 and is mostly used by small game hunters, for pest eradication, as well as plinking and target practice.

Name: Satanic Leaf-Tailed Gecko
Summary: The Satanic leaf-tailed gecko (Uroplatus phantasticus) is a small species of gecko endemic to the rainforests of Madagascar. Despite their ominous name, they are generally peaceful animals, and primarily eat small insects, such as moths and crickets. They are currently at risk due to deforestation of their natural habitat, as well as being poached for the pet trade.

Name: Scissors
Summary: Scissors are tools used for cutting objects. They rely on 2 blades with a wedge in the middle, and use at least 2 fingers to get through the handle of itself to use it. Designs and uses vary from cutting thin materials like cloth and paper to cutting through chicken bone. The word shears are used to describe tools of the same kind, but larger.[1]

Name: Scolar Visari
Summary: Scolar Visari was the founder of the Helghan Empire, the Autarch of Helghan, and the main antagonist of the Killzone series. He was vicious and violent, uniting the Helghan Nation through his charismatic and compelling leadership to become a major power on the interstellar stage.

Name: Sea Gull
Summary: Sea gulls are birds infamous for their presence in beaches and attacks on beachgoers and tourists. The notoriety primarily goes to birds such as the Western Gull (pictured to the right).

Name: Secretary Bird
Summary: Secretary birds are a large, mostly terrestrial bird of prey endemic to Africa. It is usually found in the sub-Saharan grasslands and savannah. The secretary bird is identifiable by its eagle-like body on crane-like legs. Unlike most birds of prey, secretary birds tend to stomp their prey with their long legs, slashing at them with their talons.

Name: Selene (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Born 17,000 years ago, prior to retcons Selene was noted as being the first mutant. She is a special kind of mutant known as an External. Living for many years, Selene has the power of psychic vampirism which she uses to empower herself and give herself a youthful body, effectively making her immortal so long as she feeds.

Name: Serval
Summary: The serval (Leptailurus serval) is a wild cat native to Africa. It is widespread in sub-Saharan countries, except rainforest regions. Across its range, it occurs in protected areas, and hunting it is either prohibited or regulated in range countries.

Name: Seven-Armed Sea Star
Summary: The Seven-Armed Sea Star is a predatory sea star. It is the fastest sea star, moving at a speed of 46 mm/s.

Name: Shiba Inu
Summary: The Shiba Inu is a small, Japanese dog, originally bred for hunting small game. They nearly went extinct during World War 2, but since then, they have become very popular as a pet. Shibas are also the number one companion dog in Japan.

Name: Shrunken Bones (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Jerry Morgan was a scientist who shrank his own skeleton due to an unforeseen side effect of the shrinking gas he invented. He joined a group known as Headmen in their attempts to seek world domination through science, and most often acted as assistant to Arthur Nagan

Name: Silverfish (Real World)
Summary: Silverfish are small, primitive, wingless insects in the order Zygentoma. Its common name derives from the animal's silvery light grey colour, combined with the fish-like appearance of its movements. The scientific name indicates that the silverfish's diet consists of carbohydrates such as sugar or starches.

Name: Simosuchus
Summary: Simosuchus is a genus of notosuchian crocodyliform with the single species S. clarki. It's name means is Greek for "pug nosed crocodile," referring to is blunt snout akin the beloved dog breed. It lived 70–66 million years ago, during the late Cretaceous, in present day Madagascar. Unlike many other crocodylomorphs, its characteristics, such as maple leaf shaped teeth, indicate it was herbivorous.

Name: Slyde (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Jalome Beacher was a talented chemical engineer working in the design and development laboratory of Beemont Manufacturing who created a chemical coating that, when applied to any object, eliminated all friction between that object and surfaces. Beacher was about to unveil his discovery when Beemont was purchased by a larger organization and a man named Rockwall was placed in charge. The research and development lab was closed and Beacher was fired. He decided to build his own company founded on the non-stick chemical, but discovered that no bank would lend the money needed without a sizeable down payment.

Name: Snow Leopard
Summary: The snow leopard (Panthera uncia), also known as the ounce[1], is a felid in the genus Panthera native to the mountain ranges of Central and South Asia. Unlike common leopards, the snow leopard's fur is whitish to grey with black spots on head and neck, with larger rosettes on the back, flanks and bushy tail. The snow leopard is also widely used in heraldry and as an emblem in Central Asia.

Name: Snowy Owl
Summary: The snowy owl (Bubo scandiacus) is a large, white owl of the typical owl family. Snowy owls are native to Arctic regions in North America and Eurasia. Most owls sleep during the day and hunt at night, but the snowy owl is active during the day, especially in the summertime.

Name: Sora Takenouchi (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Sora Takenouchi and Piyomon are main characters from Digimon Adventure 2020. Sora bears the crest of love, Piyomon is her partner Digimon. She is a "Chick" type Digimon who specializes in fire based attacks.

Name: Space Guppy
Summary: A fish like creature, the Space Guppy roams Wildspace and the Astral Sea. They have a unique ability where they can produce an air bubble around themselves, with it being able to sustain it and another tiny creature. This fact made so various races use it as a mount from time to time.

Name: Spiral Siphonophore
Summary: The spiral siphonophore is the longest animal in the world.

Name: Spotted Hyena
Summary: The spotted hyena (Crocuta crocuta), also known as the laughing hyena, is a carnivorous animal found in all of Sub-Saharan Africa. The species is, however, experiencing declines outside of protected areas due to habitat loss and poaching. The species may have originated in Asia, and once ranged throughout Europe for at least one million years until the end of the Late Pleistocene.

Name: Staghorn Coral
Summary: Staghorn coral (Acropora cervicornis) is a species of hard coral native to reefs across the western Atlantic, from as far north as Palm Beach down to the western coast of South America. It is one of the fastest growing coral species in the world. It is critically endangered due to catastrophic disease outbreaks and coral bleaching.

Name: Star-Nosed Mole
Summary: The star-nosed mole is a mole found in moist, low areas in the northern parts of North America. The star-nosed mole is named for its nose, which has 22 fingerlike appendages that allow it to feel out its environment thanks to sensory organs called "Eimer's organs."

Name: Stature (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Cassandra Eleanor "Cassie" Lang is the daughter of Scott Lang and Maggie Lang. Fascinated by the Quantum Realm, Lang invented the Quantum Satellite, which resulted in her, her father and the van Dyne family being shrunken deep into the Realm, being trapped in Axia. Wishing to aid the Freedom Fighters in spite of Ant-Man's denies, she donned the Stature suit to battle against Kang's Empire. However, Stature and Ant-Man were captured by M.O.D.O.K. and questioned by Kang the Conqueror, who used her life as leverage for Ant-Man to retrieve the Multiversal Engine Core. Once she escaped, Stature made a speech across Axia to motivate the oppressed citizens to revolve against Kang and his army before facing off M.O.D.O.K. and returning home with her family.

Name: Stentor Coeruleus
Summary: Stentor Coeruleus are peculiar protists, filter-feeding unicellular microorganisms part of the ciliate genus known as Stentor, sometimes referred as trumpet animalcules due to the stretched shape reminding of this object. They are particularly known for the massive size their single cells can grow to, often reaching the size of a rice grain.

Name: Stonefish
Summary: The Stonefish are a group of fish in the genus Synanceia, which includes six species. They get their name from their skin texture and color, which provides them camouflage and gives them a resemblance to a rock. These fish are found throughout the Pacific and Indian Oceans in coral reefs, though some species can also inhabit rivers. They are infamous for their potent neurotoxin, which they can inject into threats through spines on their dorsal fins. These creatures do not use their fins to catch prey, however, instead vacuuming their prey into their mouths.

Name: Striped Hyena
Summary: The striped hyena (Hyaena hyaena) is a species of hyena native to North and East Africa, the Middle East, the Caucasus, Central Asia and the Indian subcontinent. It is the only extant species in the genus Hyaena.

Name: Sun Bear
Summary: The Sun Bear is the smallest bear species in the world. They are rare and elusive animals found in the forests of Asia. Due to this fact, much is not known about the Sun Bear, at least in comparison to other bear species. They are known for their small size, long tongues, and their dog-like faces.

Name: Sunless
Summary: Sunless (or Sunny), is the main character of Shadow Slave. Growing up in the outskirts and leading a life of deceit and focusing on his own survival, he initially has a bleak outlook on life, even resigning himself to his fate when he was infected by the Nightmare Spell. But then, inside his First Nightmare, he resolved to himself that he must survive, no matter what.

Name: Swarm (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Fritz von Meyer is a former Nazi scientist who escaped the aftermath of World War II by fleeing to Argentina like many of his allies, where he spent his time researching the breeding patterns of local killer bees. In these studies, he discovered a breed of killer bees that knew no fear, were unusually passive, and highly intelligent, and created a device that he hoped would allow him to take control of them.

Name: Synagris Cornuta
Summary: Synagris Cornuta are large potter wasps. Several Synagris wasps are strongly sexually dimorphic and males bear notable morphological secondary sexual traits including metasomal lamellar or angular protruding structures and hornlike or tusklike mandibular and or clypeal projections.

Name: Taiki Kudo and Shoutmon (Manga)
Key: '''Shoutmon''' | '''Shoutmon X2''' | '''Shoutmon X3''' | '''Shoutmon X4''' | '''Shoutmon X5''' | '''OmegaShoutmon''' | '''Shoutmon DX''' | '''Shoutmon X6''' | '''Shoutmon X7''' | '''Shoutmon EX6''' | '''Shoutmon X7 Superior Mode'''
Summary: To make the whole world happy!!! That's the King that I am for!!!

Name: Takeru Takaishi (Adventure 2020)
Key: '''Takeru Takaishi''' | '''Patamon''' | '''Pegasusmon''' | '''Angemon''' | '''HolyAngemon''' / '''Holyangemon Priest Mode''' | '''Goddramon''' | '''Seraphimon and BlackSeraphimon''' | '''DanDevimon Shadow'''
Summary: Takeru and Patamon are main characters from Digimon Adventure 2020. Takeru is the crest bearer of Hope and the younger brother of Yamato Ishida.

Name: Tarantula-Hawk Wasp
Summary: The Tarantula Hawk Wasp is a spider wasp that preys on tarantulas. Tarantula hawks belong to any of the many species in the genera Pepsis and Hemipepsis. They are one of the largest parasitoid wasps, using their sting to paralyze their prey before dragging it to a brood nest as living food; a single egg is laid on the prey, hatching to a larva which eats the still-living prey.

Name: Taser
Summary: A Taser is an incapacitating weapon mainly used by the Police Force and Military forces for non-lethal arrests.

Name: Tasmanian Devil (Real World)
Summary: The Tasmanian Devil is the largest carnivorous marsupial after the extinction of the Thylacine aka Tasmanian tiger. Male Tasmanian Devils have a head and body length of 65.2 cm and weigh in at an average of 8 kg. Currently populations are endangered, with their populations slowly declining.

Name: Tenchi Masaki
Key: '''Base Form''' | '''With the Juraian armor and the Tenchi-ken''' | '''Awakened Power''' | '''New Timeline''' | '''Ascended self'''
Summary: Tenchi Masaki (柾木 天地, Masaki Tenchi) is the main protagonist of the Tenchi Muyo! series. Tenchi was a normal boy until he unsealed Ryoko Hakubi, and became the center of events surrounding the highest authority of the galaxy, Jurai. In the Ryo-Ohki continuity, he's actually the grandson of Yosho, the crown prince of Jurai as well as one of the only beings who's able to create Light Hawk Wings as a result of Tokimi's disruption of space-time in the hope of creating a being stronger than her and her sisters.

Name: Termite
Summary: Termites are eusocial insects that are classified at the taxonomic rank of infraorder Isoptera, or as epifamily Termitoidae within the cockroach order Blattodea. Like ants and some bees and wasps from the separate order Hymenoptera, termites divide labour among castes consisting of sterile male and female "workers" and "soldiers". All colonies have fertile males called "kings" and one or more fertile females called "queens".

Name: Textile Cone
Summary: The textile cone (Conus textile) is a species of cone snail, a group of venomous sea snails. Much like other cone snails, it is a predatory species that uses venom to hunt for prey. They inhabit waters along the Indian Ocean, notably of the East Coast of Africa and around Australia. Despite being prized by people for the vibrant colors on their shells, they are extremely dangerous, as they are among the most venomous animals on the planet.

Name: The Lizard (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Dr. Curtis Connors was a military surgeon turned herpetologist who lost his right arm during the war and sought to restore it by performing genetic research on the regenerative capabilities of reptiles. The serum that should have been the cure has instead turned him into the Lizard, a crazed but cunning monster who plans to return the planet to reptiles, which he believes being their righftul owners. Spider-Man always managed to foil his plans and reverse him back to a human, but every attempt at erasing the Lizard forever proved uneffective, and it remained a looming threat which could manifest anytime.

Name: The Protagonist (Digimon World: DS)
Summary: The Protagonist of Digimon World: DS is a young boy who stumbled upon the Digital World while investigating rumors he heard about "Digital Monsters". Later found by ClavisAngemon after observing the Digimon instruct a group of aspiring Tamers, the boy was allowed to become a full-fledged Tamer himself, proving to be exceptionally capable. After Unknown D began brainwashing his fellow Tamers to turn them against each other, the protagonist took it upon himself to stop Unknown D and later save the entire Digital World.

Name: Thiomargarita Namibiensis
Summary: Thiomargarita Namibiensis is a protobacteria native to the coast of Namibia. It is currently the largest bacteria species ever discovered.

Name: Thorvin Twinbeard
Summary: A gifted engineer, Thorvin Twinbeard is a dwarf who is working for Xanathar's Guild, making Xanathar a contraption which will pulverize those he petrifies.

Name: Three-Toed Sloth
Summary: Three-toed sloths are the slowest land mammals in the world. They are notoriously lethargic, only showing activity at brief moments of time. While they may move to different trees, sloths may spend 20% of their lives in a single, specific tree. Three-toed sloths have a combined head-and-body length of around 45 cm and weigh 3.5-4.5 kg.

Name: Thylacine
Summary: The Thylacine is a carnivorous marsupial that once lived throughout Australia, New Guinea, and Tasmania. It is nicknamed the Tasmania wolf due to its canine like features that arose from convergent evolution; the Tasmanian tiger nickname comes from its striped appearance. These creatures first emerged around 1.77 million to 780,000 years ago, during the early Pleistocene.[1] Around 3,200 years ago, the Thylacine population on mainland Australia would have died off, the major causes thought to be human activity and the introduction of dingoes.[2] Populations would remain prevalent on the island of Tasmania up until the early 20th century, before extermination by farmers and bounty hunters, along with habitat loss, competition from wild dogs, and disease would devastate them (with possibly already low genetic diversity worsening their chances of survival).[3] The last Thylacine was captured and kept in Hobart Zoo until he died on September 7, 1936.

Name: Tick
Summary: Ticks are arachnids, part of the superorder Parasitiformes. Along with mites, they constitute the subclass Acari. Ticks are external parasites, living by feeding on the blood of mammals, birds, and sometimes reptiles and amphibians. Ticks evolved by the Cretaceous period, the most common form of fossilisation being amber immersion. Ticks are widely distributed around the world, especially in warm, humid climates.

Name: Titan Beetle
Summary: The titan beetle is a Neotropical longhorn beetle, the sole species in the genus Titanus, and one of the largest known beetles. The titan beetle is one of the largest beetles, with the largest reliable measured specimen being 16.7 cm in length, comparable to such beetles as Xixuthrus heros and the Hercules beetle.

Name: Toxie Doxie (Marvel Comics)
Summary: You get to understand there are haves and have-nots in this world, you know? And that the have-nots don't really have the same right to life as the people who worked hard to be selected for greatness. And when the have-nots accidentally enter a position of power, where they can prevent Darwinian victors from exercising their talents... That's just wrong.

Name: Tree Weta
Summary: Tree wētā are commonly encountered in forests and suburban gardens throughout most of New Zealand. They most commonly live in holes in trees formed by beetle and moth larvae or where rot has set in after a twig has broken off. The hole, called a gallery, is maintained by the wētā and any growth of the bark surrounding the opening is chewed away. They readily occupy a preformed gallery in a piece of wood (a "wētā motel") and can be kept in a suburban garden as pets. A gallery might house a harem of up to 10 adult females and one male.

Name: Trejo Pistol
Summary: The Trejo pistol (pronounced tray-ho), and its sub-variant, the Trejo machine pistol, is a Mexican pistol or machine pistol. The machine pistol sub-variant has the distinction of being the smallest fully-automatic weapon ever produced.

Name: Truman Burbank
Summary: Christoff: Well say something god dammit, you are on television... you are live to the whole world. Truman: In case I don't see ya, Good Afternoon, Good Evening and Good Night.

Name: Tsunemori Akane
Summary: Akane Tsunemori is an Inspector of the MWPSB (Ministry of Welfare's Public Safety Bureau) in Division 1, and the main protagonist of Psycho-Pass.

Name: Tuatara
Summary: Tuataras (Sphenodon punctatus) are a species of reptile native to New Zealand. Their common name Tuatara comes from the Maori language and means "peaks on the back."[1] Although they resemble lizards, Tuataras are actually part of an order of reptiles called Rhynchocephalia, and moreover are the last surviving members of this once diverse group. Currently they are considered an At Risk Relict species in New Zeleand's Threat Classification System.[2] Tuataras were once widespread across New Zealand, but wild populations are now mostly limited to 32 islands off the coasts of the North Island and the Marlborough Sounds, with causes of their decline including poaching and the introduction of rats and other mammals to the islands.[3] However, extensive conservation efforts have helped to protect their populations, and there has been evidence that these efforts are proving fruitful.[4]

Name: Tullimonstrum
Summary: Tullimonstrum, colloquially known as the Tully monster or sometimes Tully's monster, is an extinct genus of soft-bodied bilaterian animal that lived in shallow tropical coastal waters of muddy estuaries during the Pennsylvanian geological period, about 300 million years ago.

Name: Turritopsis Dohrnii
Summary: Turritopsis Dohrnii, also known as the "immortal jellyfish," are jellyfish that are, as their nickname implies, biologically immortal. It achieves immortality by having the ability to revert itself into an immature polyp, de-aging itself in the process. Despite its inability to die of old age, it can still get killed by predators or disease.

Name: Ulysses Klaue (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Ulysses Klaue was a black-market arms dealer and smuggler as well as a gangster who had operated out of South Africa. He was a former acquaintance of Tony Stark from his weapons-dealing days, and was an associate of N'Jobu when he attempted to expose Wakanda to the rest of the world. In 2015, during an encounter with Ultron, Klaue sold his entire stockpile of the Vibranium to the A.I. before losing his arm in an argument with Ultron, and fled when the Avengers arrived.

Name: Ursa Major (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Mikhail Ursus' mutant powers of turning into a bear manifested at an early age when he was recruited into Russia's Super Soldier program. Rising to the top of his class, he donned the name Ursa Major and became Russia's longest-surviving superhero.

Name: Vaaiki
Summary: Vaaiki is a nano bioweapon made to kill people very slowly, one of Wanna's many weapons made for torture. It acts as a virus; when it is inserted into the victim's body, it immediately puts them into a comatose state and shreds apart their viscera itself, all prolonging until it either kills the victim or is removed from their body. It is impervious to any kind of antibiotics, so the Wonderful Ones had to shrink down to microscopic size and fight it inside Vorkken's body.

Name: Vapor (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Ann Darnell, along with her brother James, was among the small group led by Simon Utrecht to simulate the crash that gave the Fantastic Four their powers and has remained with the U-Foes ever since as Vapor.

Name: Variable Neon Slug
Summary: The variable neon slug (Nembrotha kubaryana) is a colorful species of sea slug native to the coasts in the west Indo-Pacific. The variable neon slug ingests a mild toxin from the sea squirts it eats, and is capable of using it defensively to ward off predators. The variable neon slug's striking coloration is due to aposematism, a natural phenomenon in which an animal has a vibrant coloration in order to warn predators that they are either toxic or distasteful to consume.

Name: Velociraptor (Real World)
Summary: Velociraptor is a genus of small theropods living in the Cretaceous Period. They are one of the most popular species of Dinosaurs, even though their appearance is vastly misunderstood.

Name: Velvet Ant
Summary: Velvet Ants are a species of wasp.

Name: Velvet Worm
Summary: Velvet Worms are members of the Onychophora phylum. They are soft-bodied invertebrates with surprisingly predatory properties. When hunting, they produce sticky strings that keep prey in place for consumption.

Name: Venus Flytrap
Summary: The Venus Flytrap is a carnivorous plant native to North and South Carolina. It obtains food through two leaves that resemble a mouth, bristling with sensitive hairs that cause the leaves to clamp shut when something bends them. The cilia, or the finger-like projects on the edges of the leaves, keep larger insects from escaping as it secretes digestive juices to break down the insect, a process which can take several days.

Name: Venus' Flower Basket
Summary: Venus' flower basket (Euplectella aspergillum) is a species of hexactinellid sea sponge, endemic to deep ocean waters off the coast of the Philippines and Japan. Sea sponges are as simple as animals can get. The nanostructures of the Venus' flower basket were claimed to be potentially useful for more efficient, low-cost solar cells.

Name: Vermin (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Edward Whelan was once a young scientist working under Baron Zemo. Upon questioning his plan to create mutated soldiers, Edward was taken and subjected the same experiments, which were meant to bring out the darkest parts of a one's inner self and change their appearance accordingly. Edward's childhood trauma of being abused by his father resurfaced, and the sense of guilt and shame he felt at the time gave birth to an entirely new personality, bearing the name of the most ugly and vile creature Edward thought to be like: Vermin.

Name: Virginia Opossum
Summary: The Virginia opossum is a species of opossum that resides in North America; in fact, it is the only native marsupial in North America. Opossums are famously known for their act of feigning death in order to deceive its opponents. This act led to the expression "playing possum."

Name: Volcana (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Marsha Rosenberg and her friend Mary MacPherran were given superpowers by Doctor Doom during the events of Secret Wars, and joined his team under the name of Volcana, where she met and fell in love with Molecule Man.

Name: Walther PPK
Summary: The Walther PPK pistol is a blowback-operated semi-automatic pistol made famous by the James Bond movies. Today, PPK pistols are manufactured by Carl Walther GmbH Sportwaffen in Germany or under license from Walther in France and the United States. These pistols feature an exposed hammer, a double-action trigger mechanism, a single-column magazine, and a fixed barrel which also acts as the guide rod for the gun's single recoil spring.

Name: Warrior Wasp
Summary: The Warrior Wasp is a genus of eusocial paper wasps found in the tropical forests of the Americas. Commonly known as drumming wasps, they are known for their aggressive behavior, a threat display consisting of multiple insects guarding a nest beating their wings in a synchronized fashion, and an extremely painful sting.

Name: Water Bear
Summary: The water bear is a micro-animal known for its immense resilience.

Name: Waterwraith
Summary: The Waterwraith is a mysterious water-based boss character in Nintendo's Pikmin 2.

Name: Werner Werman (Cuphead Show)
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:WernerWermanIntro.ogg

Name: West Indian Manatee
Summary: The West Indian manatee (Trichechus manatus), also known as the sea cow, is a large species of marine mammal native to the Caribbean and the east coast of the United States. It is herbivorous, and primarily grazes on seagrass.

Name: Whip (Real World)
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: White-Tailed Deer
Summary: White-tailed deer is the most widely-distributed wild ungulate in the Americas. Their native range ranges from Canada and the United States all the way down to Colombia, Venezuela, and even Ecuador.

Name: Wiccan (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Billy Maximoff was one of the twins that Wanda Maximoff had given birth to in the Westview Anomaly. It was discovered by Wanda that she created them using her own magic, and their lives were tethered to the hex. As S.W.O.R.D entered Westview to interrogate the Maximoff Family, he and his brother used their powers to handle the military. In the end, Wanda eventually had to give up her family, saying her goodbyes to them before she destroyed the hex.

Name: Wildcat
Summary: The wildcat is a species complex comprising two small wild cat species: the European wildcat and the African wildcat. The European wildcat (Felis silvestris) are natives of continental Europe, Scotland, Turkey and the Caucasus. It inhabits forests from the Iberian Peninsula, Italy, Central and Eastern Europe to the Caucasus. While the African wildcat (Felis lybica) is a small wildcat species native to Africa, West and Central Asia up to Rajasthan in India and Xinjiang in China. Unlike their descendants, wildcats are wild and can't be tamed.

Name: Wishiwashi
Summary: Wishiwashi is a Water Type Pokémon from Alola. Usually, it is a weak and delicious Pokémon. But if it is threatened, it will call upon its kin to form into its gigantic School form.

Name: Wolverine (Real World)
Summary: The Wolverine is a mustelid found in North America, some parts in the North of Europe and most of the north of Russia.

Name: Xenobot
Summary: Xenobots, named after the African clawed frog (Xenopus laevis), are self-healing microbots that are designed and programmed by a computer and built from the ground up using biological cells. A xenobot is a biological machine under 1 millimeter wide and small enough to travel inside human bodies. They are made of skin cells and heart cells, stem cells harvested from frog embryos.

Name: Xerces Blue Butterfly
Summary: The Xerces blue butterfly was a species of butterfly endemic to the sand dunes of California. Due to a loss in habitat and subsequent extirpation of its main food sources, lotus flowers and lupin, the Xerces blue became extinct in the early 1940s. It has since become the most famous example of an invertebrate becoming extinct due to human activity.

Name: Yacare Caiman
Summary: The yacare caiman (Caiman yacare), also known commonly as the piranha caiman, red caiman and southern spectacled caiman is a species of caiman, a crocodilian in the family Alligatoridae. The species is endemic to Argentina, Bolivia, Brazil, and Paraguay. It is sometimes considered a subspecies of the spectacled caiman (Caiman crocodilus), which would make its scientific name Caiman crocodilus yacare. These two species are the same morphologically, but are considered separate species due to their geographical differences.

Name: Yamato Ishida (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Yamato Ishida and Gabumon are main characters in the Digimon Adventure 2020. Yamato is the crest bearer of friendship and the older brother of Takeru Takaishi.

Name: Yellowjacket (Real World)
Summary: Yellowjacket is the common name in North America for predatory social wasps of the genera Vespula and Dolichovespula. Members of these genera are known simply as "wasps" in other English-speaking countries.

Name: Akane Yashiro (Kiryu Saga)
Key: '''Akane Yashiro''' | '''Piloting Maser Cannon''' | '''Piloting AC-3 White Heron''' | '''Piloting Kiryu'''
Summary: Akane Yashiro (家城茜) is the human protagonist of the 2002 Toho Godzilla film Godzilla Against Mechagodzilla, also appearing in a minor role in its 2003 sequel Godzilla: Tokyo SOS. First Lieutenant Akane Yashiro A Type 90 Maser Cannon operator for the JSDF's Anti-Megalosaurus Force, Akane unintentionally caused the death of her comrades in a battle against Godzilla in 1999. Subsequently reassigned to a desk job, Akane was recruited to become a pilot for the Kiryu Squad in 2003, receiving the rank of Second Lieutenant. A member of the Kiryu team and the pilot of Kiryu Type-3. She is an excellent operator, but as the only member without relatives, she can be a bit awkward due to not being good at reading the feelings of others. Despite the odds against her, Akane earned the respect of her squad and played a key role in the battle between Kiryu and Godzilla in Tokyo. By 2004, she had been promoted to First Lieutenant and sought further training in the United States.

Name: Akira Yuki (Godzilla)
Summary: Major Akira Yuki (結城 晃) is a G-Force soldier and the main human protagonist in the 1994 Godzilla film Godzilla vs. SpaceGodzilla. He is committed to getting revenge on Godzilla for causing the death of his best friend, Colonel Goro Gondo, during the events of the film Godzilla vs Biollante.

Name: Apollo Justice
Summary: Apollo Justice is a defense attorney who has operated in the United States and Khura'in. He started off working for Gavin Law Offices, but after his first trial, he was taken under the wing of Phoenix Wright at the Wright Anything Agency. Along with co-counsel Trucy Wright, prosecutor Klavier Gavin, and mentor Phoenix, Justice participated in a test trial for the Jurist System in 2026, which was an effort to reintegrate the jury into court proceedings.

Name: Athena Cykes
Summary: Athena Cykes is one of three defense attorneys in the Wright Anything Agency, working in this capacity alongside Phoenix Wright and Apollo Justice. She is a specialist in analytical psychology, which she studied in Europe. Cykes has a special ability to pick up subtle emotions from witnesses' voices, and she examines these using a program called the "Mood Matrix". The Mood Matrix is linked to her AI partner Widget, who hangs around her neck, that changes color with her emotions.

Name: Bat Men (Godzilla)
Summary: The Bat Men (人間コウモリ) are humanoid bat kaijin that first appeared in the 1969 Toho film, Latitude Zero.

Name: Baymax (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Baymax is a resident native to the San Fransokyo "world". After being left in another dimension, Riku Replica took him out to experiment the nature of a heart by filling his heart with darkness and negative emotions, and making him face those he once beloved.

Name: Baymax 2.0 (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Baymax is a resident native to the San Fransokyo "world". He's a member of Big Hero 6, and the replacement of the original Baymax.

Name: Bullseye (Toy Story)
Summary: Bullseye is Woody's horse and one of the characters introduced in Toy Story 2. Although he is a horse, the way he acts can be similar to that of a puppy. He is extremely affectionate towards Woody, Jessie and the other toys. He doesn't have a speaking voice; instead, he neighs and makes other horse noises. Yet he understands human speech.

Name: Carlito Keyes
Summary: Tier: 10-A, 7-C with preparation

Name: Convicts
Summary: The Convicts, consisting of Sam Franklin, Reginald Jenkins, and Miguel Sanchez, are psychopaths in Dead Rising who are involved in the mission Prisoners.

Name: Craig McKenzie
Summary: Craig McKenzie (クレイグ・マッケンジー) is the captain of the Alpha in the 1969 Toho film, Latitude Zero.

Name: Devo the Cursed
Origin: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure '''(Part III: Stardust Crusaders)'''
Summary: Devo the Cursed is a minor antagonist in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part III: Stardust Crusaders. He is given a Stand and hired by Dio Brando to kill the Joestars and allies. He appears in Singapore in an attempt to ambush Polnareff in a hotel room.

Name: Diamond Dogs
Summary: The Diamond Dogs were a PMC (Private Military Contractor) formed by Kazuhira Miller in the early 1980s, and commanded from 1984 onwards by Venom Snake, after recovering from his coma. Under his command, it would become an extremely powerful and highly influential player in the worldwide military-industrial complex, taking on jobs for all clients. The organization would end up at odds with XOF, the covert strike force of the shadow government known as The Patriots, due to the feud between Big Boss/Venom Snake and XOF's leader, Skull Face. Ultimately, Diamond Dogs would emerge victorious, with Venom Snake and Kazuhira Miller dealing the finishing blows to Skull Face and scattering XOF. The PMC would remain in operation for roughly a decade more, before being supplanted and its strength absorbed by Big Boss' military fortress nation, Outer Heaven.

Name: Emperor Antonio
Summary: Emperor Antonio (シートピア司令アントニオ Shītopia Shirei Antonio, lit. Seatopia Commander Antonio) is the ruler of Seatopia who first appeared in the 1973 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs. Megalon.

Name: Forever
Origin: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure '''(Part III: Stardust Crusaders)'''
Summary: Forever (フォーエバー Fōebā) is a minor antagonist appearing in Stardust Crusaders. He is a malicious orangutan in DIO's service who confronts the group in the South China Sea aboard a freighter. Said ship happens to be possessed by Forever's Stand Strength.

Name: Franziska von Karma
Summary: Franziska is the daughter of the legendary Prosecutor Manfred von Karma, from whom she adopted tactics and her obsession with perfection. She usually carries a whip, or a riding crop when she was younger, and she will not hesitate to use it against anyone who tries to bother her.

Name: Freddy & Friends
Summary: (Ragged moaning from animatronics can be heard) Oh no..." (Sound used by Golden Freddy during his jumpscare plays, call ends)

Name: Goro Gondo
Summary: Goro Gondo (権藤 吾郎) is a colonel in the JSDF and one of the leaders of the Defend Against Godzilla unit, along with his partner Sho Kuroki. He is a supporting character in the 1989 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs. Biollante, and is later referenced in the 1994 film, Godzilla vs. SpaceGodzilla.

Name: Hans Moleman
Summary: Hans Moleman is a recurring character in The Simpsons. He has a running gag of him being killed in various accidents, similar to Kenny McCormick.

Name: Hol Horse
Origin: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure '''(Part III: Stardust Crusaders)'''
Summary: Hol Horse is a minor antagonist in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part III: Stardust Crusaders. He is an assassin who was hired by DIO to kill the Joestars and allies. He works with his partner, J. Geil, to maximize both his and his partner's Stand abilities.

Name: Illinois (AHWM)
Summary: Illinois is an adventurer and avid treasure hunter. Shortly before meeting the Player, he lost his assistant at the time to a boulder.

Name: Kilaak Queen
Summary: The Kilaak Queen (キラアク星人首領) is the leader of the Kilaaks and the main antagonist in the 1968 Godzilla film Destroy All Monsters.

Name: Kiyoshi Sato
Summary: Kiyoshi Sato (佐藤清志) is a G-Force lieutenant and a supporting character in the 1994 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs. SpaceGodzilla.

Name: Koji Shinjo
Summary: Koji Shinjo (新城功二) is one of the main human protagonists in the 1994 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs. SpaceGodzilla. He is a lieutenant in G-Force and a co-pilot of MOGUERA.

Name: Lucas (Knack)
Summary: Lucas is the level-headed friend of Knack and long time lab assistant of Doctor Vargas.

Name: Maya Fey
Summary: Maya Fey was the younger sibling of Mia Fey. She spent a large amount of her life growing up at Kurain Village, a place where the Fey family and spirit mediums stood. After Maya left in her later years, her sister Mia was murdered and her being pinned as the killer. This is where she met Phoenix Wright, who came to her defense and proved her innocence while proving the real killer guilty. After this, Maya stuck around with Phoenix and helped him on his cases for years to come, until after the DL-6 case, she felt useless to helping Wright because of her inexperience with channeling spirits. So she took a train and headed back to her village to train further and better her skills. Months later, however, in the village, a murder occurred during a spirit summoning gone wrong. Mia was once again pinned as the killer, but again defended by Phoenix who found the true culprit. After this, she went back to helping him with future cases.

Name: Mia Fey
Summary: Mia Fey was the older sister of Maya Fey and her daughter is Misty Fey. They were part of a group of spirit channelers living in Kurain Village. However, her mother soon turned up missing, having left the village after a spirit channeling for a murder went public and brought embarrassment to their family name. Determined to find out what had happened, Mia left the village to become a lawyer, nearly quitting after her client killed themself in her first case. But when she entered into her second one, she brought justice to the one responsible, and inspired Phoenix Wright, her client she had defended for this case, into becoming a lawyer. She mentored Phoenix when he got his badge, teaching him what he knows about the courthouse. However, after having some powerful evidence against an evil person that would get them in huge trouble, she was killed. Although she has died, her spirit still lives on, and on occasion, comes to give Phoenix some helpful words or insight to help him out.

Name: Miko Nakadai
Summary: Miko Nakadai is a teenage girl from Japan with a strong love of punk and metal. She's always searching for thrills and causing trouble. As the human partner to the Autobot Bulkhead, she's helped him get over his fear of his own strength by encouraging him to get in trouble with her. Her recklessness is actually a cover for her insecurity, leaping into danger to prove herself. Her fierce loyalty and sheer gall wound up impressing Wheeljack and even Ultra Magnus enough to let her join the Wreckers.

Name: Minireenas (Five Nights At Freddy's)
Summary: The Minireenas are small, mannequin-esque ballerina animatronics meant to accompany Ballora, who, alongside the other animatronics from Afton Robotics, were found by Michael Afton after he entered the retail bunker containing them as per his father's orders.[2] Mistaking Mike for his father, William Afton, who was also the man who created them as experiments with Remnant, the Funtime animatronics all fused into Ennard and scooped out and inhabited Mike's innards, succeeding in escaping from the facility that they were trapped in.[3]

Name: Nahyuta Sahdmadhi
Summary: Nahyuta Sahdmadhi is a renowned prosecutor from the Kingdom of Khura’in. He considers trials to be the last rites of the victim, in which their souls go to the “Twilight Realm” after the true culprit is considered guilty.

Name: Riza Hawkeye
Summary: Lieutenant Riza Hawkeye (リザ・ホークアイ, Riza Hōkuai) is an officer in the Amestrian State Military as well as the personal adjutant and bodyguard of Colonel Roy Mustang. A sharpshooter and firearms specialist, Lt. Hawkeye is an invaluable asset to the Colonel both in office and on the battlefield and serves as his closest and most supportive subordinate.

Name: Ryoichi Shiraishi
Summary: Ryoichi Shiraishi (白石亮一) is an astrophysicist and one of the main characters in the 1957 Toho film, The Mysterians.

Name: Sam Flynn
Summary: Sam Flynn: Your boss works for the CEO, and the CEO works for the shareholders. Now, do you know who the biggest shareholder is? Security Guard: I don't know some kid?... You're Mr. Flynn? Why? This is your fathers company! Sam Flynn: Not anymore.

Name: Sora (Kingdom Hearts The Sceptre and the Kingdom)
Summary: Sora is the main protagonist of The Sceptre and the Kingdom. Sora is tasked alongside Riku to obtain the stolen Fairy Spectre from the Mysterious Creature by looking for him across multiple worlds.
ID: Sora (Kingdom Hearts The Sceptre and the Kingdom)-KingdomHearts-10-A

Name: The Rainman
Summary: Jason Baker, known under the alias Caleb, otherwise known as the Rainman is the titular main antagonist of the 2023 indie-horror game, The Rainman.

Name: Uta (One Piece)
Summary: Uta is a world-famous singer, or "diva" and the adopted daughter of Shanks and acted as the musician of his crew before he abandoned her on the island of Elegia with her foster father, Gordon who supported her dream of starting a "New Era" and later her desire to achieve this dream through a broadcasted, world-wide concert held on Elegia.

Name: Vanny
Summary: Vanessa, also known under the alias of Vanny, is the protagonist of Five Nights At Freddy's: Help Wanted and a main antagonist of Five Nights At Freddy's: Security Breach. She worked as a beta tester for Fazbear Entertainment before seemingly getting possessed by Glitchtrap and gaining a split personality. She later began to work at Freddy Fazbear's Mega Pizzaplex as a security guard, where she is behind the disappearances of multiple children and adults, as well as some of the strange events that take place there.

Name: William Afton (Games)
Key: '''William Afton''' | '''Post-Springlock Failure''' | '''Post-Fazbear Frights Fire''' | '''Ultimate Custom Night'''
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:WilliamAftonDeception.ogg

Name: Barry Kahn
Summary: Barry Kahn is an A-list actor from Dragon Ball set to play the Great Saiyaman in the film "Great Saiyaman vs Mister Satan." After Barry was rejected by Videl, he became increasingly jealous of Gohan and attempted to ruin his marriage, though without any success.

Name: Bishamon
Summary: Bishamon is a playable character in the Darkstalkers series and covers the role of the accursed samurai.

Name: Bulma
Summary: Bulma (ブルマ, Buruma; lit. "Bloomers") is a brilliant scientist and the second daughter of Capsule Corporation's founder Dr. Brief and his wife Mrs. Brief. At the age of 16, she found the two-star Dragon Ball in her basement. She created the Dragon Radar to find the other Dragon Balls so she can wish for a lifetime supply of strawberries, but later decides she wants to wish for the perfect boyfriend instead. As she was heading to Mount Paozu to find the next Dragon Ball when she accidentally hit a young boy named Son Goku with her car. Bulma was the first girl Goku had ever seen and even more so, the second human Goku had ever seen, after his guardian, Grandpa Gohan, who had died. After Goku took Bulma to his house, she finds out that he has the four-star Dragon Ball, and explains the legend and power behind them. After failing to seduce Goku for it, she decides to become traveling partners with him to which he agrees, thus beginning their journey as well as the Dragon Ball saga as a whole.

Name: Cletus Samson
Summary: Cletus Smason is a psychopath appearing in Dead Rising.

Name: Don Kanonji
Summary: Don Kanonji (ドン・観音寺, Don Kanonji), real name Misaomaru Kanonji (観音寺 ミサオ丸, Kanonji Misaomaru) is the host of the Television show Casual Soul Realm Assault Trip, commonly shortened to Cazh Soul.

Name: Excella Gionne
Summary: Excella Gionne was the regional director of TRICELL's African division and a business partner of Albert Wesker.

Name: Fenton Crackshell
Summary: Fenton Crackshell is a Disney character and a protagonist that appears in the 1987 Disney cartoon Ducktales, later to be featured in Darkwing Duck as his superhero alter ego, Gizmoduck. In Ducktales, Fenton has the role of Scrooge McDuck's accountant due to his fast counting. Once portrayed as Gizmoduck, he then plays the role of Scrooge's personal security system. In Darkwing Duck, Gizmoduck and Darkwing seem to look at each other eye to eye in a rivalry.

Name: Flint Lockwood
Origin: Cloudy with a Chance of Meatballs
Summary: Flint Lockwood is an eccentric and revolutionary inventor, from the town of Swallow Falls, who dreams of creating amazing things that can change everyone's life. He is the main character and protagonist of Cloudy with a Chance of Meatballs and Cloudy with a Chance of Meatballs 2.

Name: Fluttershy (Human World)
Summary: Fluttershy is one of the main characters of My Little Pony Equestria Girls, and represents the Element of Kindness.

Name: Giriko Kutsuzawa
Summary: Giriko Kutsuzawa (沓沢 ギリコ, Kutsuzawa Giriko) is a Fullbringer and a member of Xcution.

Name: Go Asahi
Summary: Go Asahi is a minor character in Mob Psycho 100. He was a normal person with latent psychic potential until Kenji Mitsuura found and took him to the Awakening Lab. After he was revealed to be an esper with pyrokinetic powers, Go chose to stay at the Awakening Lab in order to learn how to amplify his abilities even further.

Name: Gregory (Five Nights At Freddy's)
Summary: Gregory is the primary protagonist of the indie horror game Five Nights at Freddy's: Security Breach. A young and mysterious boy who finds himself trapped within Freddy Fazbear's Mega Pizzaplex's closing hours. He must then evade the hostile animatronics and the serial killer Vanny while working together with Glamrock Freddy in order to survive the night and escape unharmed.

Name: Gyro Gearloose
Summary: Gyro Gearloose is a Disney character featured in the 1987-1990 Disney cartoon, Ducktales, and in many other types of media. He is Duckburg's most famous inventor, although some of his inventions don't always work out like he intends them to. He's associated with Scrooge McDuck, Donald Duck, and many others.

Name: Hall Family
Summary: The Hall Family (also known as the Sniper Family) refers to a trio of psychopaths in Dead Rising. It consists of Roger Hall, the father and patriarch of the family, Jack Hall, the eldest son of the family, and Thomas Hall, the youngest son of the family. They are encountered in the Entrance Plaza during the scoop Mark of the Sniper.

Name: Henry Emily
Summary: nan

Name: Hero Association
Summary: The Hero Association is an organization founded by the multi-millionaire Agoni after his grandson was saved from a monster by a passerby. Operating independently of the government, the Hero Association recruits various individuals, ordinary and extraordinary alike, to fight for justice against the evil in the world. Those registered within the National Hero Registry database are tasked with protecting civilians from harm against monsters, villains, natural disasters, and other threats and are compensated for their efforts.

Name: Homeless Emperor
Summary: Homeless Emperor was once a common tramp who encountered a mysterious divine entity, who claimed to be "God", that gave him the incredible power of summoning energy spheres similar to little suns, which explode on contact and create huge flaming bursts.

Name: Hsien-Ko
Summary: Hsien-Ko is a playable character in the Darkstalkers series. She and her sister Mei-Ling were twins born in a family of chinese hermits, whose village was once attacked by a pack of Darkstalkers. Their mother sacrificed herself by using a powerful spell to annihilate the monsters, condemning her soul to be trapped in darkness in return. In order to free her, Hsien-Ko and Mei-Ling unleashed a forbidden ritual which turned them both into supernatural creatures and allowed them to hunt the Darkstalkers as Darkhunters. Hsien-Ko gained incredible strength and special powers, though with the risk of falling victim of her savage new nature. Mei-Ling then developed the ability to transform into a talisman and place herself on her sister's forehead, preventing her from losing control.

Name: Isabela Keyes
Summary: Isabela Keyes is the deuteragonist of Dead Rising, the tritagonist of Dead Rising 2: Case West, and a major character in Dead Rising 3. She is also mentioned, but does not make an appearance, in Dead Rising 2.

Name: J. Geil
Origin: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure '''(Part III: Stardust Crusaders)'''
Summary: J. Geil is a minor antagonist in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part III: Stardust Crusaders. Known for his deformed two right hands, he is originally known as the murderer of Polnareff's sister. He is later hired by Dio Brando to kill the Joestars and allies. J. Geil uses his Stand ability alongside partner Hol Horse.

Name: Juniper Montage
Summary: Juniper Montage is the main antagonist in the first 3-parter of the Equestria Girls.

Name: Kevin Flynn
Summary: Kevin Flynn: The Grid, A digital frontier. I tried to picture clusters of information as they moved through the computer. What did they look like? Ships? Motorcycles? Were the circuits like freeways? I kept dreaming of a world I thought I'd never see. And then, one day... Sam Flynn: You got in? Kevin Flynn: That's right man, I got in.

Name: King (One Punch Man)
Summary: King is a character from the series One-Punch Man. Known throughout the world as a legendary man of impressive build, an intimidating scarred face, a towering height and an amazing position as the S-Class Rank 7 hero.

Name: Launch (Dragon Ball)
Summary: Launch (ランチ, Ranchi; lit. "Lunch") is a woman with a strange disorder which causes her to switch between two different personalities each time she sneezes. Her first personality is a sweet, blue haired woman, who is pure-hearted. Her other personality is an angry, trigger-happy, blonde haired woman, who commits crimes for money and is quick to respond with gunfire when angered. Neither of Launch's personalities remembers the other's actions, or anything they said. Her blood type is AB.

Name: Layla Prismriver
Summary: Layla is the fourth and youngest daughter of the Prismriver family. Orphaned after a mishap with her father, each of the 4 daughters went on their path. Only Layla stayed, not willing to leave the mansion that had held much of her memories. Using her powers, she created three poltergeists that resembled her three older sisters, and afterwards, disappeared, alongside the mansion and her three creations.

Name: Lil' DJ Music Man
Summary: Lil DJ Music Man is a toy animatronic that serves as a minor antagonist in Five Nights At Freddy's: Security Breach.

Name: Manfred Von Karma
Summary: Manfred Von Karma is the father of Franziska von Karma, and also the mentor of Miles Edgeworth. He was a renowned Prosecutor who had a 40-year record of no losses during his time as a prosecutor and earned the title "King of Prosecutors" until meeting Phoenix Wright, who put an end to this during the case of the DL-6 Incident and put him in jail for the murder of Gregory Edgeworth, a man he killed for causing him to get a penalty. He was taken to jail and and died shortly after.

Name: Maribel Hearn
Summary: Maribel Hearn is a human from the Outside World, living in a near-future version of Kyoto. Alongside her friend Renko Usami, she is a member of the Secret Sealing Club, a two-member club whose goal is to study the various Otherworlds hidden from the rest of the world, including the Moon, Gensokyo, Hell and the Netherworld.

Name: Maya Fey
Summary: Maya Fey was the younger sibling of Mia Fey. She spent a large amount of her life growing up at Kurain Village, a place where the Fey family and spirit mediums stood. After Maya left in her later years, her sister Mia was murdered and her being pinned as the killer. This is where she met Phoenix Wright, who came to her defense and proved her innocence while proving the real killer guilty. After this, Maya stuck around with Phoenix and helped him on his cases for years to come, until after the DL-6 case, she felt useless to helping Wright because of her inexperience with channeling spirits. So she took a train and headed back to her village to train further and better her skills. Months later, however, in the village, a murder occurred during a spirit summoning gone wrong. Mia was once again pinned as the killer, but again defended by Phoenix who found the true culprit. After this, she went back to helping him with future cases.

Name: Meru Ozawa
Summary: Meru Ozawa (小沢 芽留) is a character in the 1995 Godzilla film Godzilla vs. Destroyah. She is a psychic assigned to G-Force's psychic division alongside Miki Saegusa.

Name: Mia Fey
Summary: Mia Fey was the older sister of Maya Fey and her daughter is Misty Fey. They were part of a group of spirit channelers living in Kurain Village. However, her mother soon turned up missing, having left the village after a spirit channeling for a murder went public and brought embarrassment to their family name. Determined to find out what had happened, Mia left the village to become a lawyer, nearly quitting after her client killed themself in her first case. But when she entered into her second one, she brought justice to the one responsible, and inspired Phoenix Wright, her client she had defended for this case, into becoming a lawyer. She mentored Phoenix when he got his badge, teaching him what he knows about the courthouse. However, after having some powerful evidence against an evil person that would get them in huge trouble, she was killed. Although she has died, her spirit still lives on, and on occasion, comes to give Phoenix some helpful words or insight to help him out.

Name: Michael Afton
Summary: Can you hear me? I don't know if you can hear me. ...I'm sorry.

Name: Midler
Origin: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure '''(Part III: Stardust Crusaders)'''
Summary: Midler is a minor antagonist in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part III: Stardust Crusaders. She is given a Stand and hired by Dio Brando to kill the Joestars and allies. She uses her Stand to ambush them in Avdol's submarine in the Red Sea to sink from damages, eventually confronting them on the seabed.

Name: Miki Saegusa
Summary: Miki Saegusa (三枝 未希) is a psychic character from the Heisei Godzilla series. Employed by the Japanese government and later G-Force, she uses her powers to communicate with and, in some instances, attempt to control Godzilla. She is the most frequently recurring human character in the Godzilla franchise, having appeared in six consecutive films.

Name: Miko Nakadai
Summary: Miko Nakadai is a teenage girl from Japan with a strong love of punk and metal. She's always searching for thrills and causing trouble. As the human partner to the Autobot Bulkhead, she's helped him get over his fear of his own strength by encouraging him to get in trouble with her. Her recklessness is actually a cover for her insecurity, leaping into danger to prove herself. Her fierce loyalty and sheer gall wound up impressing Wheeljack and even Ultra Magnus enough to let her join the Wreckers.

Name: Moe Shishigawara
Summary: Moe Shishigawara (獅子河原 萌笑, Shishigawara Moe) is a high school student from Miyashita Commercial High School. He is also a Fullbringer who once worked under Shūkurō Tsukishima.

Name: Monster Carrot
Summary: Monster Carrot was an antagonist in the early days of Dragon Ball.

Name: Mysterians
Summary: The Mysterians (ミステリアン) are a race of aliens created by Toho that first appeared in the 1957 film The Mysterians.

Name: N'Doul
Origin: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure '''(Part III: Stardust Crusaders)'''
Summary: N'Doul is a minor antagonist in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part III: Stardust Crusaders. A blind man with no fear of death, he is hired by Dio Brando to eliminate the Joestars and allies. He assassinates helicopter pilots from the Speedwagon Foundation in an attempt to eliminate the group and fights them in an Egyptian desert.

Name: Nightmarionne (Five Nights At Freddy's)
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:YouCantWakeFromNightmarionne.ogg

Name: Paul Carson
Summary: Paul Carson is a psychopath turned survivor appearing in Dead Rising.

Name: Pearl Fey
Summary: Pearl Fey was a member of a branch family of the Fey clan and the daughter of Morgan Fet. She had lived the first part of her life in Kurain Village, never have seen the world beyond it. She lived with her mother, and her sisters, Maya and Mia, until Mia had left to pursue a career as a defense attorney. Later, she met Phoenix Wright though completely avoided him, until a murder occurred later, and he showed her Maya's Magatama. She immediately became as helpful as she possibly could, figuring out this was the "Mr Nick" Maya spoke so much about. Due to having seen many bad marriages, after she met with Phoenix Wright, she would try and force a romantic relationship on Phoenix and her sister Maya. With her help, Phoenix was able to solve the case and prove Maya's innocence. From there, Phoenix and Maya would make some visits back to the village, and eventually, Pearl became more active in helping others of Phoenix's investigations in her later years.

Name: Pinkie Pie (Human World)
Summary: Pinkie Pie is one of the main characters of My Little Pony Equestria Girls, and represents the Element of Laughter.

Name: Princess Cadance
Summary: Princess Cadance is a secondary character in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Princess Celestia
Summary: Princess Celestia is a major character in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic and is one of the many Alicorns seen in the series, so far. She is Twilight Sparkle's mentor and the one responsible for raising the sun, every day. Celestia rules over all of Equestria and is portrayed as a wise, kind, and beloved leader.

Name: Princess Luna
Key: '''Princess Luna/Nightmare Moon''' | '''Vice Principal Luna (Equestria Girls counterpart)'''
Summary: Princess Luna is a former antagonist and recurring character in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Rarity (Human World)
Summary: Rarity is one of the main characters of My Little Pony Equestria Girls, and represents the Element of Generosity.

Name: Renko Usami
Summary: Renko Usami is a human from the Outside World, living in a near-future version of Kyoto. Alongside her friend Maribel Hearn, she is a member of the Secret Sealing Club, a two-member club whose goal is to study the various Otherworlds hidden from the rest of the world, including the Moon, Gensokyo, Hell and the Netherworld.

Name: Rintarou Okabe
Summary: Rintarou Okabe (岡部 倫太郁, Okabe Rintarō), a.k.a Okarin, a portmanteau of the Oka- from his surname and the Rin- from his given name, is a self-proclaimed mad scientist and the main protagonist of Steins;Gate.

Name: Riruka Dokugamine
Summary: Riruka Dokugamine (毒どくヶが峰みね リルカ, Dokugamine Riruka?) is a Fullbringer and formerly member No. 003 of the organization known as Xcution.

Name: Sandbag
Summary: Sandbag is a recurring character in the Smash Bros. series. It usually serves as the target of the Home-Run Contest.

Name: Space Hunter Nebula M Aliens
Summary: The M Space Hunter Nebula Aliens (Ｍ宇宙ハンター星雲人), also known as the Nebulans, are an alien species who first appeared in the 1972 Godzilla film Godzilla vs. Gigan. Insect-like aliens resembling gigantic upright cockroaches, the Nebulans hail from an unnamed homeworld located within the M Space Hunter Nebula. Having evolved into the dominant lifeforms on their planet following the extinction of a human-like species that existed before them, the Nebulans were forced to seek out a new home planet as the lasting pollution left behind by their predecessors rendered their world uninhabitable. The Nebulans discovered Earth, a planet similar to their own inhabited by a species much like their predecessors who were in the process of destroying the planet through industrial pollution. Planning to save the Earth from humanity and establish a new peaceful utopia for their kind, a Nebulan invasion force posed as a charitable organization constructing the World Children's Land theme park, using the park's Godzilla Tower attraction as a staging ground for their invasion. The Nebulans summoned their own cybernetic monster creation, Gigan, along with the dreaded King Ghidorah to eradicate human civilization. A group of humans who were privy to the conspiracy foiled the Nebulans and destroyed their base of operations, while Godzilla and Anguirus drove off the space monsters. A year later, the Seatopians, themselves in the process of launching an invasion of the surface world with their own monster Megalon, contacted the Nebulans and asked for Gigan's assistance. The Nebulans obliged and sent Gigan to assist in the invasion, but both he and Megalon were repelled by Godzilla and Jet Jaguar.

Name: Starlight Glimmer
Key: '''From Season 5 to 8''' | '''Series Finale onward''' | '''Equestria Girls Human Self'''
Summary: Starlight Glimmer was the main antagonist of Season 5 of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic, and later one of the show's main protagonists.

Name: Sung Jin-Woo (Novel)
Summary: nan

Name: The Judge (Ace Attorney)
Summary: There is not much known about The Judge. All that is known is The Judge is the one often presiding over the cases in Ace Attorney. While he is sometimes bumbling, and a little slow with details, he still stands for truth and justice. Even refusing to leave the courtroom despite the witness and killer threat of He courtroom with a bomb, until a verdict had been passed down. He does his best with his verdicts and has claimed he had never gotten a verdict wrong in his life many times before

Name: Twilight Sparkle (Pony World)
Key: '''Unicorn Form''' | '''Alicorn Form''' | '''The Ending of the End Alicorn Form''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''All Alicorn Magic''' | '''Post-Timeskip Alicorn Form''' | '''Rainbow Power''' | '''Equestria Girls Human form'''
Summary: Twilight Sparkle is the main protagonist of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Twilight Sparkle (Sci-Twi)
Summary: Twilight Sparkle is one of the main protagonists in the My Little Pony: Equestria Girls series.

Name: Vignette Valencia
Summary: Vignette Valencia is a character in Equestria Girls.

Name: Wallflower Blush
Summary: Wallflower Blush is the hidden main antagonist of the My Little Pony: Equestria Girls special, Forgotten Friendship.

Name: Yellow Rabbit (Fazbear Frights)
Summary: The Yellow Rabbit is the main antagonist of the titular first story of the first Fazbear Frights book: Into the Pit. It is a supernatural entity of unknown nature which stalks Oswald during his trips to the past and eventually follows him home, impersonating his father. It is killed when it is seemingly strangled to death by the ropes in the ball pit.

Name: Yukio Hans Vorarlberna
